Captain Richard E. Fleming ( November 2 , 1917 - -June 5 , 1942 ) was a United States Marine who received the Medal of Honor for his heroism in World War II during the Battle of Midway .

Fred Faulkner Lester ( April 29 , 1926 -- June 8 , 1945 ) was a United States Navy hospital corpsman who was killed in action during World War II while assigned to a Marine Corps rifle company during the Battle of Okinawa in 1945 .
Anselm Tupper ( 1763 - -1808 ) was an officer of the Continental Army during the American Revolutionary War , a pioneer to the Ohio Country , and one of the founders of Marietta , Ohio , the first permanent American settlement in the Northwest Territory .
Dimitrios Ioannou ( Greek : Δημήτριος Ιωάννου , 1861 - -1926 ) was a senior Greek Army officer who fought in the Macedonian Front during World War I and in the opening stages of the Greco - Turkish War of 1919 - -1922 .

No . 108 Squadron RAF was originally a squadron of the Royal Flying Corps during World War I which continued to serve with the Royal Air Force in World War II .

Delbert L. Bristol ( September 20 , 1918 -- April 3 , 1980 ) served as an Aviation Artillery Officer attached to the II Corps during World War II and was the first such officer to create a Corps level Air Artillery staff .

Zithulele Sinqe ( 9 June 1963 -- 22 December 2011 ) was a South African long distance runner .
Giovanni Battista Fornovo ( 1521 - -1575 ) was an Italian architect , active in a late - Renaissance style in Parma .
Stephen Popham ( 5 July 1745 -- 13 June 1795 ) was a British politician and solicitor who is remembered for improving the residential locality of Georgetown in the city of Chennai , India and reforming the civic and police administration .
Chauncy Townsend ( 23 February 1708 -- 28 March 1770 ) was a businessman and a Member of Parliament ( MP ) in the British Parliament .
Oliver Lanard Fassig ( 1860 - -1936 ) was an American meteorologist and climatologist who worked for the United States Weather Bureau initially as part of the Signal Corps of the United States War Department and later affiliated with the United States Department of Agriculture .
Colonel Ian Lapraik , DSO , OBE , MC & Bar , TD , ( 13 September 1915 -- 15 March 1985 ) was a distinguished officer in the Special Air Service Regiment , despite potentially crippling childhood illness .
Jeanne Dumée ( born Paris 1660 ; died 1706 ) was a French astronomer and author .
Herbert Melville Guest ( 29 January 1853 -- 29 June 1938 ) was an author , newspaper owner and politician of the Transvaal .
Henry McGee ( 14 May 1929 -- 28 January 2006 ) was a British actor , best known as straight man to Benny Hill for many years .
Malik - Shah III ( died 1160 ) ruled as Sultan of Great Seljuq from 1152 - 53 .
Henry Essex Edgeworth ( 1745 -- 22 May 1807 ) , also known as L'Abbé Edgeworth de Firmont , was an Irish Catholic priest and confessor of Louis XVI .
Jonathan Lindley ( 1756 - -1828 ) was an 18th - century member of the North Carolina legislature , land speculator , and one of the original settlers of Orange County , Indiana .
Francis Augustus Cox ( 1783 - -1853 ) was a prominent English Baptist minister .
Kate Buchdahl ( 30 September 1964 -- 10 December 1992 ) was a classically trained , Australian - born , violinist .
Aedanus Burke ( 16 June 1743 -- 30 March 1802 ) was a soldier , judge , and United States Representative from South Carolina .
John Miller Gray ( 1850 - 1894 ) was a Scottish art critic and the first curator of the Scottish National Portrait Gallery .
Jack Coolahan ( 22 August 1914 -- 22 April 1988 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and Footscray in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Horace Goldin ( 17 December 1873 -- 22 April 1939 ) was a stage magician who was noted for his lightning fast presentation style and who achieved international fame with his versions of the Sawing a woman in half illusion .
Elizabeth Jesser Reid ( 25 December 1789 - 1 April 1866 ) , was an English social reformer , anti - slavery activist and philanthropist .
Norman Pentland ( 9 September 1912 -- 28 October 1972 ) was a British Labour Member of Parliament for Chester - le - Street .
Carl Johann Philipp Noé Richard Anschütz FRSE ( Hon ) ( 10 March 1852 -- 8 January 1937 ) was a German organic chemist .
Colonel Peter Gerahty CBE ( 1 September 1921 -- 15 November 2013 ) was one of the last surviving British Army officers to have served with 6th Airborne Division in Operation Varsity on 24 March 1945 : the largest airborne operation in the history of warfare , part of Operation Plunder : the Rhine Crossing in March 1945 .
John Hothby ( Otteby , Hocby , Octobi , Ottobi , c. 1410 - 1487 ) , also known by his Latinised names Johannes Ottobi or Johannes de Londonis , was an English Renaissance composer and musical theorist who travelled widely in Europe and gained an international reputation for his work .
Sir Thomas Gower , 1st Baronet of Stittenham ( 1584 - -1651 ) was an early member of the Leveson - Gower family .
Pedro Segura y Sáenz ( 4 December 1880 - -8 April 1957 ) was a Spanish Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church who served as Archbishop of Toledo from 1927 to 1931 , and Archbishop of Seville from 1937 until his death .
Saint Ida of Herzfeld ( c. 788 -- c. 825 ) was the widow of a Saxon duke who devoted her life to the poor following the death of her husband in 811 .
Ch . Sarup Singh ( 6 October 1919 -- 23 August 2009 ) was an Indian legislator .
Baldwin Hamey the Elder , M.D. , also Baudouin Hamey ( 1568 - -1640 ) was a Flemish physician who settled in London .
Eugène Durocher ( 27 August 1881 -- 10 May 1944 ) was a Canadian politician , serving in municipal and national politics .
Joseph Gouge Greenwood ( 1821 - -1894 ) was an English classical scholar , second principal of Owens College , Manchester , and vice - chancellor of the Victoria University , Manchester .
Francesco Corneliani ( 1740 - 1815 ) was an Italian painter , mainly active in a Neoclassic style in his native Milan .
Richard Ash Kingsford ( 1821 - -1902 ) was an alderman and mayor of Brisbane Municipal Council , a Member of the Legislative Assembly of Queensland , Australia , and a mayor of Cairns , Queensland .
Edward Sturgis Ingraham ( April ? , 1852 - -August 16 ? , 1926 ) was the first superintendent of the Seattle Public Schools , a noted mountaineer who climbed Mount Rainier 13 times , and a leader in the effort to establish Mount Rainier National Park .
Robert Haggiag ( 1913 -- 1 March 2009 ) was an American film producer .
Zhang Ziqian ( simplified Chinese : 张子谦 ; traditional Chinese : 張子謙 , 1899 - -1991 ) , a famous seven - string zither qin player , was born in Yangzhou , Jiangsu Province , Qing .
Wick R. Miller ( 1932 - -1994 ) was an American linguist most well known for his work on Keresan languages and Uto - Aztecan , especially Shoshoni and Guarijio .
Otto Gebühr ( 29 May 1877 -- 14 March 1954 ) was a German theatre and film actor , who appeared in 102 films released between 1917 and 1954 .
Jean - Baptiste Collin de Sussy ( 1 January 1750 - 7 July 1826 ) was a senior official and politician .
Alonso de Fonseca y Ulloa ( also Alonso I de Fonseca)(died 1473 ) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as Archbishop of Seville ( 1454 - 1465 and 1469 - 1473 ) , Archbishop of Santiago de Compostela ( 1465 - 1469 ) , and Bishop of Ávila ( 1545 - 1454 ) .
Prince George of Denmark and Norway , Duke of Cumberland ( Danish : Jørgen ; 2 April 1653 -- 28 October 1708 ) , was the husband of Queen Anne , who reigned over Great Britain from 1702 .
Gwenllian of Wales or Gwenllian ferch Llywelyn ( June 1282 -- 7 June 1337 ) was the only child of Llywelyn ap Gruffudd , the last native Prince of Wales ( Welsh : Tywysog Cymru ) .
Giovanni Rossignoli ( 3 December 1882 -- 27 June 1954 ) was an Italian professional road bicycle racer who won 3 Giro d'Italia stages during his career .
George Barnston ( c. 1800 -- 14 March 1883 ) was a fur trader and a naturalist born in Edinburgh , Scotland .
Sir William Campbell Wylie ( 14 May 1905 -- August 1992 ) was a New Zealand born colonial judge who was the last Chief Justice of Sarawak , North Borneo and Brunei and the first Chief Justice of Borneo .
Odette Kahn ( 1923 - -1982 ) was a leading authority on wine and editor of the La Revue du vin de France ( Review of French wine ) and of Cuisine et Vins de France ( Food and Wines of France ) .
Andrej Brázda - Jankovský ( or Andrej Brázda ) ( 26 July 1915 -- 2008 ) was a Canadian - based writer who wrote in the Slovak language .
General Tapishwar Narain Raina ( 1921 -- 19 May 1980 ) was the Chief of the Army Staff of the Indian Army during 1975 - -78 .
Professor Radha Krishna Choudhary ( 15 February 1921 - 15 March 1985 ) was a historian , thinker and writer of Bihar .
Marjorie Hillis ( 1889 - 1971 ) was an American author of popular nonfiction books for women in the 1930s .
Robert Millner Shackleton FRS ( 30 December 1909 -- 3 May 2001 ) was a British field geologist who developed an interest in the geology of East Africa .
Henrietta Greville MBE , née Wyse ( 9 October 1861 -- 29 August 1964 ) was an Australian labour organiser and one of the first women to run for the Australian Parliament with major party endorsement .
Thomas Bland Strange ( 15 September 1831 -- 9 July 1925 ) , known as ' Gunner Jingo ' , was a British soldier noted for his service with the Canadian militia during the North - West Rebellion of 1885 .
Faithful Teate ( c. 1626 -- 1666 ) was a Protestant clergyman and poet from County Cavan , Ireland .
Rajadhiraja Chola II ( 1166 - -1178 CE ) reigned as the Chola king succeeding Rajaraja Chola II . According to historian N. Sethuraman , Rajadhiraja was not the direct descendant of Rajaraja Chola II but was a son of his sister .
Lionel Charles Knights ( 15 May 1906 -- 8 March 1997 ) was an English literary critic , an authority on Shakespeare and his period .
Jack Randle ( 23 August 1902 -- May 1990 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a left back .
Yerucham ben Meshullam ( Hebrew : ירוחם בן משולם‎ , 1290 - 1350 ) , often called Rabbenu Yerucham ( רבנו ירוחם ) , was a prominent rabbi and posek during the period of the Rishonim .
Hex Hector ( born April 15 , 1965 ) , is an American dance remixer .
Aert van der Neer , or Aernout or Artus ( c. 1603 -- 9 November 1677 ) , was a landscape painter of the Dutch Golden Age , specializing in small night scenes lit only by moonlight and fires , and snowy winter landscapes , both often looking down a canal or river .
Dennis Puleston ( 30 December 1905 - 8 June 2001 ) was a British - born American environmentalist , adventurer and designer .
John Manningham ( died 1622 ) was an English lawyer and diarist , a contemporary source for Elizabethan era and Jacobean era life and the London dramatic world , including William Shakespeare .
Thomas Doggett ( or Dogget ) ( ca . 1640 -- 20 September 1721 ) was an Irish actor .
Bernard Cowan ( 1922 -- July 17 , 1990 ) was a Canadian actor , announcer and writer .
Tom Maguire ( 28 March 1892 -- 5 July 1993 ) was an Irish republican who held the rank of commandant - general in the Western Command of the Irish Republican Army ( IRA ) and led the South Mayo flying column .
William Addams Williams ( 1787 - -1861 ) was a Welsh lawyer , landowner and politician .
Hugo Meurer ( 28 May 1869 - -4 January 1960 ) was a Vice - Admiral of the Kaiserliche Marine ( German Imperial Navy ) .
Vera Albreht ( 12 February 1895 -- 25 May 1971 ) was a Slovene poet , writer , publicist and translator .
Mohammed Fazle Rabbee ( occasionally spelled Rabbi , Bengali : মোহাম্মদ ফজলে রাব্বী ; 21 September 1932 -- 15 December 1971 ) was a renowned cardiologist and a published medical researcher .
Trần Hiến Tông ( 1319 - -1341 ) , given name Trần Vượng ( 陳旺 ) , was the sixth emperor of the Trần dynasty who reigned Đại Việt from 1329 to 1341 .
Adolphe Cohn ( 1851 -- 1930 ) was a Franco - American educator , born in Paris .
Arthur Mülverstedt ( 30 June 1894 -- 10 August 1941 ) was a SS - Gruppenführer und Generalleutnant der Schutzpolizei during World War II ; he was a Commander of the 4th SS Polizei Division and the first SS General to be killed in action .
Leonte Tismăneanu ( born Leonid Tisminetski ; 1913 - -1981 ) was a Romanian communist activist and propagandist .
Ferdynand Zarzycki ( 1888 , Tarnów - 1958 ) was a Polish general and politician .
Ennappadam Venkatarama Bhagavatar ( 1880 - -1961 ) was a composer of Carnatic music .
Jenny Diver , née Mary Young ( 1700 -- 18 March 1741 ) was a notorious British pickpocket , one of the most famous of her day .
Thorburn Brailsford Robertson ( 4 March 1884 -- 18 January 1930 ) was an Australian physiologist and biochemist .
Ambrose St. John ( 1815 -- 24 May 1875 ) was an English Oratorian and convert to Catholicism .
Bill Gregg ( 25 August 1914 -- 23 January 2000 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Princess Charlotte of Prussia ( Viktoria Elisabeth Auguste Charlotte ; 24 July 1860 -- 1 October 1919 ) was Duchess of Saxe - Meiningen as the wife of Bernhard III , the duchy 's last ruler .
Maurice Kenyon Taylor ( 26 June 1908 - 29 June 1986 ) was a British electrical engineer and inventor responsible for many diverse technological developments and inventions , producing over 70 patents during his career .
Abraham Khalfon ( Hebrew : אברהם כלפון‎ , 1741 - -1819 ) was a Sephardi Jewish community leader , historian , scholar , and paytan in Tripoli , Libya .
Peronne Goguillon ( died 29 May 1679 ) was an alleged French witch .
Alfred Searcy ( 4 January 1854 -- 1 October 1925 ) was a South Australian public servant and writer .
Daniel Lind Lagerlöf ( born 6 February 1969 ; missing since 6 October 2011 ) is a presumed dead Swedish director , screenwriter and producer .
Kaare Støylen ( 3 October 1909 -- 22 August 1989 ) was a Norwegian Doctor of Theology and Lutheran bishop , born in Kristiania .
Duncan Macgregor Graham ( March 1867 -- 19 October 1942 ) was Labour MP for Hamilton from 1918 to his death .
Nicolas Huet the Younger ( 1770 Louvre - 26 December 1830 Paris ) , aka Nicolas Huet II or as Nicolas Huet le Jeune , was a French natural history illustrator , active 1788 - 1827 .
On the evening of 22 August 2001 , At the age of 82 , and Sharad Talwalkar died due to a heart attack in his home in Pune .
Jacob Tanner ( 15 October 1865 -- 25 January 1964 ) was a Norwegian American Lutheran minister , educator and religious author .
Hother Erich Werner Bøttger ( 18 May 1801 -- 28 October 1857 ) was a Norwegian politician .
Gao Renhou ( 高仁厚 ) ( d. 886 ) was an army general late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty who served under the warlord Chen Jingxuan the military governor of Xichuan Circuit ( 西川 , headquartered in modern Chengdu , Sichuan ) .
Liang Boqiang 梁伯强 ( 1 February 1899 - -28 November 1968 , Jiaying , Guangdong , China ) Medicine educationalist , and pathologist , member of Chinese Academy of Sciences , pioneer pathologist in China .
Fausto Tommei ( 29 July 1909 - 23 July 1978 ) was an Italian actor , voice actor and presenter .
Sir Thomas John Mellis Napier KCMG ( 24 October 1882 -- 22 March 1976 ) was a judge of the Supreme Court of South Australia between 28 February 1924 and 28 February 1967 , and Chief Justice of South Australia from 25 February 1942 until 28 February 1967 .
Léopold Harzé ( 1831 - -1893 ) was a Belgian sculptor who worked in Brussels .
Juan Tuñas Bajeneta , nicknamed `` Romperredes '' ( 17 July 1917 -- 4 April 2011 ) was a Cuban footballer .
France Vodnik ( 1903 - -1986 ) was a Slovenian literary critic , essayist , translator and poet from Ljubljana .
John Gillanders Turriff ( 14 December 1855 -- 10 November 1930 ) was a Canadian parliamentarian .
Thomas Cathinco Bang ( 25 January 1827 -- 13 April 1902 ) was Norwegian Minister of the Interior in 1884 .
Bárid mac Ímair ( also referred to as Barith , Baraid , and Bard ; Old Norse : Bárðr or Bárǫðr ; d. 881 ) was a ninth - century King of Dublin .
Sierk Coolsma ( Dutch pronunciation : ( sirk ˈkoːlsmaː ) ; 26 January 1840 -- 20 March 1926 ) was a Dutch Protestant missionary who wrote extensively on the Sundanese language .
William Newcomb ( died 1999 ) , a professor and theoretical physicist at the University of California 's Lawrence Livermore Laboratory , is best known as the creator of Newcomb 's paradox , devised in 1960 .
Kambanthodath Kunhan Vishwanatham or Kambanthodath Vishwanatham ( 4 November 1914 -- 17 or 18 August 1992 ) was governor of the Indian state of Gujarat .

Major - General John Sydney Lethbridge CB , CBE , MC ( 11 December 1897 -- 11 August 1961 ) was a British soldier .
John Véron ( died 1563 ) was a French Protestant controversialist and preacher , known for his activities in England .

Afawarq Walda Samayat , or Afework Woldesemait , ( died 5 November 1935 ) was an Ethiopian administrator , and commander .
Olga Spiridonović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Олга Спиридоновић ; 11 June 1923 -- 15 May 1994 ) was a Serbian film , theatre and television actress who starred in a number of Yugoslav films .
Sir George Thurston KBE ( 1869 - 22 January 1950 ) was a leading British naval architect in the early half of the 20th century .
José Maria da Ponte e Horta ( b. 1824 , Faro -- d. 1892 ) was a Portuguese noble who served as a colonial administrator and soldier in the Portuguese Empire .
John Ya - Otto ( 10 February 1938 - 25 May 1994 ) was a Namibian trade unionist , politician , author and diplomat .
Abraham Gershon of Kitov , also known as Rabbi Gershon of Brody , was probably born in or near Kuty ( Kitov ) , Poland around 1701 and died in Jerusalem in 1761 .
Ernest Montaut ( 1879 - -1909 ) was a French poster artist who died at an early age .
Dmitry Kardovsky ( 5 September 1866 - 9 February 1943 ) was a Russian artist , illustrator and stage designer .
Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy , 7th Baronet , ( 19 April 1913 -- 10 August 2006 ) was an Indian philanthropist .
Ottó Misángyi ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈotːoː ˈmiʃaːnɟi ) ; 20 April 1895 -- 30 November 1977 ) was a Hungarian athletics coach , sports official and university professor .
Alden Bradford ( 17 November 1765 -- 26 October 1843 ) was an American politician , clergyman and author who served as the 5th Massachusetts Secretary of the Commonwealth .
Walter Hearne ( 15 January 1864 -- 2 April 1925 ) was an English cricketer for Kent CCC .
Anders Johan Ture Rangström ( 30 November 1884 -- 11 May 1947 ) belonged to a new generation of Swedish composers who in the first decade of the 20th century introduced modernism to their compositions .
Lizzie Black Kander ( 1858 - -1940 ) was a progressive reformer and the founder of a settlement house in Milwaukee , where she originated The Settlement Cookbook .
Robert Trewick Bone ( 24 September 1790 -- 5 May 1840 ) was an English painter of sacred , classical and genre scenes .
Willem Arondeus ( 22 August 1894 -- 1 July 1943 ) was a Dutch artist and author , who joined the Dutch anti - Nazi resistance movement during World War II . He participated in the bombing of the Amsterdam public records office to hinder the Nazi German effort to identify Dutch Jews .
Rodolphe Samuel Schenk ( 29 October 1888 , Macorna , Victoria -- 7 August 1969 ) was an Australian missionary .
Fu Qian ( died 263 ) was a military general of the state of Shu Han in the Three Kingdoms period .
Pancho Daniel ( ? -1858 ) was a Californio bandit , leader of the Flores Daniel Gang who was lynched in November 1858 while awaiting trial for his involvement in the murder of Los Angeles County Sheriff James R. Barton .
James Summers ( 5 June 1828 -- 1 February 1891 ) was a British scholar of English literature , hired by the Meiji government of the Empire of Japan to establish an English language curriculum at the Kaisei Gakuin ( the forerunner of Tokyo Imperial University in 1873 ) .
Harriet Pelham - Holles , Duchess of Newcastle - upon - Tyne ( 1701 -- 17 July 1776 ) was the wife of the British statesman and Prime Minister Thomas Pelham - Holles , 1st Duke of Newcastle - upon - Tyne .
Anna Sophie Schack ( 1689 - -1760 ) , was a Danish noble , landowner and builder .
Eiliv Odde Hauge ( 10 November 1913 -- 3 July 1971 ) was a Norwegian screenwriter , author and resistance member .
Ted Pulford was born in Saskatoon , Saskatchewan on 14 December 1914 of Welsh emigrant parents and died 11 April 1994 .
Morgan Lloyd ( 1822 - 5 September 1893 ) was a Welsh Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1874 to 1885 .
James Craufurd , Lord Ardmillan ( 12 September 1805 -- 7 September 1876 ) was a Scottish judge .
Géza Gyóni ( 25 June 1884 - 25 June 1917 ) was a Hungarian poet under the rule of the Austro - Hungarian Empire .
Samuel `` Sam '' Maguire ( 1877 -- 6 February 1927 ) , an Irish republican and Gaelic footballer , is chiefly remembered as the eponym of the Sam Maguire Cup , given to the All - Ireland Senior Champions of Gaelic football .
Roelof Diodati ( Dordrecht , 28 July 1658 -- Batavia , 10 March 1723 ) was a governor of Dutch Mauritius in the late 17th century .
George Beasley ( 26 April 1902 -- 6 August 1962 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Frank Rickwood ( 1921 - 2009 ) was an Australian businessman in the oil industry .
Jørgen Thormøhlen ( c 1640 -- 25 December 1708 ) was a Norwegian merchant and industrialist .
Bjørn Endreson ( 20 January 1922 -- 12 November 1998 ) was a Norwegian actor , stage producer and theatre director .
Charlie van Gelderen ( 1913 - -26 October 2001 ) was a South African Trotskyist active in the British Labour movement from the 1930s .
Peter Frilingos ( 1944 - -2004 ) was a sports journalist and commentator , best known for his work as a rugby league writer .
Nikki Sudden ( 19 July 1956 -- 26 March 2006 ) , born Adrian Nicholas Godfrey , was a prolific English singer - songwriter and guitarist .
Hans - Joachim Koellreutter ( 2 September 1915 -- 13 September 2005 ) was a composer , teacher and musicologist .
Emine Semiye Önasya ( 28 March 1864 - 1944 ) , mostly known as Emine Semiye and Emine Vahide , was a Turkish writer and a daughter of Ahmed Cevdet Pasha .
Byron Lavoy Cockrell ( 1935 - -2007 ) was an American rocket scientist and engineer who conducted research and development of micro - motors for solid propellant rockets and was later involved in the Minuteman ICBM program .
Alexandros Soutsos ( Greek : Ἀλέξανδρος Σοῦτσος ) ( 1803 - -1863 ) was a Greek poet from a prominent Phanariote family .
Tapio Vilpponen ( 31 May 1913 − 31 August 1994 ) was a Finnish screenwriter , set designer , costume designer , painter , graphic artist , interior designer , sculptor , copywriter , journalist , cartoonist and columnist .
Arthur Stanley Brown ( 20 May 1912 -- 6 July 2002 ) was charged in 1998 for the 26 August 1970 rape and murder of Judith and Susan Mackay in Townsville , Queensland .
Guillaume IV de Melun was also employed in many other important occasions and killed at the Battle of Agincourt on 25 October 1415 .
Rosa Bonheur , born Marie - Rosalie Bonheur , ( 16 March 1822 -- 25 May 1899 ) was a French animalière , realist artist , and sculptor .
Kirill Sokolov ( 27 September 1930 -- 22 May 2004 ) was a Russian painter , sculptor , print - maker and stage designer .
Seong Hui - ahn(korean:성희안;成希顔 , 1461 - -1513 ) was a Korean Joseon Dynasty politician and Neo - Confucianism Philosopher served as Prime Minister or Chief State Councillor during the reign of King Jungjong in 1513 until his death .
María Martina Ibaibarriaga Elorriaga ( 26 January 1788 -- 6 June 1849 ) was a Spanish guerrilla leader during the Peninsular War ( 1807 - -14 ) .
Henry F. Starbuck ( 1860 -- 1935 ) was an American architect and a specialist in church architecture .
Jean Fombertaux ( 1935 - -1976 , Sydney , Australia ) was a French émigré architect who spent most of his career designing buildings in and around Sydney .
Keeseekoowenin ( c. 1818 - 10 April 1906 ) was a First Nations leader during the period when Canada was expanding into the prairie provinces of Manitoba , Saskatchewan and Alberta .
George Lothrop Starr ( 14 July 1878 -- 1925 ) was a Canadian Dean of Ontario from 1917 to 1925 .
Maj Lillemor Arvidsson ( 1 May 1943 -- 23 April 2012 ) was a Swedish trade union leader and the Governor of Gotland from 1998 to 2004 .
Haukur Clausen ( 8 November 1928 -- 1 May 2003 ) was an Olympic athlete and later a dentist .
Bullen Reymes ( 28 December 1613 - 18 December 1672 ) was an English courtier , diplomat and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1672 .
Victor Tortez ( juillet 18 1843 -- 1890 ) was a French painter of the beaux arts school , taught by Jean - Jacques Henner .
Prem Singh Brahma ( Bodo : प्रेम सिंह ब्रह्मा ; 1952 -- 2007 ) was the former leader of the Bodo Liberation Tigers Force and deputy chief from 1994 to 1996 .
Raymond Greenleaf ( 1 January 1892 - 29 October 1963 ) was an American actor , best known for All the King 's Men ( 1949 ) , Angel Face ( 1952 ) , and Pinky ( 1949 ) .
Ismail Mustafa or Ismail Mustafa al - Falaki ( 1825 - 27 July 1901 ) was an Egyptian astronomer and mathematician .
Jonathan Peter Sharp ( 20 February 1964 -- 29 May 2009 ) , better known by the pseudonym Jonny Dollar , was an English record producer and songwriter .
Sir ( Lawrence ) Emmet McDermott KBE ( 6 September 1911 -- 31 August 2002 ) was an Australian dentist , politician and Lord Mayor of Sydney between 1969 and 1972 .
Louise Élisabeth d'Orléans ( Spanish : Luisa Isabel ; 11 December 1709 -- 16 June 1742 ) was Queen consort of Spain as the wife of King Louis I.
Fujiwara no Kinsue ( 藤原 公季 ; 957 - -1029 ) , also known as Kaikō , was a Japanese statesman , courtier and politician during the Heian period .
Yvonne Cernota ( 19 September 1979 -- 12 March 2004 ) was a German bobsledder who competed from 2000 to 2004 at the position of the brakeswomen .
Mathew Forde , also spelt ' Matthew Forde ' ( 17 May 1785 -- 5 August 1837 ) was an Irish landowner and politician .
The Hon . David John Smith ( May 20 , 1907 -- 1976 ) was the third son of Frederick Smith , 2nd Viscount Hambleden and Lady Esther Gore .
John Paul Visscher ( 1895 - -1950 ) was an American protozoologist .
Khagendranath Mitra ( Bengali : খগেন্দ্রনাথ মিত্র ) ( 1896 - -1978 ) was a writer for children of Bengal .
William of Cassingham ( or Willikin of the Weald ) ( died 1257 ) was a country squire of Cassingham ( now Kensham ) in Kent at the time of the First Barons ' War .
Val Bennett ( born Lovall Bennett , ? , died 1991 ) was a Jamaican tenor saxophonist and jazz and roots reggae musician who began his career in the 1940s .
Marc Iliffe ( 27 June 1972 -- 11 February 2003 ) was a British strongman famous for being the winner of Britain 's Strongest Man contest in 2002 .
Hiram Abas ( 1932 in Istanbul -- 26 September 1990 ) was a Turkish intelligence official in the National Intelligence Organization ( MIT ) .
John William Crombie ( 4 March 1858 -- 22 March 1908 ) was a Scottish woollen manufacturer , folklorist and Liberal Party politician .
Mary MacLane ( May 1 , 1881 -- c. 6 August 1929 ) was a controversial Canadian - born American writer whose frank memoirs helped usher in the confessional style of autobiographical writing .
Meir Atlas ( Hebrew : מאיר אטלס‎ ; 1848 - -1926 ) was the rabbi of numerous communities in pre - World War II Europe and one of the founders of the Telz Yeshiva .
Andrew Leith Adams FRSE , FRS ( 21 March 1827 -- 29 July 1882 ) was a Scottish physician , naturalist and geologist .
Elizabeth Lamb , Viscountess Melbourne ( née Elizabeth Milbanke ; 1751 -- 1818 ) was one of the most influential of the political hostesses of the extended Regency period , and the wife of Whig politician Peniston Lamb , 1st Viscount Melbourne .
Harry Liston ( 7 October 1843 -- 12 April 1929 ) was an English comedian and actor who appeared in music hall , variety shows and other entertainments during the Victorian era and in the first decades of the 20th century .
Adrien Meunier ( 24 December 1905 -- 31 October 1971 ) was a Liberal party , initially independent Liberal , member of the Canadian House of Commons .
Păuna Greceanu - Cantacuzino ( died 1740 ) , was a Princess consort of Wallachia by marriage to Ştefan Cantacuzino ( r. 1714 - -1716 ) .
Hugh Montgomerie , 1st Earl of Eglinton ( c. 1460 -- June 1545 ) was a Scottish peer .
Friedrich Wilhelm Rust ( 6 July 1739 -- 28 February 1796 ) was a German violinist , pianist and composer .
José Beyaert ( 1 October 1925 -- 11 June 2005 ) was a French professional cyclist who , during the 1940s and 1950s , was the 1948 Olympics road race champion .
John Bascom Crenshaw ( 1861 - -1942 ) was the head of the Department of Modern Languages at the Georgia Institute of Technology for 38 years , and also served as the school 's first athletic director , in which capacity he started Georgia Tech 's lacrosse team .
Hester Maria Elphinstone , Viscountess Keith , born Hester Maria Thrale ( 17 September 1764 -- 31 March 1857 ) , was a British literary correspondent and intellectual .
Titus Cassius Severus ( died in 32 AD ) was an ancient Roman rhetor from the gens Cassia .
Peder Claussøn Friis ( 1 April 1545 -- 15 October 1614 ) was a Norwegian clergyman , author and historian .
Luce Langevin - Dubus ( born 26 December 1899 in Marissel in Oise , died on 27 August 2002 in Paris ) was a French physicist and biologist , teacher of physical sciences and biology at Fénelon highschool in Paris and a communist activist .
Hana Zelinová ( 20 July 1914 -- 2004 ) was a Slovak prose writer and dramatist .
Sir John Dackombe ( 1570 -- 29 January 1618 ) was the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster between 1616 and 1618 .
Vernon Ahmadjian ( 19 May 1930 , Whitinsville , Massachusetts -- 13 March 2012 , Falmouth , Massachusetts ) was a distinguished professor at Clark University in Worcester , Massachusetts .
Antoine Ignace Melling ( 1763 - -1831 ) was a painter , architect and voyager who is counted among the `` Levantine Artists '' .
His Honour Sir Thomas Artemus Jones KC LLD ( 1871 -- 15 October 1943 ) , was a Welsh Judge , journalist , nationalist and Liberal Party politician who campaigned for the Welsh language .
Elisabeth Dhanens ( 1915 -- 11 March 2014 ) was a Belgian art historian specialising in Early Netherlandish painting .
Alexander Ross ( 15 September 1879 -- 25 June 1952 ) , generally known as Alec Ross and sometimes as Alex or Aleck , was a Scottish professional golfer .
Lt . Col . Robert Sandilands Frowd Walker , C.M.G. , ( also known as R. S. F. Walker ) ( 13 May 1850 -- 16 May 1917 ) was a prominent figure in Malaya during the British colonial era in the late 19th century .
José de Grimaldo y Gutiérrez de Solórzano ( 1660 - -1733 ) was a Spanish statesmen .
Pierre Statorius ( Tonneville , Seine - Maritime , 1530 -- Pińczów , 1591 ) was a French grammarian and theologian , who settled among the Polish Brethren , becoming rector of a Calvinist Academy in Pińczów at the invitation of Francesco Lismanino .
Princess Auguste of Schleswig - Holstein - Sonderburg - Glücksburg ( 27 June 1633 -- 26 May 1701 ) was a Danish - German princess of the senior Glücksburg line of the Duke of Schleswig - Holstein .
Admiral of the Fleet Sir Charles Ogle , 2nd Baronet ( 24 May 1775 -- 16 June 1858 ) was a Royal Navy officer .
The publisher Thomas Jonathan Wooler ( 1786 -- 29 October 1853 ) was active in the Radical movement of early 19th century Britain , best known for his satirical journal The Black Dwarf .
Carole Lynne , Baroness Delfont ( 16 September 1918 -- 17 January 2008 ) was a British theatre actress , best known for her work in the 1940s and 1950s .
Lars Johannes Irgens ( 9 October 1775 -- 22 April 1830 ) was a Norwegian jurist and public official .
Lebian ( Lebiantu ) ( died September 1776 ) was toqui from 1769 to 1774 , who led the Pehuenche against the Spanish Empire in Chile following the Mapuche Uprising of 1766 during the Arauco War .
Dame Maria Amieriye Osunde ( 1928 - -2008 ) was a Nigerian educationist who founded Auntie Maria School .
Francis Charles McMath ( 1867-February 13 , 1938 ) was an American engineer and amateur astronomer .
Arend De Keysere ( Arnoldus cesaris , Arnoul de keysere ) ( ? - Ghent , 1490 ) was a Flemish masterprinter of incunabula .
Peter van Huizen ( 3 September 1932 -- 12 September 2011 ) was a Malaysian field hockey player of Dutch ancestry .
Antonio Aldonza Lobato , known as Aldonza ( 21 January 1926 -- 11 April 2014 ) was a Spanish professional footballer who played as a left back .
Mary Greenleaf Clement Leavitt ( 1830 - -1912 ) was a divorced Boston schoolteacher who became the first round - the - world missionary for the Woman 's Christian Temperance Union ( WCTU ) , of which she was a founding member .
Yasin Osman Kenadid ( Somali : Yaasiin Cismaan Keenadiid , Arabic : ياسين عثمان كينايديض‎ ) ( 1919 - -27 November 1988 ) was a Somali intellectual , writer and linguist .
Jørgen von Cappelen Knudtzon ( 28 April 1784 -- 29 July 1854 ) was a Norwegian businessman and patron of the arts .
Chatin Sarachi ( in Albanian Paskal `` Çatin '' Saraçi ) ( 1899 - -1974 ) , was an Albanian painter and politician .
John Wills D.D. ( died 16 June 1806 ) was an English academic administrator at the University of Oxford .
Elizabeth Tilberis ( 7 September 1947 -- 21 April 1999 ) , born Elizabeth Jane Kelly , known professionally throughout her career as Liz Tilberis , was a British fashion magazine editor of Manx and English ancestry .
Joe Frisco ( November 4 , 1889 -- February 12 , 1958 ) was an American vaudeville performer who first made his name on stage as a jazz dancer , but later incorporated his stuttering voice to his act and became a popular comedian .
The Hon . William Douglas - Home ( 3 June 1912 -- 28 September 1992 ) was a British dramatist and politician .
William Forbes Mackenzie ( 18 April 1807 -- 24 September 1862 ) was a Scottish Conservative politician and temperance reformer .
Bill Vickers ( 18 February 1904 -- 25 August 1976 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Vũ Quốc Uy ( 1920 - -1994 ) was a Vietnamese writer and cultural politician .
Ubaldo Caccianemici ( died 1171 ) was an Italian cardinal and cardinal - nephew of Pope Lucius II , his cousin who elevated him in May or June 1144 .
James Eccles FGS ( 1838 -- 6 June 1915 ) was an English mountaineer and geologist who is noted for making a number of first ascents in the Alps during the silver age of alpinism .
Edward Cobden , D.D. ( 1684 - 1764 ) was a British divine , poet , and Archdeacon of London , from 1742 - -1764 .
Heremigarius ( or Hermigarius ) ( fl . 427 - -429 ) was a Suevic military leader operative in Lusitania in the early fifth century .
Armand Gregg ( 1820 - -1897 ) was a German - born journalist with democratic beliefs .
Colonel Calvin Ira Kephart LL.D. ( 1883 - -1969 ) was an American professor of law , genealogist , historian , expert on heraldry and amateur ethnologist .
Robert Jocelyn , 2nd Earl of Roden KP , PC ( Ire ) ( 26 October 1756 -- 29 June 1820 ) was an Irish peer , soldier and politician .
Gerhart Lüders ( 25 February 1920 -- 31 January 1995 ) was a German theoretical physicist who worked mainly in quantum field theory and was well known for the discovery and a general proof of the CPT theorem .
Sir William Arrol ( 13 February 1839 -- 20 February 1913 ) was a Scottish civil engineer , bridge builder , and Liberal Unionist Party politician .
Bertie Marshall ORTT ( 6 February 1936 - 17 October 2012 ) ( born as Bertram Lloyd Marshall in Port - of - Spain , Trinidad ) was a pioneer , musician and music instrument maker of the Steel Pan .
Marie Sanlaville ( 1847 - -1930 ) was a leading dancer with the Paris Opéra .
Cecil Quinlan ( 4 May 1893 -- 23 December 1926 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Per Ericson ( 1965 - -2007 ) was a Swedish journalist and author with a background in the Moderate Party .
Zoltán Halmay ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈzoltaːn ˈhɒlmɒi ) , 18 June 1881 -- 20 May 1956 ) was a Hungarian Olympic swimmer .
E. Alison Kay ( 1928 -- 9 June 2008 ) was a malacologist , environmentalist , and professor at the University of Hawaiʻi .
Clement Cruttwell ( 1743 -- 5 August 1808 ) was an English compiler of religious works and gazetteers .
Zhang Wenjin ( ca . 1915 -- 18 February 1991 ) was a Chinese Deputy Foreign Minister and Ambassador to the United States and Canada .
Zheng Zhu ( 鄭注 ) ( died December 18 , 835 ) , probably né Yu Zhu ( 魚注 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty .
Philip Tilden ( 1887 - -1956 ) was an English architect , active in the early twentieth century , who worked for some of the most prominent members of English society , including Winston Churchill , David Lloyd George , Lord Beaverbrook , Sir Philip Sassoon , Lady Ottoline Morrell and Gordon Selfridge .
Aideen O'Kelly ( 5 September 1940 -- 22 April 2015 ) was an Irish actress of stage and television , who worked in both Ireland and the United States .
Dato ' Y. T. Lee , also Lee Yoon Thim ( 1905 - -1977 ) was a Malaysian Chinese architect active in Kuala Lumpur in the 1950s and 1960s .
Courtenay Hughes Fenn , or C. H. Fenn , ( April 11 , 1866 - -1927 ) was an American Presbyterian missionary to China , and compiler of The Five Thousand Dictionary , a widely used basic Chinese - English dictionary that has gone through numerous reprints .
Carmen Blacker FBA ( 13 July 1924 -- 13 July 2009 ) was a British scholar of Japanese language .
Eustace de Balliol ( or Eustace de Helicourt ) ( died c. 1209 ) was the cousin and successor of Bernard II de Balliol , lord of Balliol and Barnard Castle .
José Ignacio García Hamilton ( 1 November 1943 -- 17 June 2009 ) was an Argentine writer , noted historian , lawyer and politician .
Mohammad Zakaria ( 1923 -- 1993 ) was a Bangladeshi actor and producer .
James Bird ( Jimmy Jock ) ( c. 1798 -- 11 December 1892 ) was a fur trader , hunter , interpreter , and guide in both western Canada and the United States .
John St John , 11th Baron St John of Bletso ( died 24 June 1757 ) was a British peer .
Eliodoro Matte Ossa ( 11 April 1905 - 22 July 2000 ) was a Chilean businessman , founder of the Chilean forestry and paper company CMPC .
Francis Gurdon ( 11 April 1861 , Barnham Broom -- 23 December 1929 , York ) was an Anglican bishop , the third Bishop of Hull in the modern era ..
Rudolf Mansfeld ( 17 January 1901 , Berlin -- 1960 ) was a German botanist and agricultural scientist .
Charles C. Holt ( 21 May 1921 -- 13 December 2010 ) was Professor Emeritus at the Department of Management at the McCombs School of Business at the University of Texas at Austin .
Ram Waeerkar ( d. 26 February 2003 ) was an artist for the Indian comic book series Amar Chitra Katha , based on Indian mythology , history , and folklore .
Francis Delaram ( born around 1590 , fl . 1615 - -1624 or 1627 ) , was an English engraver .
Stanley Alexander de Smith FBA ( 27 March 1922 -- 12 February 1974 ) was an English academic lawyer and author .
Abraham Edel ( 6 December 1908 -- 22 June 2007 ) was a North American philosopher and ethicist .
Giuni Russo ( stage name of Giuseppa Romeo ; 10 September 1951 -- 14 September 2004 ) was an Italian singer - songwriter , who specialised in experimental music after a short successful stint as art - pop singer in the early 1980s .
Gus Troxler ( c. 1871 -- February 16 , 1945 ) was a professional strong man , boxer , actor , sports promoter , physical - training expert , and inventor .
Mischa Spoliansky ( 28 December 1898 -- 28 June 1985 ) was a Russian - born composer and a long - term resident in Britain .
Rosamund Clifford ( before 1150 -- ca . 1176 ) , often called `` The Fair Rosamund '' or the `` Rose of the World '' , was famed for her beauty and was a mistress of King Henry II of England , famous in English folklore .
René Théodore Berthon ( 1776 - -1859 ) was a French painter of religious and historical subjects , and of portraits .
Johann Nepomuk von Fuchs ( 15 May 1774 -- 5 March 1856 ) was a German chemist and mineralogist .
Emidio Greco ( 20 October 1938 -- 22 December 2012 ) was an Italian film director and screenwriter , best known for the 1974 film Morel 's Invention .
Christian of Oliva ( Polish : Christian z Oliwy ) , also Christian of Prussia ( German : Christian von Preußen ) ( died 4 December ( ? ) 1245 ) was the first missionary bishop of Prussia .
Vincent Liff ( c. 1951 - -2003 ) was an American casting director of Broadway musicals and plays .
Charles Paulet , 1st Duke of Bolton PC JP ( c. 1630 -- 27 February 1699 ) , was an English nobleman , the son of John Paulet , 5th Marquess of Winchester and his first wife , Jane Savage .
Air Commodore Charles Rumney Samson CMG , DSO & Bar , AFC ( 8 July 1883 -- 5 February 1931 ) was a British naval aviation pioneer .
Alexander Møller ( 24 April 1762 -- 28 December 1847 ) was a Norwegian physician who served at the Norwegian Constituent Assembly in 1814 .
Zhang Peiyuan ( died 1934 ) was a Han chinese general , commander of the Ili garrison .
Harold Larwood ( 14 November 1904 -- 22 July 1995 ) was a professional cricketer for Nottinghamshire and England between 1924 and 1938 .
Thomas Octavius Prichard ( 1808 - -1847 ) was an English psychiatrist , one of the earliest advocates of `` moral management '' , the humane treatment of the mentally ill . Having served as superintendent for two years at Glasgow Royal Lunatic Asylum , Prichard was appointed founding superintendent of the Northamptonshire County General Lunatic Asylum in 1838 .
Leif Utne ( 1919 -- 25 August 2004 ) was a Norwegian resistance member during World War II and later a physician .
Henry of Badewide ( or Badwide ) ( German : Heinrich von Badewide ) ( died ca . 1164 ) was a Saxon Count of Botwide ( after 1149 ) and Count of Ratzeburg ( after 1156 ) .
Luis Omar Salinas ( 1937 - -2008 ) was a leading Chicano poet who published a number of well - received collections of poetry , including the Crazy Gypsy , which has been described as `` a classic of contemporary and Chicano poetry '' ) , I Go Dreaming Serenades , and Afternoon of The Unreal .
Lionel Cranfield , 3rd Earl of Middlesex ( 1625 -- 26 October 1674 ) was an English peer , styled Hon . Lionel Cranfield from 1640 until 1651 .
Isaac Sharp ( 1681 - -1735 ) was an early New Jersey settler , politician , judge and Colonel of the militia .
Tempe Pigott ( 2 February 1884 -- 6 October 1962 ) was a silent and sound screen character actress .
Václav Tikal ( 24 December 1906 in Ptetin village , Plzeň Region -- 26 November 1965 in Prague ) was a Czech surrealist painter and ceramist .
Harry Noon ( 6 October 1937 -- 1996 ) was an English professional football player and coach .
The Rev Dr William Kelynack ( 22 May 1831 -- 1 November 1891 ) was an Cornish Australian Methodist minister , President of Newington College , and President of the General Conference of the Australasian Wesleyan Methodist Church .
Amin - Salim Jarjora ( Hebrew : : אמין - סלים ג'רג'ורה‎ 1886 -- 20 August 1975 ) was an Israeli Arab politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Democratic List of Nazareth between 1949 and 1951 .
Francesco III Ordelaffi ( c. 1357 -- September 8 , 1405 ) , also known as Cecco II , was an Italian condottiero and lord of Forlì .
James Douglas , 3rd Earl of Angus , Lord of Liddesdale and Jedburgh Forest ( 1426 - -1446 ) was a Scottish Nobleman .
Charles Anthony Swainson ( 1820 - -1887 ) was an English theologian , Norrisian and subsequently Lady Margaret 's Professor of Divinity , Master of Christ 's College , Cambridge and a canon of Chichester .
Anders Selinder , ( 4 November 1806 , Stockholm -- 6 November 1874 , Stockholm ) , was a Swedish dancer , Ballet master , choreographer and director .
Samuel More ( 1593 - -1662 ) was at the centre of two historical incidents in seventeenth century England .
Knut Luraas ( 1782 - -1843 ) was a Norwegian Hardingfele fiddler and artist .
Just Knut Qvigstad ( 20 December 1902 -- 6 May 2001 ) was a Norwegian engineer .
Osgod Clapa ( died 1054 ) , also Osgot , was a nobleman in Anglo - Saxon England during the reigns of Kings Cnut the Great , Harold Harefoot , Harthacnut , and Edward the Confessor .
Andrew Hynes ( February 28 , 1750 -- September 1800 ) was the founder of Elizabethtown , Kentucky , which town was named for his wife , Elizabeth Warford Hynes .
Robert Denoon Cumming ( 1916 -- 25 August 2004 ) was a Canadian - American philosopher and historian of twentieth - century Continental philosophy , especially phenomenology .
Reg Gutteridge , OBE ( 29 March 1924 -- 24 January 2009 ) was a boxing journalist and television commentator .
Johannes Ciconia ( c. 1370 -- between 10 June and 13 July 1412 ) was a composer and music theorist of the late Middle Ages .
Fred Leach ( 6 March 1878 -- 14 April 1908 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Andreas or Aindréas of Caithness ( † 1184 ) is the first known bishop of Caithness and a source for the author of de Situ Albanie .
Gian Nicola Babini ( 24 April 1944 -- 11 March 2012 ) was an Italian scientist who specialised in the field of ceramics .
Dr. Vasant Parikh ( 1929 - -2007 ) was an Indian politician born at Vadnagar in Mehsana district , Gujarat .
Blanche Armwood ( 1890 - -1939 ) , Educator , activist and the first African - American woman in the state of Florida to graduate from an accredited law school .
Lokenath Bal ( Bengali : লোকনাথ বল ) ( 8 March 1908 -- 4 September 1964 ) was an Indian independence activist and a member of the armed resistance movement led by Surya Sen , which carried out the Chittagong armoury raid in 1930 .
Bahjat al - Muhaisen ( 1927 - 10 April 2007 ) was a Royal Jordanian Land Force officer who served in significant infantry commands during his career .
Cec Hammer ( 24 June 1926 -- 1 April 2013 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Antonis Papadakis , or Kareklas ( 1893 - -1980 ) was a Cretan musician and famous for his superb lyra performance .
Issa Basil Bandak ( 1891 -- May 1984 ) was a Palestinian / Jordanian politician who served as Jordanian ambassador to Spain and commissioner to Chile after serving as Mayor of Bethlehem and appearing as part of the Jordanian delegation to the UN in 1950 .
Balthasar Denner ( 15 November 1685 -- 14 April 1749 ) was a German painter , highly regarded as a portraitist .
James Daly , 1st Baron Dunsandle and Clanconal ( 1 April 1782 -- 7 August 1847 ) was an Irish politician .
Leonardos Philaras ( c. 1595 -- 1673 ) ( Greek : Λεονάρδος Φιλαρᾶς , Leonardos Filaras , French : Leonard Philara also known as Villeret , Villare ) was a Greek Athenian scholar , politician , diplomat and advisor to the French court .
Rick Roderick ( 1949 - -2002 ) was an American professor of philosophy , best known for his lectures for The Teaching Company .
Nancy Perriam ( 1770 - 1867 ) was an English woman from Exmouth , Devon , who was one of the few women of her time to serve on a warship .
Cesare Rinaldi ( 1559 - -1636 ) was one of Bologna 's most eminent poets .
Robert de Beauchamp ( d. 1252 ) was an English judge , was a minor at the death of his father , Robert de Beauchamp , feudal baron of Hatch Beauchamp , Somerset , in 1211 - 12 .
Count Anders Torstenson ( 1641 - -1686 ) , Swedish statesman , son of Lennart Torstenson and member of the Privy Council , was from 1674 to 1681 Governor - General of Estonia .
Matthew Dodsworth ( c.1544 -- 1631 ) was , sometime before 1593 , appointed as Judge of the Admiralty Court in England 's Northern Counties .
Münevver Andaç ( died 1998 ) was a translator of Turkish literature .
Wilhelm Friedrich Karwinski von Karwin ( 19 February 1780 -- 2 March 1855 ) was a Bavarian naturalist who collected plants and animals in Brazil ( 1821 - -1826 ) and Mexico ( 1826 - -1831 , 1840 ) .
Hassan al - Amri ( Arabic : حسن العمري‎ ) ( 1916 - -1989 ) Known as The General of Yemen .
Roland Caldwell Harris ( May 1875 - 3 September 1945 ) was the Commissioner of Public Works for Toronto from 1912 until his death in 1945 .
Xia Chang ( Chinese : 夏昶 ; pinyin : Xià Chàng ; Wade -- Giles : Hsia Ch'ang ; 1388 - -1470 ) was a Ming dynasty Chinese painter and government official .
Lucian Popescu ( 12 January 1912 , Bucharest- 9 December 1982 ) was a Romanian boxer who won European titles in three different classes .
Wilhelm Karl Ritter von Haidinger ( or Wilhelm von Haidinger , or most often Wilhelm Haidinger ) ( 5 February 1795 -- 19 March 1871 ) was an Austrian mineralogist .
Osman Rastoder ( 1882 -- 23 January 1946 ) was a cleric ( hodja ) and commander of the Muslim militia in upper Bihor during the Second World War .
Eugen Țurcanu ( 8 July 1925 -- 17 December 1954 ) , Romanian political prisoner , was executed for his role in the Pitești Experiment .
Samuel Jasper Loring ( 1914 - 1963 ) was an aeronautical engineer with Chance Vought and later Hamilton Standard who worked on various aspects of the aeroelastic flutter problem .
Josephine Casey ( 1 January 1878 ( ? ) -- 27 January 1950 ) was a labor organizer and leader , and a women 's rights advocate .
James Mack ( Galvan Kepler Macnamara ; 1941 -- 3 June 2004 ) was a curator , director , advisor and arts advocate in New Zealand and the Pacific .
Sir Richard Thorne Thorne ( 13 October 1841 -- 18 December 1899 ) was a British physician , the fourth Chief Medical Officer in the United Kingdom .
Asta Nørregaard ( 13 August 1853 - 23 March 1933 ) was a Norwegian painter who is best known for her portraits .
Captain Kunwar Awadhesh Pratap Singh ( born October 1888 , Rampur Baghelan -- died 16 June 1967 , Kanpur ) was a noted Indian politician and Indian independence activist .
White Parker ( 1887 - -1956 ) was a son of Mah - Cheeta - Wookey and Quanah Parker , chief of the Comanches .
Arthur Brennan ( 2 March 1881 -- 12 September 1931 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Jacob Tonson , sometimes referred to as Jacob Tonson the elder ( 1655 - -1736 ) was an eighteenth - century English bookseller and publisher .
Jacob Rosted ( 23 October 1750 -- 8 October 1833 ) was a Norwegian educator , editor and librarian .
Gatjil Djerrkura OAM ( Yolŋu_Matha : Gätjil Djerrkura ) ( 30 June 1949 -- 26 May 2004 ) was an Aboriginal leader and indigenous spokesman in the Northern Territory and Australia .
Major - General Sir Henry Edward Colvile KCMG CB ( 10 July 1852 -- 25 November 1907 ) was an English soldier .
Dr. Charles V. Paterno ( 1876 -- May 30 , 1946 ) was an American real estate developer .
Jesse Milton Coburn ( 1853 - -1923 ) was a one - term Republican mayor of South Norwalk , Connecticut , from 1897 to 1898 .
Muriel Box ( 22 September 1905 -- 18 May 1991 ) was an Oscar - winning English screenwriter and director .
Angéle de la Barthe ( c. 1230 - -1275 ) was allegedly a woman from Toulouse , France , who was tried for witchcraft and condemned to death by the Inquisition in 1275 .
George Withy ( May 15 , 1924 -- November 17 , 1998 ) was a journalist , member of the Press Council ( UK ) , President of the CIOJ ( 1975 - -1976 ) and the great nephew of Edward Withy .
Edmund Lockyer , ( 21 January 1784 -- 10 June 1860 ) was a British soldier and explorer of Australia .
William Baker of Audlem ( 1705 - -1771 ) was an architect , surveyor and building contractor , working in Shropshire and the adjacent counties in the middle years of the 18th Century .
Colonel Philip Ludwell III ( 1716 - -1767 ) was the earliest known Eastern Orthodox Christian in North America .
Petrus Vuyst or Vuijst ( 1691 , Batavia , Dutch East Indies - 19 May 1732 , Batavia ) was the 20th Governor of Ceylon during the Dutch colonial period .
Charles William Previté - Orton ( 16 January 1877 -- 11 March 1947 ) was a medieval historian and the first Professor of Medieval History at the University of Cambridge on the establishment of the position in 1937 .
Hallvard Vebjørnsson ( Hallvard Den Hellige ) ( c. 1020 -- 1043 ) , commonly referred to as Saint Hallvard ( Sankt Hallvard ) , is the patron saint of Oslo .
Sergei Gavrilovich Simonov ( Russian : Сергей Гаврилович Симонов ; 9 April 1894 -- 6 May 1986 ) was a Russian weapons designer ; he is one of the fathers of the modern assault rifle .
Samuel de Lange Jr. ( 22 October 1840 -- 7 July 1911 ) was a Dutch composer , music conservatory director , organist , pianist , conductor and music teacher .
Paul Cérésole ( 16 November 1832 , Friedrichsdorf , Hesse - Homburg -- 7 January 1905 ) was a Swiss politician , judge of the Supreme Court ( 1867 - 1870 ) and member of the Swiss Federal Council ( 1870 - 1875 ) .
Edward Lascelles , 1st Earl of Harewood ( 7 January 1740 -- 3 April 1820 ) was a British peer and Member of Parliament .
Dr. Reginald Tustin Baker FRCO ( 4 July 1900 - December 1966 ) was an organist and composer based in England .
Professor Y. K. Sohoni ( 1911 - 2003 ) was a teacher and professor of French for over fifty years .
Damerla Rama Rao ( born March 8 , 1897 in Rajahmundry -- died February 6 , 1925 ) was an Indian artist .
Doctor Sheik Umar Khan ( 6 March 1975 -- 29 July 2014 ) was the chief Sierra Leonean doctor attempting to curb the country 's Ebola outbreak in 2014 .
Major General Sir Denzil Macarthur - Onslow CBE , DSO , ED ( 5 March 1904 -- 30 November 1984 ) was an Australian general .
Charles Mohun , 4th Baron Mohun ( c. 1675 -- 15 November 1712 ) was an English politician best known for his frequent participation in duels and for his reputation as a rake .
Alfred Baldwin Raper ( 8 May 1889 - 30 April 1941 ) was a British businessman , air force officer and Conservative politician .
Óscar Acosta Zeledón ( 14 April 1933 -- 15 July 2014 ) was a Honduran writer , poet , critic , politician and diplomat .
Philip Naviasky ( 1894 - 1983 ) was a Leeds - based artist .
Sir Joseph Beecham , 1st Baronet ( 8 June 1848 -- 23 October 1916 ) , was a British businessman .
Gerhard Braunitzer ( 24 September 1921 - 27 May 1989 ) was a German biochemist who was a pioneer in protein sequencing .
Col . John Cox Gawler ( 1830 - -1882 ) was a Keeper of the Crown Jewels and British Israelite author .
Sir Richard Marchant Knowles ( 20 May 1917 -- 18 February 2008 ) , known as Dick Knowles , was a British politician known for his work in local government in Birmingham .
Christopher Gallard Gilbert ( 7 September 1936 -- 29 September 1998 ) was a British furniture historian and museum curator .
Dr. Henry Ndifor Abi Enonchong ( 22 March 1934 -- 26 June 2008 ) was a Cameroon barrister .
Ernie England ( 3 February 1901 -- 22 February 1982 ) was an English footballer who played for Sunderland as a full back .
Sir John Fowler , 1st Baronet , KCMG , LLD ( 15 July 1817 -- 20 November 1898 ) was an English civil engineer specialising in the construction of railways and railway infrastructure .
Mary Meilak ( 9 August 1905 -- 1 January 1975 ) is one of the few Maltese women poets .
Ralph Payne , 1st Baron Lavington KB PC ( 19 March 1739 -- 3 August 1807 ) was a British politician and Governor of the Leeward Islands .
Isaac Blackwell ( died 1699 ) was a composer and English Cathedral organist , who served at St. Paul 's Cathedral .
Al - Mahdi Ahmad bin al - Husayn ( died 20 February 1258 ) was an imam of the Zaidi state in Yemen who ruled in the period 1248 - 1258 .
Cao Zhenyong ( Chinese : 曹振镛 ; pinyin : Cáo Zhènyōng ; 1755 - -1835 ) was a Chinese statesman of the Qing dynasty .
Shamsher Gazi or Samsher Gazi ( 1712 - 1760 ) was a governor in historical Comilla , Bangladesh .
Nawab Mehdi Nawaz Jung ( 23 May 1894 -- 28 June 1967 ) was an Indian bureaucrat and was Secretary to the Executive Council during the Nizam rule .
Francis H. Schell ( 1834 - -1909 ) was an American artist , illustrator , and lithographer , active in Philadelphia and New York .
Aiyathurai Nadesan , a prominent and veteran minority Sri Lankan Tamil journalist was shot dead on May 31 , 2004 on his way to work in eastern Sri Lankan town of Batticaloa by gunmen belonging to an armed paramilitary group widely believed to be so called Karuna Group .
Thomas Scott , 2nd Earl of Clonmell ( 15 August 1783 -- 18 January 1838 ) , styled Lord Earlsfort between 1793 and 1798 , was an Irish peer and politician .
Lady Mary Dering ( née Mary Harvey ) ( bap . 3 September 1629 -- 7 February 1704 ) was an English composer .
Harry Kiyoshi Ishisaka ( 25 December 1927 -- January 1978 ) was a leading sensei , or master of the Japanese martial art of aikido .
Alfred Paxton Backhouse ( 25 May 1851 -- 1 August 1939 ) was an Australian judge of the District Court of New South Wales , and occasional acting Supreme Court judge .
Lodovic Hugh Gavin ( 25 October 1878 -- 13 November 1940 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played 108 games with Essendon in the years following the formation of the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Horace Tennyson O'Rourke , ( 1880 - -1963 ) was Dublin city architect for Dublin Corporation , now , Dublin City Council from 1922 - 1945 .
Mark Hiddesley or Hildesley ( 1698 - -1772 ) was an Anglican churchman .
Adriaan Stoop ( 18 October 1856 , Dordrecht -- 7 September 1935 , Bloemendaal ) was a Dutch oil explorer .
Elahi Ardabili ( Persian : الهی اردبیلی‎‎ ) ( Kamāl al - Dīn Ḥusayn al - Ilāhī al - Ardabīlī , died 1543 CE ) was an Iranian author and scholar .
Aengus Finucane ( 26 April 1932 -- 6 October 2009 ) was a Roman Catholic missionary of the Spiritan Fathers order , who organized food shipments from Ireland to the Igbo people during the Nigerian Civil War .
Stanisław Bóbr - Tylingo ( 1919 - -2001 ) was a Polish - born historian who specialized in 19th - century Polish history , a Polish resistance fighter who after 1945 had to live his life in exile in Britain and Canada , and a decorated veteran of the Polish Warsaw Uprising in August--
Lester Balog ( April 18 , 1905 -- February 1976 ) was a labor activist and founding member of the Workers ' Film & Photo League .
Paul Fabre ( 1867 -- 18 December 1902 ) was a French Canadian actor , theatre critic and journalist who was active in Paris in the 1890s .
Tadhg Ó Donnchadha ( 1874 -- 1949 ) was an Irish writer , poet , editor , translator and a prominent member of the Gaelic League ( Conradh na Gaeilge ) and the Gaelic Athletic Association .
Gráinne Yeats ( 14 April 1925 - 18 April 2013 ) was an Irish harpist and singer , and also a historian of the Irish harp .
Felice Schiavoni ( 1803 -- January 30 , 1868 ) was an Italian painter , depicting history , genre , and portraits .
Dorothy Osborne , Lady Temple ( 1627 - -1695 ) was a British writer of letters and wife of Sir William Temple , 1st Baronet .
Saul Adadi ( Hebrew : שאול אדאדי‎ , 1850 -- September 18 , 1918 ) was a Sephardi Hakham , rosh yeshiva , and paytan in the 19th - century Jewish community of Tripoli , Libya .
Thomas Mansel , 1st Baron Mansel of Margam PC ( c. 1668 -- 10 December 1723 ) , sometimes referred to as Thomas Mansell , was a Welsh peer and Member of Parliament for Cardiff and Glamorgan .
Apolinary Szeluto ( 23 July 1884 -- 22 August 1966 ) was a Polish pianist and composer of the Mloda Polska style .
Ken Aitken ( 25 June 1928 -- 3 June 2008 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Ponsonby , 1st Viscount Ponsonby , GCB ( 1770 -- 22 February 1855 ) was a longtime British diplomat and politician .
Patriarch Dorotheus IV Ibn Al - Ahmar ( died 1611 ) , sometime known also as Dorotheus V , was Melkite Patriarch of Antioch from 1604 to 1611 .
Lajos Czinege ( 1924 - -1998 ) was a Hungarian military officer and politician , who served as Minister of Defence from 1960 to 1984 .
Thomas Byng ( or Bynge ) ( died 1599 ) was an English academic and lawyer , Master of Clare Hall , Cambridge from 1571 .
Benjamin Shapira ( Hebrew : בנימין שפירא‎ ; 10 June 1913 -- 1993 ) was an Israeli biochemist .
Mikkjel Hemmestveit ( 6 March 1863 -- 22 April 1957 ) , was a Norwegian - American Nordic skier who shared the Holmenkollen medal with his brother , Torjus Hemmestveit in 1928 .
George Brosius ( September 9 , 1839 -- March 17 , 1920 ) was a gymnastics teacher associated from 1854 to 1915 with the Milwaukee Turnverein .
Martha Neumark ( 1904 - -1981 ) was an important figure in the history of women 's ordination as rabbis .
Ali Iman Sharmarke ( Somali : Cali Imaan Sharmaarke , Arabic : علي ايمان شرماركي‎ ) ( b. 1956/1957-d . 11 August 2007 ) was a Somali - Canadian journalist , civil servant and philanthropist .
Thomas Dillon , 4th Viscount Dillon ( 1615 - -1672 ) was an Irish peer .
Rosa Valetti ( 17 March 1878 -- 10 December 1937 ) , born Rosa Vallentin , was a German actress , cabaret performer and singer .
Barbara Blaugdone ( c. 1609 - -1704 ) was an English Quaker preacher , who left an autobiographical account of her travels , evangelism , and religious and political views .
Marie - Jeanne Renard du Bos ( 1701 -- 1730 - 1750 ) , was a French engraver .
Charles Cutler Torrey ( 20 December 1863 -- 12 November 1956 ) was an American historian , archeologist and scholar who presented manuscripturial evidence to support alternate views on Christian and Islamic religious sources and origins .
Nirmal Chandra Jain ( 24 October 1924 -- 22 September 2003 ) was an Indian Politician . He was elected to the Lok Sabha the lower house of Indian Parliament from Seoni in Madhya Pradesh in 1977 as a candidate of the Janata Party .
John Medley , ( 19 December 1804 -- 9 September 1892 ) , was a Church of England clergyman who became the first bishop of Fredericton in 1845 .
Pandit Lachhu Maharaj ( 1907 - 1978 ) was an Indian classical dancer and choreographer of Kathak .
Will Ingwersen ( 7 May 1905 -- 14 June 1990 ) , nurseryman and alpine specialist of renown .
General Sir Edmund Haythorne KCB ( 1818 -- 18 October 1888 ) was a British Army officer who served as Adjutant - General in India .
Dr. José María Marxuach Echavarría ( baptized as José Monserrate Marxuach Echavarría ) ( April 16 , 1848 -- 1910 ) , was a medical doctor and politician who served twice as Mayor of the City of San Juan , Puerto Rico .
Evripidis Bakirtzis ( Greek : Ευριπίδης Μπακιρτζής ; 16 January 1895 -- 9 March 1947 ) , born in Kozani ( or according to other sources in Serres ) , Ottoman Empire , was a Hellenic Army officer and politician .
Paolo Animuccia ( died 1563 ) was a Renaissance Italian composer .
Misael Acosta Solís ( Ambato , December 16 , 1910 -- Quito , April , 1994 ) was an Ecuadorian naturalist .
Carlo Tessarini ( 1690 -- after 15 December 1766 ) , was an Italian composer and violinist in the late Baroque era .
Antônio Augusto Borges de Medeiros ( 19 November 1863 -- 25 April 1961 ) was a Brazilian lawyer and politician , and the President of Rio Grande do Sul for a total of 35 years ( 1898 - -1908 and 1913 - -1928 ) , during the period of Brazilian history known as the República Velha .
On 22 October 1999 , Dr Hudson Silva died in Colombo , Sri Lanka .
Harry Powditch ( 21 May 1894 -- 21 January 1963 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thomas Lee Ballenger ( December 22 , 1882 -- November 8 , 1987 ) was a historian , author and teacher .
Anthony Keck ( 1726 - -1797 ) was an 18th - century English architect with an extensive practice in Gloucestershire , Worcestershire , Herefordshire and South Wales .
Philip Braham ( 18 June 1881 -- 2 May 1934 ) was an English composer of the early twentieth century , chiefly associated with theatrical work .
Sir John Charles Clegg ( 15 June 1850 -- 26 June 1937 ) , better known as Charles Clegg , was an English footballer and later both chairman and president of the Football Association .
Henry Bromfield ( c. 1610 -- 19 February 1683 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 .
Frank Macky ( 19 December 1891 -- 29 December 1975 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with University .
Adolphe Gutmann ( originally Wilhelm Adolf Gutmann ) ( 12 January 1819 -- 22 October 1882 ) was a German pianist and composer who was a pupil and friend of Frédéric Chopin .

Albert Wassell ( 14 June 1892 -- 27 April 1975 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket in seven matches for Warwickshire in 1923 .
Dilys Laye ( 11 March 1934 -- 13 February 2009 ) was an English actress and screenwriter , best known for comedy roles .
Frank Broadstreet Carvell , PC ( 14 August 1862 -- 9 August 1924 ) was a Canadian lawyer , businessman , and politician .
Alan Blackshaw OBE ( 7 April 1933 -- 4 August 2011 ) was an English mountaineer , skier and civil servant who was President of the Alpine Club from 2001 to 2004 and President of the Ski Club of Great Britain from 1997 to 2003 .
Alexandre Joseph Sosnowsky , ( 1937 -- 3 December 2013 ) , better known by the name Sacha Sosno , was an internationally renowned French sculptor and painter .
Col Davey ( 29 June 1927 -- 20 July 2013 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Robert D'Silva ( 7 June 1925 -- 15 October 2015 ) was a Pakistani Roman Catholic prist .
Catherine Littlefield ( 1908 -- 1951 ) was an American ballerina , choreographer , and artistic director .
Miguel Ahumada Sauceda ( 1844 - 1917 ) served as the Governor of Chihuahua and Jalisco .
Leonte Răutu ( until 1945 Lev Nikolayevich ( Nicolaievici ) Oigenstein ; February 28 , 1910 -- 1993 ) was a Bessarabian - born Romanian communist activist and propagandist .
Sir John Rous , 1st Baronet ( c 1608 - 27 November 1670 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1670 .
Consort Song ( 宋貴人 , personal name unknown ) ( died 82 ) , posthumous title Empress Jingyin ( 敬隱后 , literally `` the respectful and hidden empress '' ) , was an imperial consort for Emperor Zhang of Han who was the victim of palace intrigue at the hands of Emperor Zhang 's wife Empress Dou .
Margaret Llewelyn Davies ( 1861 - -1944 ) was the general secretary of the Co - operative Women 's Guild from 1899 until 1921 .
Salvatore Fontana ( Venice , c. 1550s - 1590 ) was an Italian painter of the Renaissance period , a minor pupil of Cesare Nebbia active mainly in Rome .
Hedwig of Kalisz ( Polish : Jadwiga Bolesławówna ; 1266 -- 10 December 1339 ) was the second of three daughters born to Boleslaw the Pious and Saint Yolanda of Hungary .
Jacques - Alexandre Laffon de Ladebat ( 2 January 1719 -- 18 November 1797 ) was one of the most important shipbuilders and merchants of the port of Bordeaux in the late 18th century .
Elisabeth of Oettingen also known as Elizabeth of Leuchtenberg ( born : c. 1360 ; died : 9 July 1406 ) was a member of the House of Oettingen - Wallerstein by birth .
Enrico Rocca ( b. Turin , 21 April 1847 -- Genova , 9 June 1915 ) was an Italian violin maker of the 19th and the 20th Centuries and son of Giuseppe Rocca .
Blessed Maria Bolognesi ( 21 October 1924 -- 30 January 1980 ) was a Roman Catholic Italian layperson .
Judocus de Vos ( 1661 - -1734 ) was a Flemish weaver .
Arthur Shoosmith ( 1888 - 1974 ) was an English architect who emigrated to India and worked for a time on behalf of the well - known English architect Sir Edwin Lutyens .
Aylmer Buesst ( 28 January 1883 -- 3 January 1970 ) was an Australian conductor , teacher and scholar , who spent his career in the United Kingdom .
Louise Duprey ( 1957-February 2000 ) was a British character actress , best known for her 1993 stint as shop girl Amy Nelson in ITV1 's soap opera , Coronation Street .
Ernest Prater ( 1864 - -1950 ) was a noted English artist and book illustrator , notable also for his work as a war correspondent and reportage artist during the Anglo - Boer War .
Sybil Arundale ( 20 June 1879 -- 5 September 1965 ) was an English stage and film actress born Sybil Kelly .
Huang Wei ( Chinese : 黃維 ; 1904 - -1989 ) was a Chinese Nationalist military general who fought in the Encirclement Campaigns , Second Sino - Japanese War and Chinese Civil War .
Reginald Hankey ( 3 November 1832 - 25 August 1886 ) was an English amateur cricketer who played first - class cricket from 1853 to 1860 .
Giovanni Stefano Marucelli ( 1586 - c. 1646 ) was an Italian painter and architect of the Baroque period , active in Tuscany , including Florence and Pisa .
Charlie Backhouse ( died 5 August 1925 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played in the VFA between 1891 and 1905 for the Richmond Football Club .
Reinhold Tiling ( 13 June 1893 -- 11 October 1933 ) was a German engineer , pilot and a rocket pioneer .
Jon Eriksson Helland II ( 1849 - -1869 ) was a Norwegian Hardanger fiddle maker from Bø in Telemark .
Sir Francis Arthur Vick ( 5 June 1911 -- 2 September 1998 ) was a physicist and university administrator .
Helen Frances Gregor CM ( 28 June 1921 - 25 May 1989 ) was a Czechoslovakian - Canadian artist who specialised in textile art . She was born in Prague in Czechosolvakia , the daughter of Fred and Lily Lorenz .
Ernst Detlof von Krassow , Swedish noble and military commander , born around 1660 , dead 23 January 1714 , freiherr ( 1707 ) .
Jan Achacy Kmita ( died 1624 ) was a Polish poet and translator from Bochnia .
George Jensen ( 9 August 1878 -- 4 October 1977 ) , is an artist of Danish descent born in Port Clinton , Ohio .
Jure Grando Alilovič or Giure Grando ( 1579 - 1656 ) was a villager from the region of Istria in modern day Croatia ) who may have been the first real person described as a vampire in historical records .
Ubaldo Giraldi ( 1692 - -1775 ) , also known by the Latin name Ubaldus A Sancto Cajetano , was an Italian canonist .
Cui Huan ( 崔渙 ) ( died January 14 , 769 ) was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor briefly during the reign of Emperor Suzong -- although he was commissioned by Emperor Suzong 's father Emperor Xuanzong , not Emperor Suzong .
David Keilin FRS ( 21 March 1887 -- 27 February 1963 ) was an entomologist , among other things .
Henry St George , the younger ( 1625 - -1715 ) , was an English Officer of arms .
Marye Dahnke ( August 1897-February 1980 ) was an American home economist who worked for the Kraft Foods corporation , one of the first women to work in the food industry in that role .
Domenico Mariani ( 3 April 1863 -- 23 April 1939 ) was a Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church and was President of the Administration of the Patrimony of the Apostolic See .
Andrew Chan ( Chinese : 陳子維 ; Jyutping : Can4 Zi2 Wai4 ; 12 January 1984 -- 29 April 2015 ) was an Australian who was convicted and executed in Indonesia for drug trafficking as a member of the Bali Nine .
Maurits Binger ( 5 April 1868 -- 9 April 1923 ) was a Dutch film director , producer and screenwriter of the silent era .
Edward Magruder Tutwiler ( October 13 , 1846 -- April 19 , 1925 ) was an American industrialist and civil engineer who was a leading businessman in Birmingham , Alabama .
Li Tai ( Chinese : 李泰 ; pinyin : Lǐ Tài ; 618 -- December 15 , 652 ) , courtesy name Huibao ( 惠褒 ) , nickname Qingque ( 青雀 ) , formally Prince Gong of Pu ( 濮恭王 ) , was an imperial prince of the Chinese Tang Dynasty .
Sulṭāna Taj ul - Alam Safiatuddin Syah ( 1612 -- 23 October 1675 ; born Putri Sri Alam ) was the fourteenth ruler of Aceh .
György Berencsi 3rd ( 4 December 1941 -- 25 April 2013 ) was a Hungarian virologist .
Pierre - Louis Billaudèle ( 20 November 1796 -- 19 October 1869 ) was a priest from , and educated in , France who spent over 30 years of his service in Canada .
Karel Lamač ( 27 January 1897 -- 2 August 1952 ) was a Czech film director , actor , screenwriter and producer .
Sir Maziere Brady , 1st Baronet PC ( 20 July 1796 -- 13 April 1871 ) was an Irish judge , notable for his exceptionally long , though not very distinguished , tenure as Lord Chancellor of Ireland .
Radvila Astikas or Astikaitis ( baptized Nicholas ; Polish : Radziwiłł Ościkowicz ; died in 1477 ) was a magnate , a member of the Astikai and founder of the Radvila ( Radziwiłł ) family .
George Fletcher Moore ( 10 December 1798 -- 30 December 1886 ) was a prominent early settler in colonial Western Australia , and `` one ( of ) the key figures in early Western Australia 's ruling elite '' ( Cameron , 2000 ) .
William Wedd Tuxford ( ca.1826 -- 28 January 1878 ) was a parliamentarian and agricultural machinery dealer in the early days of the Colony of South Australia .
Aylmer Bourke Lambert ( 2 February 1761 -- 10 January 1842 ) was a British botanist , one of the first fellows of the Linnean Society .
Tore Forslund ( 26 February 1927 - -15 March 2000 ) , also known as Spökprästen ( `` the ghostpriest '' ) , was a writer , poet , Lutheran priest , street musician , and editor of the magazine A Voice Crying in the Wilderness , that he founded 1957 .
Major Sir Lord Nicholas Gosselin ( before 1866 -- 4 February 1917 ) was an Irish military officer and intelligence agent .
Alex F. T. W. Rosenberg ( 1926 - -2007 ) was a German - American mathematician who served as the editor of the Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society from 1960 to 1965 , and of the American Mathematical Monthly from 1974 to 1976 .
Robert Galbraith Heath ( 9 May 1915 -- 24 September 1999 ) was an American psychiatrist .
Norm Sexton ( 12 February 1903 -- 21 October 1952 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Footscray in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Edward Acquah ( 23 July 1935 -- 5 October 2011 ) was a Ghanaian footballer striker .
John Henry Whitley ( 8 February 1866 -- 3 February 1935 ) , often known as J. H. Whitley , was a British politician and Georgist .

George Doukas Philanthropenos ( Greek : Γεώργιος Δούκας Φιλανθρωπηνός ; died before 1452 ) was a close confidant of Byzantine Emperor John VIII Palaiologos ( r. 1425 - -1448 ) and served briefly as mesazon ( chief minister ) of the Byzantine Empire in 1438 - -1439 .
Krokodeilos Kladas ( Greek : Κροκόδειλος Κλαδάς , 1425 - -1490 ) , also known as Korkodeilos , Krokondeilos , or Korkondelos , was a Greek military leader , specifically an armatolos , in the Morea ( medieval Peloponnese ) who fought against the Ottomans on behalf of the Republic of Venice during the latter 15th century .
Else Werring , née Wilhelmsen ( 29 April 1905 -- 23 November 1989 ) was a Norwegian royal servant .

Koula Agagiotou ( Greek : Κούλα Αγαγιώτου ; 1915 -- 25 October 2006 ) was a Greek actress .
John Thompson Charlton , also known as John Charlton Thompson ( 1826 -- 26 November 1878 ) was a politician in colonial Victoria ( Australia ) , a member of the Victorian Legislative Council .
Euphemia Lamb ( c.1889 - -1957 ) , born Nina Forrest , was an artists ' model and the wife of Henry Lamb .
Richard Mansfield ( 24 May 1857 -- 30 August 1907 ) was an English actor - manager best known for his performances in Shakespeare plays , Gilbert and Sullivan operas and for his portrayal of the dual title roles in Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde .
