Deng Tingzhen ( Chinese : 鄧廷楨 ; pinyin : Dèng Tíngzhēn ; Wade -- Giles : Teng T'ing - chen ; 1776 - -1846 ) was the Governor - General of Liangguang ( Guangdong and Guangxi ) from early 1836 until early 1840 .
Seán McGuinness ( died 28 October 1978 ) , also known as John McGuinness , was an Irish republican who was elected to Dáil Éireann but did not take his seat and was later disqualified .
Stephen Rowland Pierce F.R.I.B.A , F.S.A. ( 1896 - -1966 ) was an architect and town planning consultant .
Thomas McCall ( 1834 - -1904 ) was a Scottish cartwright .
James Trubshaw ( 13 February 1777 -- 28 October 1853 ) was an English builder , architect and civil engineer .
Nevena Kokanova ( Bulgarian : Невена Коканова ) ( 12 December 1938 -- 3 June 2000 ) was a Bulgarian film actress .
Gary DeVore ( September 17 , 1941 -- June 28 , 1997 ) was a Hollywood screenwriter best known for Raw Deal and for his bizarre death in 1997 .
Lü Wencheng ( 吕文成 , pinyin : Lǚ Wénchéng , or Lui Man Sing in Cantonese ) ( 1898 - 1981 ) was a Chinese composer and musician .
John MacNeil ( 1854-August 1896 ) , was a Presbyterian author and evangelist in Australia .
Tage William - Olsson ( 8 June 1888 -- 22 August 1960 ) was a Swedish architect and chief town planning architect of Gothenburg .
Florence Reeves ( 17 February 1894 -- 30 August 2005 ) was an English suffragette , civil servant and notable supercentenarian .
George Spencer , 4th Duke of Marlborough , KG , PC , FRS ( 26 January 1739 -- 29 January 1817 ) , styled Marquess of Blandford until 1758 , was a British courtier and politician from the Spencer family .
Karl Glitscher ( 1886 -- 1945 ) was a German physicist who made contributions to quantum mechanics .
Anthony Greville - Bell DSO ( 7 March 1920 -- 4 March 2008 ) was an Australian - born officer who served in the Special Air Service during World War II and later a notable scriptwriter and sculptor .
Eddie Pollack or Pollock ( May 9 , 1899 -- June 1955 ) was an American jazz saxophonist .
Krzysztof Perwanger ( 1700 - -1785 ) was a Polish sculptor and mayor .
Hans de Jong ( 26 March 1932 -- 3 March 2011 ) was a Dutch sculptor , designer and ceramist .
Les Laver ( 9 December 1900 -- 9 January 1982 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the VFL during the late 1920s and early 1930s .
Francesco Bordoni ( 1580 - -1654 ) , also known as Francisque Bourdon , was an Italian sculptor who was active mainly in France .
Henrik Hybertsson ( or Hendrik Hubertsen ) ( died 1627 ) was a Dutchborn master shipbuilder working in the Stockholm navy yard in the early 17th century .
Hjalmar Stolpe ( 23 April 1841 -- 27 January 1905 ) , was a Swedish entomologist , archaeologist , and ethnographer .
Chung Chil - sung ( 1897 - -1958 ) , also known by her pen name Geumjuk , was a Korean dancer , feminist , and independence activist .
Sheikh Salahuddin Ahmed ( 10 February 1969 -- 29 October 2013 ) was a Bangladeshi international cricketer .
Countess Magdalena Elisabeth of Hanau - Münzenberg ( 28 March 1611 -- 26 February 1687 ) was a German noblewoman .
Balthazar Korab ( Hungarian : Koráb Boldizsár ; 1926 - -2013 ) was a photographer based in Detroit , Michigan specializing in architectural , art and landscape photography .
Leif Schiller ( 4 April , 1939 - 21 October , 2007 ) was a Danish - born fashion and commercial photographer .
Edgar Allison Peers ( 7 May 1891 -- 21 December 1952 ) , also known by his pseudonym Bruce Truscot , was an English Hispanist and educationist .
Sir Rabindrah Ghurburrun ( 1928 - -2008 ) was the Vice President of Mauritius from 1992 to 1997 .
Robert Beatson , LL.D. FRSE FSA ( 1742 - 1818 ) was a Scottish compiler and miscellaneous writer .
Eugen Miskolczy ( Croatian : Miškolci : 16 January 1907 -- 18 January 1947 ) was Croatian physician , Partisan and Major in the Yugoslav People 's Army .
Alexander Speirs ( died 5 October 1844 ) was a Scottish politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1835 to 1841 .
Mercedes Gleitze or Mercedes Carey ( 18 November 1900 -- 9 February 1981 ) was a British professional swimmer .
Punya Thitimajshima ( 9 November 1955 -- 9 May 2006 ) , a Thai professor in the department of telecommunications engineering at King Mongkut 's Institute of Technology at Ladkrabang , is the co - inventor with Claude Berrou and Alain Glavieux of a groundbreaking coding scheme called turbo codes .
James Scurry ( 1766 - -1822 ) was a British soldier and memoirist .
Theobald the Elder ( 854 - 942 ) was a Norman Count of Chartres in medieval France .
Luis Landa Escober ( December 28 , 1875 - 1977 ) was a Honduran academic , scientist and lawyer .
Frank McClean FRS ( 1837 - -1904 ) was a British astronomer and pioneer of objective prism spectrography .
Ugolino Brunforte ( c. 1262 -- c. 1348 ) was an Italian Friar Minor and chronicler .
Kostas Rigopoulos ( 1930 -- 14 January 2001 ) ( Greek : Κώστας Ρηγόπουλος ) was a Greek actor .
John Saunders Taylor ( February 23 , 1875 -- 1958 ) was a college football player and coach as well as an attorney .
Johann Heinrich Schmelzer ( c. 1620 - -1623 -- between 29 February and 20 March 1680 ) was an Austrian composer and violinist of the Baroque era .
Trevor Kent ( 24 April 1940 -- 4 November 1989 ) was an Australian theatre and television actor who achieved a level of public recognition in the 1980s .
Richard Himber ( 20 February 1899 - 11 December 1966 ) was an American bandleader , composer , violinist , magician and practical joker .
Henry Eustace Guinness ( 22 September 1897 -- 19 February 1972 ) was an Irish banker and politician .
Édouard Montpetit ( 1881 - -1954 ) was a Quebec lawyer , economist and academic .
Pietro Gaspari ( 1720 - -1785 ) was an Italian artist , known for veduta and capriccio in etchings and paintings .
Larry Rice ( 24 March 1946 -- 20 May 2009 ) was an American racing driver in the USAC and CART Championship Car series .
Arthur Hayley ( birth registered April→June 1854 -- death registered January→March 1947 ( aged 92 ) ) birth registered in Wakefield district , was an English rugby union footballer of the 1880s , playing at representative level for Yorkshire , and at club level for Wakefield Trinity , death registered in Wakefield district .
William Edward Gumbleton ( 2 March 1840 -- 4 April 1911 ) was an eminent Irish horticulturist with at least one species ( Arctotis gumbletonii ) and two cultivars named after him .
Harry Austin ( 17 April 1892 -- 29 August 1968 ) was an English cricketer who played six first - class matches between the wars : four for Warwickshire in 1919 , and two for Worcestershire in 1928 .
Grete von Zieritz ( 10 March 1899 -- 26 November 2001 ) was an Austrian - German composer and pianist .
Pope Marinus II ( or Martin III ; died May 946 ) , was Pope from 30 October 942 to his death in 946 .
Thomas Jeffery Parker F.R.S. ( 17 October 1850 -- 7 November 1897 ) was a zoologist who worked in New Zealand .
William Hacket , also known as Hackett ( died 1591 ) , was an English puritan and religious fanatic , who claimed to be a messiah and called for the removal of Queen Elizabeth I. He was executed in London after being found guilty of treason .
Yun Gwan ( 12 July 1040 - 15 June 1111 ) was a general of Goryeo who was known for training a seventeen - thousand man army and leading it to victory against the Jurchens tribes .
Jan Konopacki ( born ? - died April 23 , 1530 in Lubawa ) - Bishop of Culm ( Chełmno ) ( 1508 - 1530 ) , Treasury of the King of Poland , Provost of Malbork .
John Stilley Carpenter ( 11 February 1849 at Centreville , Delaware -- 3 January 1925 at Kanab , Utah ) was a pioneer settler of Utah and fifth bishop of the LDS Church in Glendale , Utah ( Kanab Stake ) in Kane County , Utah .
Senjee Pulney Andy ( 1831 -- September 1909 ) , also known by name S. Parani Andi or S. Parani Andy , was a doctor by profession and , in 1860 , became the first Indian to receive a British medical degree .
Aripert II ( also spelled Aribert ) was the king of the Lombards from 701 to 712 .
Werner Naumann ( 16 June 1909 -- 25 October 1982 ) was State Secretary in Joseph Goebbels ' Ministry of Public Enlightenment and Propaganda during the Third Reich .
Norah Hoult ( 10 September 1898 -- 6 April 1984 ) was an Irish writer of novels and short stories .
Thomas Some D.D. ( d. 5 May 1649 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1622 to 1644
Scott Barchard Wilson ( 1865 - 1923 ) was a British ornithologist and explorer .
Juan Pablos obtained the necessary patents and permissions to continue Cromberger 's workshop as his own after the death of Cromberger in 1540 , until his own death in 1560 or 1561 , when he had printed at least 37 books .
John Venning ( 1776 - -1858 ) was an English merchant , and a philanthropist interested in prison reform in Russia , where he was in business .
Yehoshua Rabinovitz ( Hebrew : יהושע רבינוביץ‎ , born 12 November 1911 , died 14 August 1979 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a government minister and mayor of Tel Aviv .
Henry Dundas Trotter ( 1802 - -1859 ) was a Scottish officer of the Royal Navy , who reached the rank of rear - admiral .
Reginald New born Lewisham , Kent ( April 1902 ) -- died Beckenham , Kent ( 28 November 1958 ) was a popular UK theatre organist whose career spanned the 1920s through to the 1950s .
Amasa Holcomb ( 1787 - 1875 ) was an American farmer , surveyor , civil engineer , businessman , and manufacturer of surveying instruments and telescopes .
Ante Bakotić ( 14 June 1921 -- 22 April 1945 ) was a Croatian Partisan known for marking the beginning of the 1945 breakthrough from the Jasenovac concentration camp by shouting `` Forward , comrades ! ' .
Fryderyk Sapieha ( before 1599 - 1650 ) was a Polish - Lithuanian noble from Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth .
Cao Chun ( died 210 ) , courtesy name Zihe , was a cavalry general serving under the warlord Cao Cao in the late Eastern Han dynasty .
John Walley ( died 1615 ) , was an English politician .
Ralph Wheelock ( 1600 - -1683 ) was an English Puritan minister , American colonial public official , and educator .
James Joseph Rowley ( October 14 , 1908 -- November 1 , 1992 ) was the head of the United States Secret Service between 1961 and 1973 , under Presidents Kennedy , Johnson , and Nixon .
Joseph Maréchal ( 1 July 1878 -- 11 December 1944 ) was a Belgian Jesuit priest , philosopher , theologian and psychologist .
Frederic Seebohm , Baron Seebohm , TD ( 18 January 1909 -- 15 December 1990 ) , was a British banker , soldier and social work innovator .
Kiyoaki Saibara ( 1884 - -1972 ) and his father Seito Saibara are credited with much of the success of the Texas Gulf Coast rice crop .
Trevor Roberts ( 25 February 1942 -- June 1972 ) was a Welsh professional footballer who played as a Goalkeeper .
Fulk Bourchier , 10th Baron FitzWarin ( 25 October 1445 -- 18 September 1479 ) was the son and heir of William Bourchier , 9th Baron FitzWarin ( 1407 - 1470 ) and the father of John Bourchier , 1st Earl of Bath .
St Clare John Byrne ( 1831 - 1915 ) was a British naval architect , who specialized in the design of luxury yachts during the late Victorian and early Edwardian period .
Ike Woods ( 20 August 1879 -- 28 September 1962 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
George Sondes , 1st Earl of Feversham KB ( Nov 1599 -- 16 April 1677 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1626 and 1676 and was then created a peer and member of the House of Lords .
William de Turbeville ( or William Turbe ; c. 1095 -- January 1174 ) was a medieval Bishop of Norwich .
John Christie Wright ( 22 August 1889 -- 2 May 1917 ) , generally referred to as J. Christie Wright , was a Scottish - born Australian sculptor .
Sir Rupert Alfred Kettle ( 9 January 1817 -- 6 October 1894 ) was an English barrister and county court judge , involved in arbitration of trade disputes .
John Durang ( 6 January 1768 -- 31 March 1822 ) was the first native - born American to become known as a dancer .
Frederick Norton Cook DSC ( 20 February 1905 -- 1 August 1985 ) , usually known as F. N. Cook was an officer of the Royal Australian Navy .
Wiktor Tomir Drymmer ( 1896 - -1975 ) was a Polish Army colonel and intelligence officer .
Richard Neele , Knt . , King 's Serjeant KS ( died 1486 ) was a British judge .
Jack Powers ( John Power ) ( 1827 -- November 1860 ) was an Irish born gambler , outlaw , highway - robber , gang leader , and murderer in southern and central California during the Gold Rush era .
Arthur Robert Hinks , CBE , FRS ( 26 May 1873 -- 14 April 1945 ) was a British astronomer and geographer .
Alexander von Volborth / Aleksandr Fedorovich von Volborth ( 1800 - 1876 ) , was a Russian palaeontologist .
Sir George Speke , 2nd Baronet ( 1 October 1653 - 14 January 1683 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1675 and 1683 .
Dr. Jay C. Smith ( c. 1929 -- May 12 , 2009 ) was a Pennsylvania high school principal who was convicted and sentenced to death in 1986 for the 1979 murder of Susan Reinert and her two children .
Josiah Fisher Bell ( 1820-October 1890 ) was the youngest son of Josiah Bell ( for whom the Bell House is named ) and his wife Mary .
Nawab Kapur Singh ( 1697 - -1753 ) is considered one of the pivotal figures in Sikh history , under whose leadership the Sikh community traversed one of the darkest periods of its history .
Frank Egginton ( 10 November 1908 -- 7 April 1990 ) was a British contemporary painter .
Richard Clark Kroeger Jr. died 9 November 2010 , Catherine Clark Kroeger on 14 February 2011 .
Randle Ayrton ( 9 August 1869 -- 28 May 1940 ) was a British actor , producer and director .
Robert Clements , 1st Earl of Leitrim ( 25 November 1732 -- 27 July 1804 ) was an Irish nobleman and politician .
Gian Paolo Iraldo ( 2 June 1943 - 17 August 2009 ) was an Italian sprinter , mainly specialized in 400 metres .
José Maria de Sousa Horta e Costa , CavA , OA , OSE ( 20 October 1858 -- 21 September 1927 ) , also known as José Maria de Sousa Horta e Costa ( de ) Almeida e Vasconcelos , was a Portuguese soldier , politician , and diplomat .
J. H. Wallis ( 1885 - 1958 ) was a writer whose best - selling book Once Off Guard ( in later publications it was called The Woman in the Window ) was made into a film , The Woman in the Window ( 1944 ) , directed by Fritz Lang .
James Edward Allen Gibbs ( 1829 - -1902 ) was a farmer , inventor , and businessman from Rockbridge County in the Shenandoah Valley in Virginia .
John O'Banion ( 16 February 1947 -- 14 February 2007 ) was an American vocalist and actor .
Henry Sidambarom ( 5 July 1863 -- 15 September 1952 ) was a Justice of the Peace and defender of the cause of Indian workers in Guadaloupe .
Ernest Milton ( 7 August 1897 -- 2 September 1984 ) was an English footballer who played as a left or right back for Sheffield United in The Football League .
Gladys Henson ( 27 September 1897 -- 21 December 1982 ) was a British actress whose career lasted from 1932 to 1976 and included roles on stage , radio , films and television series .
Kapitein Broos ( 1821 - -1880 ) was a Surinamese freedom fighter .
Luca Pitti ( 1398 - -1472 ) was a Florentine banker during the period of the republic presided over by Cosimo de ' Medici .
Matthew Hamont ( died 20 May 1579 ) was a Norfolk ploughwright , accused of heresy , who was burnt at the stake in Norwich Castle by the Church of England .
J. Bowyer Bell ( 15 November 1931 -- 23 August 2003 ) was an American historian , artist and art critic .
Juntree Siriboonrod ( Thai : จันตรี ศิริบุญรอด ; March 31 , 1917 -- March 13 , 1968 ) was a Thai novelist .
Karl Jakob Weber ( 12 August 1712 -- 1764 ) was a Swiss architect and engineer who was in charge of the first organized excavations at Herculaneum , Pompeii and Stabiae , under the patronage of Charles III of Naples .
Robert Huish ( 1777 -- April 1850 ) was a prolific , but generally poorly regarded , English author of history books , novels , and miscellaneous other works .
Theophilus Enos Pike ( 25 March 1907 -- 26 October 1967 ) , known as Tot Pike , was an English professional footballer who scored 33 goals in 123 appearances in the Football League playing for Fulham , Bournemouth & Boscombe Athletic , Birmingham , Southend United and Norwich City .
Nasib al - Bakri ( 1888 -- 1966 ) was a Syrian politician and nationalist leader in the first half of the 20th century .
John Dibblee Crace ( 1838 -- 18 November 1919 ) was a distinguished British interior designer who provided decorative schemes for the British Museum , the National Gallery , the Royal Academy , Tyntesfield and Longleat among many other notable buildings .
William Carstares ( also Carstaires ) ( 11 February 1649 -- 28 December 1715 ) , was a minister of the Church of Scotland , active in Whig politics .
Eduardo Neumann Gandía ( 1852 -- 1913 ) , was one of Puerto Rico 's most accomplished historians .
Shō Gen ( 尚元 ) ( 1528 - -1572 ) was king of the Ryūkyū Kingdom from 1556 to 1572 .
Elisha John Durbin ( February 1 , 1800 in Madison County , Kentucky -- 1887 at Shelbyville , Kentucky ) was an American Roman Catholic priest , known as the `` patriarch - priest of Kentucky '' .
Laura Martinozzi ( 27 May 1639 -- 19 July 1687 ) was a Duchess consort of Modena .
Publius Atilius Aebutianus ( died 188 ) was a prefect of the Roman imperial bodyguard , known as the Praetorian Guard , during the reign of emperor Commodus , from 185 until his death in 188 .
Sir Frank Trevor Roger Bigham , KBE , CB ( 22 May 1876 -- 23 November 1954 ) , known as Sir Trevor Bigham , was an English barrister , an Assistant Commissioner of the London Metropolitan Police from 1914 to 1931 , and Deputy Commissioner from 1931 to 1935 .
Abu Abdallah Ya'qub ibn Dawud ( died 802 ) was a close confidant of the Abbasid Caliph al - Mahdi ( r. 775 - -785 ) and vizier of the Caliphate for a period of three years ( 779/80 - -782/3 ) .
Friedrich Gulda ( 16 May 1930 -- 27 January 2000 ) was an Austrian pianist and composer who worked in both the classical and jazz fields .
Frank Showell Styles ( 14 March 1908 -- 19 February 2005 ) was a Welsh writer and mountaineer .
Giovanni Andrea Lampugnani ( died 26 December 1476 ) was a member of the Milanese nobility and an assassin of Galeazzo Maria Sforza , the Duke of Milan .
Gayle Williams ( 18 December 1973 -- 20 October 2008 ) was an aid worker for SERVE Afghanistan of joint British and South African nationality .
Col . Samuel Thaxter ( 1665 - 1740 ) , Hingham , Massachusetts , was one of the most prominent and influential citizens in Plymouth , New England .
Bede Evelyn Dominick Elwes ( 24 August 1931 -- 5 September 1975 ) was an English portrait painter , credited as Dominick Elwes or Dominic Elwes , whose much publicized elopement with an heiress in 1957 created an international scandal .
Margaret of Brieg ( 1342 - -1386 ) was a daughter of Ludwik I the Fair and his wife , Agnes of Sagan .
William Callister MHK ( 1808 - -1872 ) was a timber importer from Ramsey who became a Member of the House of Keys .
Charlotte Jay was the pseudonym adopted by Australian mystery writer and novelist , Geraldine Halls ( 17 December 1919 - 27 October 1996 ) .
Eva Knardahl Freiwald ( 10 May 1927 -- 3 September 2006 ) was a Norwegian pianist , with a noted career both as a child prodigy and adult performer .
Noel Peverill ( 25 December 1907 -- 21 October 1997 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Georg Joseph Beer ( 23 December 1763 -- 11 April 1821 ) was an Austrian ophthalmologist .
Tino Schirinzi ( 12 August 1934 - 18 August 1993 ) , was an Italian actor and stage director .
Thom Keyes ( 1949 - -1995 ) , was a writer , of science fiction and screenplays .
Sámal Pætursson Lamhauge , died 1752 in Lambi , Faroe Islands .
Charles Burger Woodcock , created Freiherr Woodcock - Savage , later Charles Woodcock - Savage ( 1 May 1850 -- 26 June 1923 ) was a New Yorker who achieved notoriety as the lover of King Karl of Württemberg , by some decades his elder .
Heinrich Gontermann ( 25 February 1896 -- 30 October 1917 ) was a German First World War fighter ace credited with 39 victories during the war .
Aubrey de Vere , 1st Earl of Oxford ( c. 1115 -- 26 December 1194 ) was a noble involved in the succession conflict between King Stephen and Empress Matilda in the mid - twelfth century .
Meg Shelton ( died 1705 ) known as the `` Fylde Hag '' was an English woman accused of witchcraft .
David Austin Sayre ( March 12 , 1793 - September , 1870 ) was a prominent silversmith , banker and educator .

Francis Gwyn PC ( 1648 -- 14 June 1734 ) , was a Welsh politician and official .
Tiberius Avidius Quietus ( died by 107 ) was a Roman politician who flourished under the emperors Domitian , Nerva and Trajan .
Mick Falvey died following a short illness in the Mater Hospital on Wednesday , 20 December 2006 .
William Otto Adolph Julius Danckwerts KC ( 1853 -- 25 April 1914 ) was a noted British lawyer .
Edgar Sanderson ( 1838 - -1907 ) was an English cleric , schoolteacher and historical writer .
Pedro Sotillo ( 1902 - -1977 ) was a Venezuelan writer , journalist , and poet .
George Molnar ( 1910 - -1998 ) was born in Nagyvarad , Romania but came to Australia in the late 1930s , where he practiced as a cartoonist .
Henry Howard , 1st Earl of Northampton ( 25 February 1540 -- 15 June 1614 ) was an important English aristocrat and courtier .
Pope Innocent IV ( Latin : Innocentius IV ; c. 1195 -- 7 December 1254 ) , born Sinibaldo Fieschi , was head of the Catholic Church from 25 June 1243 to his death in 1254 .
Itzquauhtzin ( 9 Reed ( 1475 ) -- 2 Flint ( 1520 ) ) was a king ( tlatoani ) of Nahua altepetl Tlatelolco .

Noel Dwyer ( born 30 October 1934 in Dublin ; died January 1993 ) was an Irish professional footballer .
Victor Schiøler was a Danish classical pianist ( 7 April 1899 -- 17 February 1967 ) .
Tom Bendelow ( 1868 - -1936 ) , nicknamed `` The Johnny Appleseed of American Golf '' , was a prolific Scottish American golf course architect during the first half of the twentieth century .
Leverett Candee ( 1 June 1795 -- 27 November 1863 ) was an industrialist , businessman , and pioneer rubber manufacturer .
John Inshaw ( 1807 - -1893 ) was a mechanic and inventor who lived in Aston , now a district of Birmingham , England .
Dr Antonie Viljoen ( 1858 - 26 October 1918 ) was an influential liberal Afrikaner politician and progressive farmer of the Cape Colony , South Africa .
C. M. Sundaram ( 1919 - -2008 ) was minister for local administration in the Congress - led United Democratic Front ( UDF ) government in Kerala from 1982 to 1987 .
Marjorie Ogilvie Anderson ( 9 February 1909 -- 27 May 2002 ) was a Scottish historian and paleographer .
Panna Cinka ( Hungarian : Czinka Panna , Slovak : Panna Cinková ) ( 1711 ( ? ) -- 1772 ) was a famous Hungarian - Romani violinist .
Nicolaas Everaerts , also called Nicolaus Everardi ( 1461/62 - -1532 ) was a Dutch jurist and the father of Johannes Secundus , an acclaimed poet .
Claude Loyola Allgén , officially Claude Johannes Maria Klas Thure Allgén ; born 16 April 1920 in Calcutta , died 18 September 1990 in Täby , was a Swedish composer .
Mal Drury ( 6 April 1910 -- 19 August 1993 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) and West Torrens in the South Australian National Football League ( SANFL ) .
Newcome Cappe ( 21 February 1733 -- 24 December 1800 ) , was an English unitarian divine .
James Joseph O'Kelly ( 1845 -- 22 December 1916 ) was an Irish nationalist journalist , politician and member of the House of Commons of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland and as member of the Irish Parliamentary Party represented the Roscommon constituency between 1880 and 1916 .
James Habersham ( c. 1712 -- 1775 ) was a pioneering merchant and statesman in the British North American colony of Georgia .
Eoin MacWhite ( 1923 - -1972 ) was an Irish diplomat , archaeologist , and scholar .
Manly Benson ( 27 April 1842 -- 20 July 1919 ) was a Methodist minister .
Jock Doherty ( 3 October 1894 -- 15 June 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne and North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

William Hook Morley ( 1815 - -1860 ) was an English barrister and orientalist .
Ronnie Baker , also known as Ron Baker ( 1947 - 1990 ) was a famous record producer , bassist , arranger and songwriter .
Benjamin Carier ( 1566 - -1614 ) was an English clergyman , a fellow of Chelsea College who was a well - publicised convert to Catholicism .
Momodu Bama ( died 14 August 2013 ) , also known by the alias Abu Saad , was the second in command of the militant Islamist group Boko Haram .
Gerard Flaitel ( † c. 1047 ) was a Norman knight and a ' most powerful lord in Normandy at the time of the Richards ' according to Orderic Vitalis .

Kurt Mandelbaum ( 13 November 1904 -- 28 September 1995 ) was an economist well known for his pioneering contribution in the field of the economics of development .
Moha ou Said l'Irraoui ( died March 1924 ) was a Moroccan tribal leader who opposed French rule of the protectorate of Morocco .
Ugyen Dorji ( Dzongkha : ཨོ་རྒྱན་རྡོ་རྗེ་ , Wylie : o rgyan rdo rje , 1855 - -1916 ) was a member of the elite Dorji family and an influential Bhutanese politician .
Ernest Harry Edmonds ( 28 August 1883 -- 8 April 1962 ) , always referred to as `` Harry Edmonds '' or E. H. Edmonds , was a politician in South Australia .
P. P. Ummer Koya ( 1 July 1922 -- 1 September 2000 ) was an Indian politician , Gandhian , freedom fighter and educationist .
Petrus Scriverius , the Latinized form of Peter Schrijver or Schryver ( 12 January 1576 -- 30 April 1660 ) , was a Dutch writer and scholar on the history of Holland and Belgium .
Fermín Chávez ( Nogoyá 13 July 1924 -- 28 May 2006 ) was an Argentine historian , poet and journalist , born in El Pueblito , a small town near Nogoyá , province of Entre Ríos .
Uttam Kumar ( 3 September 1926 -- 24 July 1980 ) ( born as Arun Kumar Chatterjee ) was an Indian film actor , director , producer , singer and music composer , playback singer who predominantly worked in Indian Cinema .
Francisco Ramírez de Madrid ( died 1501 ) was a Spanish artillery officer , counselor of the Catholic Monarchs and Secretary of King Ferdinand II of Aragon .
Denewulf ( died 908 ) was a medieval Bishop of Winchester from 878 or 879 until his death .
Muriel Wheldale Onslow ( 31 March 1880 -- 19 May 1932 ) was a British biochemist .
Andrew Strahan ( 1749 - -1831 ) was a MP and printer who served as the King 's Printer .
Thomas James Mulvany ( 1779 - -1845 ) was an Irish painter and keeper of the Royal Hibernian Academy .
Beata Rosenhane ( 21 January 1638 in Norrköping - 1 June 1674 ) was a Swedish Baroness and writer .
Vesna Girardi - Jurkić ( 15 January 1944 -- 25 August 2012 ) was a Croatian archeologist and museologist .
Robert Ritter von Greim ( 22 June 1892 -- 24 May 1945 ) was a German Field Marshal , pilot , army officer , and the last commander of the Luftwaffe ( German Air Force ) during the Second World War .
Akmal Shaikh ( 5 April 1956 -- 29 December 2009 ) was a Pakistani - British businessman who was convicted and executed in China for drug trafficking .
Felice Pasquale Baciocchi Levoy ( 18 May 1762 -- 28 April 1841 ) was born at Ajaccio into a noble , but poor , Corsican family .
Johannes Itten ( 11 November 1888 -- 25 March 1967 ) was a Swiss expressionist painter , designer , teacher , writer and theorist associated with the Bauhaus ( Staatliche Bauhaus ) school .
Sigurjón Brink ( 29 August 1974 -- 17 January 2011 ) , better known as Sjonni Brink or just the mononym Sjonni , was an Icelandic musician and singer .
Prudente de Morais Neto or Prudente de Moraes Neto ( 1904 - 1977 ) , writing under the pseudonym Pedro Dantas was a Brazilian lawyer and journalist .
Andrew Nicholl RHA ( 4 April 1804 -- 16 April 1886 ) was an Irish painter .
Dudley Weldon Woodard ( 1881 - -1965 ) was an African American mathematician and professor , and the second person of African descent to earn a PhD in Mathematics , the first being Elbert Frank Cox , ( PhD Cornell , 1925 ) , Woodard 's mentor .
John Monck Mason ( 1726 - -1809 ) was an Irish politician and literary scholar .
George Napper ( Napier ) ( born at Holywell manor , Oxford , 1550 ; executed at Oxford 9 November 1610 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest .
Harold Addison Woodruff ( 10 July 1877 -- 1 May 1966 ) was an Australian veterinary pathologist and bacteriologist .
Jan Mooy ( 1776 in Callantsoog -- 1847 in Den Helder ) , was a Dutch painter .
Fateh Singh Rao Gaekwad ( Born before April 1751 , died 26 December 1789 ) was the Maharaja of Baroda ( r.1778 - 1789 ) .
Anna Rosemond ( February 16 , 1886 -- 1966 ) was one of the earliest film actresses of the early silent film era .
Charles Duquette ( 25 July 1869 -- 30 December 1937 ) was a Canadian politician in the province of Quebec .
Eliyahu Moshe Panigel ( 1850 - -1919 ) was the sephardi chief rabbi of the Ottoman Empire , Palestine and Jerusalem .
Kulwant Singh Virk ( 20 May 1921 -- 24 December 1987 ) was an author who wrote mostly in Punjabi but also extensively in English .
Richard Robert Madden ( 22 August 1798 -- 5 February 1886 ) was an Irish doctor , writer , abolitionist and historian of the United Irishmen .
Joseph Derenbourg , or Joseph Naftali Derenburg ( 21 August 1811 - 29 July 1895 ) was a Franco - German orientalist .
Gabriel Biel , C.R.S.A. ( 1420 to 1425 -- 7 December 1495 ) , was a German scholastic philosopher and member of the Canons Regular of the Congregation of Windesheim , who were the clerical counterpart to the Brethren of the Common Life .
Fred McGinis ( 11 November 1874 , in Hobart -- 30 March 1953 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football Association ( VFA ) and the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
James Chilton ( c. 1556 -- 1620 ) was a Leiden Separatist passenger on the historic 1620 voyage of the ship Mayflower and was the oldest person on board .
Zsuzsi Roboz ( 15 August 1929 -- 9 July 2012 ) was a London - based Hungarian painter .
Kristian Schultze ( 21 January 1945 -- 22 November 2011 ) was one half of the German New Age band Cusco .
Mary Ellen Bamford ( 10 December 1857 -- 21 May 1946 ) was an American author from Healdsburg , California .
Abdelaziz Gorgi ( عبد العزيز القرجي ) ( born 2 June 1928 - -died 10 January 2008 ) was a Tunisian artist .
Francesco Torniello da Novara ( c. 1490 -- 1589 ) was a Milanese typographer , writer and Franciscan friar who became known for applying geometric specifications to Latin capital letters fonts .
Sir Henry Austin Lee ( 1847 - -7 November 1918 ) was a British diplomat , governor and landowner .
John Kelynge KS ( or Kelyng ) ( 1607 - -1671 ) was an English judge and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1661 to 1663 .
Israhel van Meckenem ( c.1445 -- 10 November 1503 ) , also known as Israhel van Meckenem the Younger , was a German printmaker and goldsmith , perhaps of a Dutch family origin .
G. B. Harrison ( July 14 , 1894 -- November 1 , 1991 ) was one of the leading Shakespeare experts of his time and the editor of the Shakespeare Penguin Classics .
Leopoldo Torre Nilsson ( 5 May 1924 -- 8 September 1978 ) , also known as Leo Towers and as Babsy , was an Argentine film director , producer and screenwriter .
Olga Kevelos ( 6 November 1923 - -28 October 2009 ) was an English Motorcycle trials and enduro rider who was the only woman to win two gold medals at the International Six - Day Trial .
Edward Fraunceys ( died 1628 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1597 and 1626 .
Captain Arthur Granville Soames , OBE ( 12 October 1886 - 6 July 1962 ) , was a member of HM 's Coldstream Guards .
Sir John Meres ( c.1660 -- 15 February 1736 ) knight , FRS of Kirby Bellars , Leicestershire was the director of a number of companies in the early 18th century , including the Charitable Corporation , the York Buildings Company , and Company of Mineral and Battery Works .
Paul Grümmer ( 26 February 1879 -- 30 October 1965 ) was a German - born cellist .
Georg Stollenwerk ( 19 December 1930 -- 1 May 2014 ) was a German footballer and trainer .
Arthur Ernest Tiffin OBE ( 11 February 1896 -- 27 December 1955 ) , commonly known as Jock Tiffin or A. E. Tiffin , was the third general secretary of the British Transport and General Workers ' Union ( TGWU ) .
Frank Hoddinott ( born Francis Hoddinott , 29 November 1894 -- November 1980 ) was a Welsh association footballer .
Constantia Jones ( born c.1708 -- December 22 , 1738 ) was a prostitute in London , UK during the term of Prime Minister Robert Walpole , who was sentenced to hang for stealing 36 shillings and a half - guinea ( the equivalent of about £ 300 today ) from one of her clients .
Roy Simmonds ( 29 December 1928 -- 9 August 2008 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Hawthorn in the VFL during the 1950s .
Eli Krog ( 1891 - -1970 ) was a Norwegian publicist and translator .
William Willes ( 1814 - -1890 ) was an early Latter - day Saint songwriter and , along with Hugh Findlay , was one of the first Mormon missionaries to enter India .
King Kaolie of Chu ( Chinese : 楚考烈王 ; pinyin : Chǔ Kǎoliè Wáng , died 238 BC ) was from 262 to 238 BC the king of the state of Chu during the late Warring States period of ancient China .
General William Gustavus Brown ( died 27 November 1883 ) was Commander of British Troops in China and Hong Kong .
Baron Mōri Gorō of Chōshū ( 1871 - -1925 ) was the fifth son of the former head of the Chōshū clan , Mōri Motonori ( 1839 - -1896 ) .
Allen Axel Strom ( c.1914 -- 23 March 1997 ) was an Australian teacher and conservationist .
Jim McNab ( 13 April 1940 , Denny , Stirlingshire , Scotland -- 29 June 2006 ) was a footballer with Sunderland , Preston North End and Stockport County .
James Almond ( September 1874 -- 1923 ) was an English footballer who played as a left - half .
Robert Harpur ( January 25 , 1731 Ballybay , County Monaghan , Ireland - April 15 , 1825 ) was an American teacher , politician , pioneer , and landowner who settled in the Binghamton , New York area .
Dušan Džamonja ( Macedonian : Душан Џамоња , pronounced ( duʃan d͡ʒamɔɲa ) ; 31 January 1928 -- 14 January 2009 ) was a contemporary Macedonian sculptor of Croatian ancestry .
Sir William Dolben , 3rd Baronet ( 1727 - -1814 ) was a British MP and campaigner for the abolition of slavery .
Stewart Granger ( born James Lablache Stewart ; 6 May 1913 -- 16 August 1993 ) was an English film actor , mainly associated with heroic and romantic leading roles .
John Frederic Daniell ( 12 March 1790 -- 13 March 1845 ) was an English chemist and physicist .
Seth Chhaju Ram ( 1861 - -1943 ) was from Punjab , India and made a fortune in Calcutta during the British Raj period .
Dallas Wiebe ( 1930 - -2008 ) was an American writer , poet , and a professor of English .
Stephen I of Antioch ( Latin : ' Stephanus ' ) was the Bishop of Antioch between 341 and 345 or 342 and 344 , depending on the source .
William Theed , also known as William Theed , the younger ( 1804 -- 9 September 1891 ) was an English sculptor , the son of the sculptor and painter William Theed the elder ( 1764 - -1817 ) .
Major John Penrice ( Great Yarmouth , 5 December 1818 -- 1892 ) was a British soldier , photographer , and the author of an English glossary of the Quran ( 1873 ) based on the edition of Gustav Leberecht Flügel ( 1834 ) .
Seepersad Naipaul ( 1906 - -1953 ) was a writer of Indo - Trinidadian heritage .
Bhai Daya Singh ( 1661 - -1708 ) was one of the Panj Pyare , the first five Sikhs to be initiated into the Khalsa order in the 17th century India .
Dr. Tivadar Pauler ( 9 April 1816 -- 30 April 1886 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Religion and Education between 1871 and 1872 .
Harry Boully ( 28 December 1879 -- 16 May 1970 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hoàng Diệu ( chữ Hán : 黃耀 , 1828 - 25 April 1882 ) was a Nguyễn Dynasty governor of Hanoi , on behalf of Emperor Tự Đức , resident in Huế .
Hector Hercules Bell CBE ( 1 December 1876 -- 12 November 1964 ) was an Australian contractor , municipal councillor , and tramway administrator .
Frans Van Giel ( born Franciscus Alexius van Giel ; 16 July 1892 -- 7 April 1975 ) was a Belgian painter who was born in Oostmalle and died in Wechelderzande .
Jiang Gui 姜貴 , also Chiang Kuei , ( 1908 - -1980 ) was a Chinese novelist active in Taiwan .
The Rt . Hon . Thomas Brooke , 2nd Viscount Alanbrooke ( 9 January 1920 -- 19 December 1972 ) , was a British peer .
Urmila Eulie Chowdhury ( 1923 -- 20 September 1995 ) was an Indian architect who worked during the mid - to - late 20th century .
Jürg Schubiger ( 14 October 1936 -- 15 September 2014 ) was a Swiss psychotherapist and writer of children 's books .
Ernst Wolrad , Prince of Schaumburg - Lippe ( 19 April 1887 -- 15 June 1962 ) was a head of the Princely House of Schaumburg - Lippe .
Cornelis de Heem ( 8 April 1631 ( baptized ) -- 17 May 1695 ( buried ) ) was a still - life painter associated with both Flemish Baroque and Dutch Golden Age painting .
Princess Marie of Edinburgh , more commonly known as Marie of Romania ( Marie Alexandra Victoria ; 29 October 1875 -- 18 July 1938 ) , was the last Queen consort of Romania as the wife of King Ferdinand I. Born into the British royal family , she was titled Princess Marie of Edinburgh at birth .
Croft McKenzie ( 17 February 1894 -- 15 February 1928 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Field Marshal Sir George Pollock , 1st Baronet GCB GCSI ( 4 June 1786 -- 6 October 1872 ) was a British Indian Army officer .
John Hadley ( 16 April 1682 -- 14 February 1744 ) was an English mathematician , and laid claim to the invention of the octant , two years after Thomas Godfrey claimed the same .
Ann McPherson CBE FRCGP FRCP SCH ( née Egelnick ; 22 June 1945 -- 28 May 2011 ) was a British general practitioner , author , health campaigner and communicator who co - founded The DIPEx Charity and founded Healthcare Professionals for Assisted Dying .
Totaram Sanadhya ( 1876 - -1947 ) was deceitfully recruited as an indentured labourer from India and brought to Fiji in 1893 .
Aleš Debeljak ( 25 December 1961 -- 28 January 2016 ) , was a Slovenian cultural critic , poet , and essayist .
Agmondesham Vesey ( 1708 -- 3 June 1785 ) was an Irish politician and the second husband of Elizabeth Vesey , one of the founders of the Blue Stockings Society .
Egil Reichborn - Kjennerud ( 4 February 1903 -- 10 April 1974 ) was a Norwegian judge , cyclist and sports administrator .
Sir Thomas Bromley ( 1530 -- 11 April 1587 ) was a 16th - century lawyer , judge and politician who established himself in the mid - Tudor period and rose to prominence during the reign of Elizabeth I. He was successively Solicitor General and Lord Chancellor of England .
Jack McLaren ( 13 October 1884 - -16 May 1954 ) was an Australian novelist who wrote novels based on his life experiences and who was renowned for his `` authenticity of background '' .
Eline Hansen ( 1859 - 1919 ) , was a Danish feminist and peace leader .
Giovanni Francisco Vigani ( c. 1650 - -1712 ) , known also as John Francis , was an Italian chemist who became the first professor of chemistry in the University of Cambridge .
Kenneth Crosby ( 1904 - -1998 ) was a British Wesleyan missionary , a Bible translator and language scholar , who worked in Sierra Leone .
Zhang Gensheng ( Chinese : 张根生 ) ( 1923 - -2008 ) was a People 's Republic of China politician .
Sir John Potts , 1st Baronet ( c. 1592 - -1673 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1648 and in 1660 .
Sir John Acland , 1st Baronet ( c. 1591 -- 24 August 1647 ) was the son of Sir Arthur Acland ( d.1610 ) of Acland in the parish of Landkey , Devon , by his wife Eleanor Mallet .
Yvan Goor ( 30 November 1884 -- 20 March 1958 ) , sometimes written as Ivan Goor , was a Belgian cyclist and motorcyclist .
Suremphaa ( reign 1751 - -1769 ) , or Swargadeo Rajeswar Singha ( Assamese : স্বৰ্গদেউ ৰাজেশ্বৰ সিংহ ) , the fourth son of Rudra Singha , became the king of the Ahom kingdom after the death of his brother King Pramatta Singha .
John Francis Wade ( 1711 -- 16 August 1786 ) was an English hymnist who is sometimes credited with writing and composing the hymn `` Adeste Fideles '' ( which was later translated to `` O Come All Ye Faithful '' ) , even though the actual authorship of the hymn remains uncertain .
Louise `` Lua '' Aurora Getsinger ( née Moore ) ( 1 November 1871 , Hume , NY -- 1 May 1916 , Cairo , Egypt ) known as Lua Getsinger was one of the first Western members of the Bahá'í Faith , becoming a member in 1897 .
Major Sir Murdoch McKenzie Wood OBE , DL ( 1881 -- 11 October 1949 ) was a Scottish Liberal politician .
Gerald Mortimer ( 1937 -- 30 December 2013 ) was an English author and sports journalist , whose career spanned over four decades .
Konstantin Pamfilov ( Russian : Памфилов , Константин Дмитриевич ; 25 May 1901 - 2 May 1943 ) - Soviet statesman .
Felix Woyrsch ( 8 October 1860 , Troppau ( now Opava in the Czech Republic ) -- 20 March 1944 ) was a German composer and choir director .
Eliezer Gordon ( 1841 - -1910 ) also known as Reb Laizer Telzer , served as the rabbi and rosh yeshiva of Telz , Lithuania .
Odd Myre ( 9 November 1912 -- 4 July 2005 ) was a Norwegian marketing agent .
David Murray , 5th Viscount of Stormont ( 1665 -- 19 November 1731 ) was a Scottish peer .
Sir Brajendra Nath Seal ( Bengali : ব্রজেন্দ্রনাথ শীল ) ( 1864 - -1938 ) was a renowned Bengali Indian humanist philosopher .
Christian Hermann Weisse ( also Weiße ; 10 August 1801 -- 19 September 1866 ) , was a German Protestant religious philosopher .
Odotheus ( in Zosimus Aedotheus ; Latinized form of a Gothic name , possibly Audaþius was a Greuthungi king who in 386 led an incursion into the Roman Empire . He was defeated and killed by the Roman general Promotus . His surviving people settled in Phrygia .
Harvey Kilpatrick Stuart O'Melveny , known as H.K.S. O'Melveny , ( 1823 - -1893 ) was a Circuit Court judge in Illinois and a Superior Court judge in California during the 19th century .
Hasso von Boehmer ( 9 August 1904 -- 5 March 1945 ) was a German Lieutenant Colonel on the General Staff and one of the July 20 Plotters .
Brian Aherne ( 2 May 1902 -- 10 February 1986 ) was an English actor of both stage and screen , who found success in Hollywood .
Professor Alfred Lodge MA ( 1854 -- 1 December 1937 ) , was an English mathematician , author , and the first president of The Mathematical Association .
William Grey , 1st Baron Grey of Werke ( died 1674 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1621 to 1622 .
Patrick Galloway ( c. 1551 -- c. 1626 ) was a Scottish minister , a Moderator of the General Assembly of the Church of Scotland .
John Thorpe or Thorp ( c.1565 - -1655 ? ; fl.1570 - -1618 ) was an English architect .
Jan de Meyer ( 21 February 1921 in Mechelen - 15 February 2014 ) was a Belgian jurist .
Sister Simona Noorenbergh ( 1907 - -1990 ; her surname is also spelled Noorenberghe or Noorenberg , and her original given name was Maria ) was a Belgian - born religious leader and community organizer .
George Alexander Hill ( 1892 - -1968 ) was a British intelligence officer .
Werburh or Wærburh ( also known as Werburgh and Werburga ) ( d. 3 February 699 at Trentham ) was an Anglo - Saxon princess who became an English saint and the patron saint of Chester .
Momik ( Armenian : Մոմիկ ; died 1333 ) was an ethnic Armenian architect , sculptor and a master artist of Armenian illuminated manuscripts .
Brigadier Surendra Singh Panwar ( 19 October 1919 -- 29 April 2002 ) served as an artillery officer in the Indian Army .
Pietro Paolo Cristofari ( 1685 - -1743 ) was a late - Baroque Italian mosaicist active in Rome , and the son of Fabio Cristofari .
Wilhelm Rath ( 14 May 1897 , in Berlin -- 13 January 1973 , in Wolfsburg /Kärnten Austria ) was a German writer , translator , bio - dynamic farmer and anthroposophist .
Elisa Bailly de Vilmorin ( 3 May 1826 -- 5 August 1868 ) was a French horticulturist and plant breeder .
Harold ( `` Harry '' ) Gemmell Kippax AO , better known as H. G. Kippax ( 6 October 1920 -- 12 August 1999 ) was an Australian print journalist .
Edward Frederick Leitner , also Friedrich August Ludwig Leitner ( 4 February 1812 , Stuttgart -- 15 January 1838 , age 25 ) was a German botanist , naturalist and physician .
Alexander Colyn ( also spelt Colin or Colins ; 1527/29 -- 17 August 1612 ) was a Flemish sculptor .
Sylvester Norris ( alias Smith and Newton ) ( 1570 or 1572 -- 16 March 1630 ) was an English Roman Catholic controversial writer and missionary priest .
Elias Pym Fordham ( 1788 - 1850 ) was the original surveyor of Indianapolis .
Shurguchi Nimgirov ( died 1920 ) was a Buddhist priest of Kalmyk origin who was born in the Bayuda aimak ( Batlaevskaia stanista ) in the Salsk District of the Don Cossack Host .
Alf Brodal ( 25 January 1910 -- 29 February 1988 ) was a Norwegian professor of anatomy .
Colm Murray ( 22 March 1952 -- 30 July 2013 ) was an Irish broadcaster , newsreader , and sports journalist , best remembered for his reports on horse racing .
Konstantinos Miliotis - Komninos ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Μηλιώτης-Κομνηνός , 1854 - -1941 ) was a Greek Army officer who rose to the rank of Lieutenant General .
Sochlachan mac Diarmata ( died 909 ) was 31st King of Uí Maine .
Herbord Sigismund Ludwig von Bar ( 1 November 1763 - 20 December 1844 ) was a lawyer in the Electorate of Brunswick - Lüneburg who became a politician and public official , serving at one stage as president of the provisional parliament in the Kingdom of Hanover .
Farideh Mashini or Farideh Machini ( Persian : فریده ماشینی ; died 30 May 2012 ) was an Iranian researcher , Islamic feminist , women 's rights activist , and reformist .
Frederick Methvan Whyte ( March 2 , 1865 -- 1941 ) was a mechanical engineer of Dutch background who worked for the New York Central in the United States .
Martin Allerdale Grainger ( 17 November 1874 -- 15 October 1941 ) was a Canadian journalist , forester and author .
Gheorghe Șaru ( also George Saru ; 1920 - -2003 ) was a Romanian - American painter , born in Romania at Checea , Timis County .
Peter McFarline ( died April 2002 ) was an Australian journalist best known for his work as a cricket writer .
Havryil Kolenda died on 11 February 1674 and was buried on next 18 February in the Saint Sophia Cathedral in Polotsk .
Walther Hesse ( 27 December 1846 -- 19 July 1911 ) is best known for his work in microbiology , specifically his work in developing agar as a medium for culturing microorganisms .
Edvard Natvig ( 16 August 1907 -- 6 November 1994 ) was a Norwegian decathlete .
Margaret Bingham , Countess of Lucan ( 1740 -- 27 February 1814 ) was a British painter , copyist , and poet .
Otto Spoerri ( 1933 - -2008 ) was a Swiss accountant who happened upon one of the most powerful positions in Hollywood .
John Booker ( 1603 - -1667 ) was an English astrologer , respected in that career for over 30 years .
Sir Hilarian Marcus Fernando , FRCP ( 1864 - -1936 ) was a pre - independence Ceylonese statesmen , physician and banker .
Count Arthur John Moore ( 1849 -- 5 January 1904 ) was a wealthy Irish Catholic and nationalist politician .
Gilla Dubh Ó Flaithbheartaigh , Lord of Iar Connacht and Chief of the Name , died 1442 .
Thomas Henry Flewett , MD , FRCPath , FRCP ( 29 June 1922 -- 12 December 2006 ) was a founder member ( and subsequently Fellow ) of the Royal College of Pathologists and was elected ( by distinction ) a Fellow of the Royal College of Physicians of London in 1978 .
Peter Elson ( 13 January 1947 -- March 1998 ) was an English science fiction illustrator whose work appeared on the covers of numerous science fiction paperback novels , as well as in the Terran Trade Authority series of illustrated books .
Alekos Alexandrakis ( Greek : Αλέκος Αλεξανδράκης ; born 27 November 1928 ; died 8 November 2005 ) was a famous Greek actor .
John W. McCoy ( 1910 - -1989 ) was an American artist who painted landscapes , portraits , and still lifes .
Joan Root ( 18 January 1936 -- 13 January 2006 ) was a Kenyan conservationist , ecological activist and Oscar - nominated filmmaker .
Moses Sheppard ( 1771 - 1857 ) was a Baltimore businessman , a Friend ( Quaker ) , a philanthropist , and founder of the now Sheppard and Enoch Pratt Hospital .
Violet Gordon - Woodhouse ( 23 April 1872 -- 9 January 1948 ) was an acclaimed British harpsichordist and clavichordist , highly influential in bringing both instruments back into fashion .
Thomas Trahern ( died 25 November 1542 ) was Somerset Herald , an English officer of arms .
Franz Anton Voegeli ( 1825 - -1874 ) was a Swiss Chemist who was the first to synthesize the triethyl phosphate ( TEP ) while he was working in Gustav Magnus 's laboratory in Berlin .
Janet Key ( 10 July 1945 -- 26 July 1992 ) was an English actress with a varied career in theatre , film and television from the late 1960s until her death .
Bran ua Máele Dúin ( or Bran mac Dúnchada ) ( died 712 ) was a king of the Uí Cheinnselaig of South Leinster .
Matthew Sutcliffe ( 1550 ? -- 1629 ) was an English clergyman , academic and lawyer .
Richard White , 1st Earl of Bantry ( 6 August 1767 -- 2 May 1851 ) was an Anglo - Irish soldier and peer .
Shaikh Ayaz ( Urdu : شیخ ایاز‎ ) born Mubarak Ali Shaikh ( Urdu : مبارک علی شیخ‎ March 1923 -- 28 December 1997 ) was one of the prominent Sindhi poets of Pakistan in general and Sindh in particular .
Leslie George Katz ( c. 1918 -- April 18 , 1997 ) was an author and publisher who founded Eakins Press , a specialty publisher of books of art and literature .
Adolphe Stoclet ( 1871 - 1949 ) was a Belgian engineer and financier .
Sir Gurunath Venkatesh Bewoor KCIE ( 1888 -- 1950 ) ( Marathi : गुरुनाथ वेंकटेश बेवूर /ಗುರುನಾಥ್ ವೆಂಕಟೇಶ್ ಬೇವೂರ್ ) was a senior Indian civil servant .
Sir John Hobart , 3rd Baronet ( 20 March 1628 -- 22 August 1683 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1654 and 1683 .
Iqbal Hussain Qureshi ( Urdu:اقبال حسين قریشی ; 27 September 1937 -- 8 December 2012 ; SI , FPAS ) , best known as I.H. Qureshi , was a Pakistani nuclear chemist and professor of chemistry at the Institute of and Applied Sciences in Islamabad .
Dorothy Minto ( ca . 1886 -- 6 December 1957 ) was a prominent actor on the London stage between 1905 and the mid-1930s , notably appearing in the first runs of several plays written by George Bernard Shaw .
Fred Dick ( 18 November 1898 -- 23 January 1980 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sam Marron ( 7 February 1884 -- 6 May 1954 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
In a judgement delivered on 2 September 2005 , the court also held that between his arrest on 5 March 1952 and his execution on 2 August 1952 Johann Burianek had been unlawfully deprived of his freedom .
Khan Sarwar Murshid ( Bengali : খান সারওয়ার মুরশিদ ; 1 July 1924 -- 8 December 2012 ) was a Bangladeshi educationist , diplomat and intellectual .
Giuseppe Zannoni ( Verona , 1849 - Monteforte d'Alpone , Province of Verona , 1903 ) was an Italian painter .
Aznar Galíndez I ( also Asnar ) ( died 839 ) was a Basque Count of Aragon and Conflent from 809 and Cerdanya and Urgell from 820 .
Sir Charles Galton Darwin , KBE , MC , FRS ( 18 December 1887 -- 31 December 1962 ) was an English physicist , the grandson of Charles Darwin .
Hemish Shah ( 7 April 1968 - 5 September 2001 ) was an English stockbroker before he became a professional poker player , and the winner of Late Night Poker series 4 , where he beat the season 2 champion Simon `` Aces '' Trumper in the final heads - up confrontation .
Du Pinhua ( Chinese : 杜品华 , 22 April 1886 ? -- 11 December 2006 ) was a Chinese claimant to the world 's oldest person title .
Gunnar Reiss - Andersen ( 21 August 1896 -- 29 July 1964 ) was a Norwegian lyric poet and author .
Florence Mary Spry ( 9 August 1922 in Birkenhead - November 2002 ) was an international cricketer , who played three Test matches for the England women 's cricket team against Australia in 1951 .
Frank Donoghue ( 17 August 1904 -- 31 May 1971 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Frederick Newton Gisborne ( 8 March 1824 -- 30 August 1892 ) was a Canadian inventor and electrician .
Vladimír Hrivnák ( 23 April 1945 -- 17 October 2014 ) was a Slovak football player and later a football manager .
Anton Elfinger ( 15 January 1821 -- 19 January 1864 ) was an Austrian physician and illustrator .
Nathan Wetherell D.D. ( 1726 - -1808 ) was an academic administrator at the University of Oxford .
James Terry Gardiner ( May 6 , 1842 -- September 10 , 1912 ) was an American surveyor and engineer .
Jack Wasserman ( 1927 - 1977 ) was a nightlife and celebrity columnist for the Vancouver Sun newspaper from 1949 until his death .
John Belling ( 1866 - -1933 ) , born in Aldershot , England , was a cytogeneticist who developed the iron - acetocarmine staining technique which is used in the study of chromosomes .
Elisabeth Howen ( 1834 - 1923 ) was an Estonian pedagogue .
Eugene Wambaugh ( February 29 , 1856 - -August 6 , 1940 ) was an American legal scholar .
Ahmed Rıza Bey ( Turkish : Ahmet Rıza Bey ; 1859 -- 26 February 1930 ) was a prominent Young Turk , activist , scientist , and statesman during the Second Constitutional Era of the Ottoman Empire .
Noel Rayson ( 24 May 1933 -- 11 February 2003 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong and South Melbourne during his ten - year career in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Robert Abdy , 3rd Baronet FSA ( 8 April 1688 -- 27 August 1748 ) was a British Tory politician .
Joachim Wasserschlebe ( 1 May 1709 , Salzwedel , Margraviate of Brandenburg - 13 March 1787 , Wassersleben estates ) was a German - Danish diplomat , politician , councillor , patron of the arts and art collector .
Jacobus Nicolaas Boshoff ( 31 January 1808 -- 21 April 1881 ) was a South African ( Boer ) politician and statesman , member of the Voortrekker movement , and the second state president of the Orange Free State , in office from 1855 to 1859 .
Victor Rietti ( 29 February 1888 - 3 December 1963 ) was an Italian - born actor and director who became known through his work in television , especially through the many live television productions of the Italian play To Live in Peace during the 1950s .
Monica Wilson , née Hunter ( 1908 - 26 October 1982 ) was a South African anthropologist , professor of social anthropology at the University of Cape Town .
Peire Lunel de Montech ( fl . 1326 - -1384 ) , also known as Cavalier Lunel or Peire de Lunel , was a lawyer , politician and author of Toulouse .
Petrus Bosman ( 1928 -- 19 July 2008 ) was a South African ballet dancer , teacher , choreographer , and répétiteur , active in England , France , and the United States .
Georg Elias Müller ( 20 July 1850 -- 23 December 1934 ) was a significant early German experimental psychologist who is credited with the theory of retroactive interference .
Rae Selling Berry ( 1880 - -1976 ) was an American gardener and horticulturist .
Major General Otto Christian von Rohr ( died 1839 ) was a Prussian army officer during the Napoleonic Wars .
Julius Frederik Macody Lund ( born 18 November 1863 in Stavanger , died 16 December 1943 in Farsund ) was a controversial Norwegian historian , most known and remembered for his engagement in the restoration of Nidaros Cathedral .
Marshall Russell Reed ( 15 September 1891 -- March 1973 ) was an American Bishop of The Methodist Church and the United Methodist Church , elected in 1948 .
Demetra Kenneth Brown ( 1877 -- 1946 ) was a Greek - American author , born on the island of Bouyouk Ada , Sea of Marmora .
Lino Landolfi ( 6 April 1925 - 11 February 1988 ) was an Italian comic book artist and writer .
Werner Rudolf Breslauer ( 4 July 1903 -- middle Europe , 28 February 1945 ) was a German photographer of jewish descent .
Martin Larkin ( 20 December 1903 -- 1 July 1971 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray and Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Norman Shrapnel ( 5 October 1912 -- 1 February 2004 ) was an English journalist , author , and parliamentary correspondent .
Abel Thomas ( 1848 -- 23 July 1912 ) was a Welsh Liberal politician and lawyer .
Albert VI , Duke of Mecklenburg ( German : Albrecht VI . , Herzog zu Mecklenburg ; 1438 - before 27 April 1483 ) was a Duke of Mecklenburg .
Rudolph August Witthaus ( 1846 - 1915 ) was an American toxicologist , born in New York City .
Susan Harrison ( 1948 -- 14 April 2013 ) was a Canadian writer and artist who published under the name A. S. A. Harrison .
John Edmund Bentley ( 1847 - -12 December 1913 ) was an English sportsman who played in the first international rugby football match in 1871 , representing England as a halfback .
Patrick of Salisbury , 1st Earl of Salisbury ( c. 1122 -- 1168 ) was an Anglo - Norman nobleman , and the uncle of the famous William Marshal .
Jeronimas Kačinskas ( or Kacinskas ; 17 April 1907 -- 15 September 2005 ) was a Lithuanian - born American composer .
Jockel Finck ( 26 March 1962 - 28 January 2006 ) was a photojournalist for the Associated Press .
Ernst Sabeditsch ( 6 May 1920 -- 30 June 1986 ) was an Austrian footballer and coach .
Blessed Tommaso Riccardi ( 24 June -- 25 March 1915 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic priest who was a professed member of the Benedictines of the Cassinese Congregation .
Diarmaid mac Tadgh Ua Ceallaigh , 38th King of Uí Maine and 3rd Chief of the Name , died 1065 .
Henry de Longchamp or Henry de Longo Campo ( c1150 - -1212 ) was an Anglo - Norman administrator .
Jacques van de Werve , Baron of Schilde ( 1793 - -1845 ) was a member of a noble family of Antwerp .
Sir William Harpur ( c. 1496 -- 27 February 1574 ) was a merchant from Bedford who moved to London , amassed a large fortune , and became Lord Mayor of London .
Esther Vanhomrigh ( known by the pseudonym Vanessa ; c. 1688 -- 2 June 1723 ) , an Irish woman of Dutch descent , was a longtime lover and correspondent of Jonathan Swift .
Giuseppe Gherardi ( Piacenza , 1750 - 7 November 1828 ) was an Italian painter , active in the Neoclassic style .
Pearl London ( 1916 - -2003 ) was a teacher of poetry at The New School , in New York City .
Laurent - Théodore Biett ( 25 July 1781 -- 3 March 1840 ) was a Swiss - born dermatologist from Schams in the canton of Graubünden .
Lowes Cato Dickinson ( London 27 November 1819 -- 15 December 1908 London ) was an English portrait painter and Christian socialist .
Andrey Yevgenyevich Lichko ( Russian : Андре́й Евге́ньевич Личко ; 1926 - -1994 ) was a Russian psychiatrist , an honored science worker of the Russian Federation , Doctor of Medicine , and vice principal of Saint - Petersburg Psychoneurological Institute n.a .
John Fleming , 2nd Lord Fleming ( c. 1465 -- 1 November 1524 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
George Henry Weiss ( 1898 - -1946 ) was an American poet , writer and novelist .
Ann Way ( 14 November 1915 -- 13 March 1993 ) was an English character actress in film and television .
Lucius Mussius Aemilianus ( d. 261 or 262 ) was a Roman usurper .
Khoren Sargsian ( Armenian : Խորեն Սարգսյան ; 1891 - -1970 ) was an Armenian writer , critic , doctor of philology , and professor .
Conrad William Eden TD ( 1905 -- 1995 ) was an English cathedral organist , who served in Wells Cathedral and Durham Cathedral .
Sakaibe no Marise ( 境部 摩理勢 ) ( died 628 ) was a court aristocrat of the Asuka period of Japanese history , and member of the Soga clan .
Feriha Tevfik Dağ ( née Negüz ) ( 1910 -- 22 April 1991 ) was a Turkish beauty pageant contestant and actress .
Jørgen Olsen Thon ( 8 March 1866 -- 12 January 1937 ) was a Norwegian newspaper editor and politician for the Labour and Social Democratic Labour parties .
Sarla Thakral ( 1914 -- 15 March 2008 ) was the first Indian woman to fly an aircraft .
Sterling Elliott ( 1852 - -1922 ) produced a series of successful inventions in the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Manuel de Faria e Sousa ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( mɐnuˈɛɫ dɨ fɐˈɾiɐ i ˈsozɐ ) ; Spanish : Faria y Sousa ; 18 March 1590 -- 3 June 1649 ) was a Portuguese historian and poet , frequently writing in Spanish .
Roy Radin ( 13 November 1949 -- 10 June 1983 ) was a show business promoter who packaged vaudeville shows in the 1970s and early 1980s .
David Denholm , Ph.D. ( 1924 -- 19 June 1997 ) was an Australian author and historian who published fiction under the pseudonym David Forrest , and history under his own name .
Sir William Knyvett ( c. 1440 -- 2 December 1515 ) was an English knight in the late Middle Ages .
Nicos Poulantzas ( Greek : Νίκος Πουλαντζάς ; 21 September 1936 -- 3 October 1979 ) was a Greek - French Marxist political sociologist .
Corinne Morgan ( 16 February 1876 -- 1945 ? ) was the stage name of Corinne ( or Cora ) Welsh .
Nathaniel Torporley ( 1564 - -1632 ) was an English clergyman , mathematician , and astrologer .
Josef Vinklář ( 10 November 1930 -- 18 September 2007 ) was a Czech actor , a member of the National Theatre .
Abdullah Totong Mahmud ( generally abbreviated A. T. Mahmud ; 3 February 1930 -- 6 July 2010 ) was a renowned Indonesian composer of children 's songs .
Curt Weibull ( 19 August 1886 -- 10 November 1991 ) was a Swedish historian , educator and author .
Conn Ua Mellaig ( died 1202 ) was the Bishop of Annaghdown .
Ivan Polunin ( 1920 - -2010 ) was a medical doctor , author , teacher , documentary filmmaker and photographer .
Oton Iveković ( 17 April 1869 -- 4 July 1939 ) was one of the foremost Croatian painters .
Countess Leon , or Elisa Heuser Leon ( 1799 - -1881 ) , was a founder and leader of the communal Germantown Colony established in 1835 north of Minden in the U.S. state of Louisiana .
Mary Elizabeth Barber ( 5 January 1818 -- 4 September 1899 ) was a pioneering amateur woman scientist of the nineteenth century .
Charles Wynne Nicholls ( 20 October 1831 -- 24 January 1903 ) was an Irish painter of genre and historical subjects .
Sir John Vavasour KS ( ca . 1440 -- 26 November 1506 ) was an English judge .
Barnabas Brough ( c. 1795 -- 30 October 1854 ) , was a British merchant and accountant who wrote several plays under the nom de plume , Bernard De Burgh .
Sir Edwin Durning - Lawrence , 1st Baronet ( 2 February 1837 -- 21 April 1914 ) was a British lawyer and Member of Parliament .
Bhojsing Gurdinomal Pahalajani ( d. February , 1938 ) was an Indian politician and the first speaker of the Sind legislative assembly .
Marco La Piana ( 1883 - -1958 ) was an Italian scholar of Arbëresh origin .
Delano Ames ( May 29 , 1906 -- January 1987 ) was an American writer of detective stories .
Sir Isaac Heard ( 10 December 1730 -- 29 April 1822 ) was a long - serving officer of arms at the College of Arms in London .
Charles Eaves ( 1908 - -2006 ) was a Canadian scientist who extended the storage of apples by controlling levels of oxygen and carbon dioxide .
As'ad Pasha al - Azm ( Arabic : أسعد باشا العظم‎ , died March 1758 ) was the governor of Damascus under Ottoman rule from 1742 to his deposition in 1757 .
Sir Edward Frankland , KCB , FRS ( 18 January 1825 -- 9 August 1899 ) was a British chemist .
William Bede Dalley ( 5 July 1831 -- 28 October 1888 ) was an Australian politician and barrister and the first Australian appointed to the Privy Council of the United Kingdom .
Ernie Ashton ( 7 July 1883 -- 1 August 1955 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
James Hedderwick LLD ( 1814 - -1897 ) was a Scottish poet , journalist and newspaper proprietor .
Gilbert Randoll Coate ( 8 October 1909 -- 2 December 2005 ) was a British diplomat , maze designer and `` labyrinthologist '' .
John Glashan ( born John McGlashan , 24 December 1927 -- 15 June 1999 ) was a Scottish cartoonist , illustrator and playwright .
Mary Anne Schimmelpenninck ( née Galton , 25 November 1778 -- 29 August 1856 ) was a British writer in the anti - slavery movement .
Lucy Osburn ( 1 April 1836 -- 22 December 1891 ) was an English nurse trained at the School of Nursing founded by Florence Nightingale .
George Whyte - Watson , FRCS(Ed ) ( 1908 - -1974 ) was a surgeon , and was born on the 9 August 1908 in Edinburgh .
Sir Thomas Holte , 1st Baronet ( c. 1571 -- 14 December 1654 ) was the original owner of Aston Hall ( a Jacobean country house in Birmingham ) , the man after whom the Holte End stand of Villa Park is named , and the possessor of quite a legendary temper .
Asbjørn Nilssen ( 19 January 1875 -- 19 October 1958 ) was a Norwegian Nordic combined skier and physician .
Hu Sanxing ( Chinese : 胡三省 ; pinyin : Hú Sānxǐng , 1230 -- 1302 ) , born Hu Mansun ( 胡滿孫 ) , courtesy names Shenzhi ( 身之 ) , Meijian ( 梅澗 ) , and Jingcan ( 景參 ) , was a Chinese historian and commentator who lived during the late Song dynasty and early Yuan dynasty .
Gaspare Gori - Mancini ( April 1653 - 16 July 1727 ) was an Italian prelate who was appointed as Bishop of Malta in 1722 .
Hender Robartes ( November 1635 -- 31 January 1688 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1688 .
Robert A. Fuhrman ( February 23 , 1925 -- November 21 , 2009 ) was an American engineer responsible for the development of the Polaris Missile and Poseidon missile , as well as President and Chief Operating Officer of Lockheed Corporation .
Harlan Thompson ( 24 September 1890 -- 29 October 1966 ) was an American theatre director , screenwriter , lyricist , film director , and film and television producer .
Dominick Sarsfield , 1st Viscount Sarsfield of Kilmallock ( c. 1570 -- 1636 ) was an Irish peer and judge who became Chief Justice of the Irish Common Pleas , but was removed from office for corruption and died in disgrace .
Richard Watson Dixon ( 5 May 1833 -- 23 January 1900 ) , English poet and divine , son of Dr James Dixon , a Wesleyan minister .
Giovanni Battista Agucchi ( 20 Nov 1570 , Bologna -- 1 Jan 1632 ) was an Italian churchman , Papal diplomat and writer on art theory .
Dobri Zhelyazkov Fetisov ( Bulgarian : Добри Желязков Фетисов , pronounced ( ˈdɔbri ʒɛˈlʲaskɔf fɛˈtisɔf ) ) ( 1800 - -1865 ) was the first Bulgarian factory - owner and industrialist , the founder of the first textile factory in Bulgaria and the Ottoman Empire .
Thomas Rickard ( 1865 - -1911 ) was an early resident of Berkeley , California , and served as the last President of the Town Board of Trustees from 1903 to 1909 , before the new city charter went into effect , creating the office of Mayor .
James Tuchet , 7th Baron Audley ( c. 1463 -- 28 June 1497 ) was a leading rebel in the 1st Cornish Rebellion of 1497 opposing the rule of Henry VII of England born in Heleigh Castle , Staffordshire to John Tuchet , 6th Baron Audley and Anne Echingham and sentenced to beheading in the year of the rebellion .
Thomas Berdmore was dentist to King George III . He was born around 1740 and died in 1785 .
Diana Rowntree ( 14 May 1915 -- 22 August 2008 ) was a British architect and architectural writer .
Eric Pohlmann ( German : Erich Pohlmann ; 18 July 1913 -- 25 July 1979 ) was an Austrian theatre , film and television character actor who worked mostly in Britain .
Florence MacMoyer ( fl . 1662 -- 12 February 1713 ) , a native of Ballymoyer , County Armagh , Ireland was the last hereditary keeper of the Book of Armagh , a 9th - century Irish manuscript written mainly in Latin .
Babu Karam Singh Bal ( Punjabi : ਬਾਬੂ ਕਰਮ ਸਿੰਘ ਬੱਲ ) ( c. 1927 -- 7 October 1992 ) was a Sikh Sarpanch for Sathiala .
Soe Lwin Lwin ( Burmese : စိုးလွင်လွင် ; 1962 - -1999 ) , also known as Po Po , was a well - known singer - composer in 1980s in Burma .
Anton Florian , Prince of Liechtenstein ( 28 May 1656 -- 11 October 1721 ) was the Prince of Liechtenstein between 1718 and 1721 .
William James Topley ( 13 February 1845 -- 16 November 1930 ) was a prolific Canadian photographer based in Ottawa , Ontario .
Hermann Guggiari ( 20 March 1924 -- 1 January 2012 ) was a Paraguayan engineer and sculptor .
Berchtold of Engelberg , German Berchtold von Engelberg ( died 3 November 1197 ) was a Swiss German Benedictine monk , who was Abbot of Engelberg Abbey in Switzerland .
Richard Meredith Hart ( 1811 - -1864 ) was an American cattleman and politician .
Pan Fusheng ( Chinese : 潘复生 ; December 1908 -- April 1980 ) was a Chinese Communist revolutionary and politician .
Thomas Pierpoint ( born 15 September 1789 at Lindfield , Sussex ; died 12 June 1849 at Brighton , Sussex ) was an English professional cricketer who played first - class cricket from 1827 to 1833 .
Robert Gould Shaw III ( 18 Aug 1898 -- 10 July 1970 ) was an American - born English socialite .
Elizabeth Strong Worthington ( October 5 , 1851 - October 2 , 1916 ) was a popular American writer during the latter part of the 19th century .
Sister María Ignacia , OSC , born Bertilda Samper Acosta ( 31 July 1856 -- 31 July 1910 ) was a Colombian Poor Clare nun , poet and writer .
Air Marshal Charles Roy Slemon , CB , CBE , CD ( 7 November 1904 -- 12 February 1992 ) , known as Roy Slemon , was the Royal Canadian Air Force 's Chief of the Air Staff from 1953 to 1957 .
Francis Bland Tucker ( 1895 - -1984 ) was born in Norfolk , Virginia on 6 January 1895 .
Jacopo Torni ( 1476 - -1526 ) , also known as Jacobo Fiorentin , L'Indaco , and Jacopo dell'Indaco , was an Italian ( Florentine ) painter .
Avrohom Bornsztain ( 14 October 1838 -- 7 February 1910 ) , also spelled Avraham Borenstein or Bernstein , was a leading posek in late - nineteenth - century Europe and founder and first Rebbe of the Sochatchover Hasidic dynasty .
Jacob Marrel ( 1613/1614 -- 11 November 1681 ) was a German still life painter active in Utrecht during the Dutch Golden Age .
Darvish Khan ( Persian : درویش‌خان ‎ , Gholam Hossein Darvish ; 1872 -- 22 November 1926 ) was a Persian classical musician and a tar player .
Asgaut Olsen Regelstad ( 1761 -- 8 January 1847 ) was a Norwegian farmer and bailiff who served as a representative at the Norwegian Constituent Assembly at Eidsvoll in 1814 .
Jacob Mantino ben Samuel ( died 1549 ) was a Jewish scholar and Italian physician , known also as Mantinus .
Charles G. Coulon ( b. 16 Feb. 1825 , Göttingen , Germany -- d. 2 Feb. 1881 ) was the sixth mayor of the city of Indianapolis , Indiana .
Vere Gordon Childe ( 14 April 1892 -- 19 October 1957 ) , better known as V. Gordon Childe , was an Australian archaeologist and philologist who specialized in the study of European prehistory .
Song Jing ( 宋璟 ) ( 663 -- November 21 , 737 ) , formally Duke Wenzhen of Guangping ( 廣平文貞公 ) , was an official of the Chinese Tang Dynasty and Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty , serving as the chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Ruizong and Emperor Xuanzong .
Andrey Insunovich Pak ( November 1926 -- 1994 ) was a Doctor of Geological and Mineralogical Sciences , Lenin Prize winner .
Jonkheer Joan Röell ( 21 July 1844 -- 13 July 1914 ) was a Dutch nobleman , lawyer and statesman .
George Campbell Macaulay ( 6 August 1852 -- 6 July 1915 ) , also known as G. C. Macaulay , was a noted English Classical scholar .
Dennis Chinnery ( 14 May 1927 -- 29 February 2012 ) was a British actor , noted for his performances in television .
Richard Knerr ( 30 June 1925 -- 14 January 2008 ) was an American inventor best known for marketing the Frisbee and Hula Hoop .
Shura Cherkassky ( Russian : Александр ( Шура ) Исаакович Черкасский ; 7 October 1911 -- 27 December 1995 ) was an American classical pianist known for his performances of the romantic repertoire .
Gabrielle Brune ( Born , Bournemouth , Hampshire , 12 February 1912 -- Died , Chichester , Sussex , 18 January 2005 ) was a British actress .
John II of Pernstein ( Czech : Jan II . z Pernštejna ; c. 1406 -- 28 December 1475 ) was a Moravian nobleman and supporter of the Hussites .
Thomas Sotherton ( by 1525 - 1583 ) , of Norwich , Norfolk , was an English politician .
Lajos Balogh ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈlɒjoʃ ˈbɒloɡ ) ; 10 May 1903 -- 9 October 1986 ) was a Hungarian athlete and later coach , architect , enigineer , politician and sports official .
Ronald Dare Gillespie ( 1890 - - 8 April 1981 ) was a Scottish Canadian and British Army officer .
Manasses IV , Count of Rethel ( died 1199 ) was a son of Ithier I and Beatrice of Namur .
Nicolae Filip ( March 3 , 1926 -- 15 May 2009 ) was born in the village of Sofia , Bălţi to a family of farmers .
Fred Parkinson Holliday DSO , MC , AFC ( 20 February 1888 -- 5 March 1980 ) was an Australian fighter pilot and ace of the First World War .
Ariadna Tyrkova - Williams died on 12 January 1962 in Washington DC and was buried there in Rock Creek Cemetery .
Andreas Kontogouris ( Greek : Ανδρέας Κοντογούρης , 1700s - 1824 ) was a Greek revolutionary leader during the Greek War of Independence .
Carus ( Latin : Marcus Aurelius Carus Augustus ; c. 222 -- July or August 283 ) was Roman Emperor from 282 to 283 , and was 60 at ascension . During his short reign , Carus fought the Germanic tribes and Sarmatians along the Danube frontier with success .
Edmund Piers Barclay ( 2 May 1898 -- 26 August 1961 ) was an English - Australian writer known for his work in radio drama .
Lady Florence Henrietta Darwin ( née Fisher , previously Maitland ; 31 January 1864 -- 5 March 1920 ) , was an English playwright .
Herbert Poore or Poor ( Norman : Hubert or Herbert le Poer ; died 1217 ) , also known as Herbert of Ilchester and Herbert Pauper , was a medieval English clergyman who held the post of Bishop of Salisbury during the reigns of Richard I and John .
Hedy Graf ( 12 October 1926 -- 31 January 1997 ) was a Spanish - born Swiss classically trained soprano .
Philip the Good ( French : Philippe le Bon , Dutch : Filips de Goede ; 31 July 1396 -- 15 June 1467 ) was Duke of Burgundy as Philip III from 1419 until his death .
Steele Rudd was the pseudonym of Arthur Hoey Davis ( 14 November 1868 -- 11 October 1935 ) an Australian author , best known for On Our Selection .
Thirumudi N. Sethuraman(Tamil : திருமுடி.ந.சேதுராமன் ) ( b. 24 January 1923 - d. 23 December 1979 ) was an Indian politician .
Carl'Alberto Perroux ( 1905 - -1977 ) was an Italian contract bridge official , the founder and long - time non - playing captain of the Blue Team , the most successful team in bridge history .
Dr Mu ( 1962 - 2014 ) was a hard trance DJ and record producer who lived and worked in London , England .
Ram Chandra Ram ( d. 2 March 2009 , Ranchi ) was an Indian politician , affiliated to the Communist Party of India ( CPI ) .
Ioannis Zisis ( Greek : Ιωάννης Ζήσης , 1888 - 1941 ) was a Greek Army general during World War II . He was born in village Makri , near to Makrakomi , Fthiotida .
Risto Stijović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Ристо Стијовић ; 8 October 1894 -- 20 December 1974 ) was a Yugoslav sculptor , considered to be one of the most original artists of his time .
Bruce Greensill ( c. 1942 -- 30 June 2007 ) was a rugby union player who represented both the Auckland Rugby Football Union and Sydney in rugby .
Sir Humphrey Chetham ( 10 July 1580 -- 1653 ) was an English merchant , responsible for the creation of Chetham 's Hospital and Chetham 's Library , the oldest public library in the English - speaking world .
Wilhelmina Cooper ( 1 May 1939 -- 1 March 1980 ) was a Dutch model who began with Ford Models and , at the peak of her success , founded her own agency , Wilhelmina Models , in New York City in 1967 .
Eleanor of Aquitaine ( French : Aliénor / Éléonore ; 1122 or 1124 -- 1 April 1204 ) was one of the wealthiest and most powerful women in western Europe during the High Middle Ages and a member of the Ramnulfid dynasty of rulers in southwestern France .
Louis de Chastillon ( c.1639 - -1734 ) was a French painter in enamel and miniature , and an engraver .

James Idwal Robling ( 1927 -- 9 June 2011 ) was a Welsh sports commentator , who worked for the BBC in Wales for almost 40 years .

Dr J J Lagowski was an American chemist working at The University of Texas at Austin .
Henry Keazor ( born 4 March 1965 ) is a Professor of Art History at the University of Heidelberg .

Born in Vienna of Austrian - Moravian ancestry , Hermann Mückler studied anthropology and political science at the University of Vienna .

Harry Reis ( born in 1949 ) is a professor of psychology at the University of Rochester .

Koch Institute for Integrative Cancer Research , which brings together biologists and engineers to improve detection , diagnosis , and treatment of cancer .

The Samuel Fleming House , also known as Flemington Castle , is an historic home located in Flemington , in Hunterdon County , New Jersey , United States , built in 1756 .

Haviland - Davison Grist Mill is a historic grist mill located at East Rockaway in Nassau County , New York .
The Canton of Agde is a subdivision of the French department of Hérault , and its subdivision , the Arrondissement of Béziers .

Johann Georg Ritter von Zimmermann ( 8 December 1728 , in Brugg , Aargau -- 7 October 1795 , in Hanover ) was a Swiss philosophical writer , naturalist , and physician .
Maria Carmela Lico or Licco ( 1927 - -1985 ) spent most of her research life as a physiologist studying the neural mechanisms of pain at the Department of Physiology of the Faculdade de Medicina de Ribeirão Preto ( Brazil ) .
Simon Le Duc ( Paris , 15 January 1742- 22 January 1777 ) was a French violinist , soloist at the Concert Spirituel , music publisher and composer .

Edoardo Molinar ( 31 August 1907 , Rocca Canavese , Italy -- 22 September 1994 , Rocca Canavese , Italy ) was an Italian cyclist .
Hansi Lang ( born January 13 , 1955 in Vienna -- d. August 24 , 2008 in Vienna ) was an Austrian singer and actor .
