Ely Jacques Kahn ( 1884 - -1972 ) was an American commercial architect who designed numerous skyscrapers in New York City in the twentieth century .
Wilhelm Wackernagel ( 23 April 1806 , Berlin -- 21 December 1869 , Basel ) was a German - Swiss philologist specializing in Germanic studies .
Karl Grobben ( August 27 , 1854 , Brno -- April 13 , 1945 , Salzburg ) was an Austrian biologist .
Guido Frederico João Pabst ( born 19 September 1914 in Porto Alegre , died 27 April 1980 in Rio de Janeiro ) was a Brazilian botanist .
Elisabeth of Saxony ( born : 18 October 1552 at Wolkenstein Castle in Wolkenstein -- died : 2 April 1590 in Heidelberg ) was an Saxon princess from the House of Wettin by birth and by marriage Countess Palatine of Simmern .
Jüri Randviir ( 27 May 1927 , Tallinn -- 8 August 1996 , Tallinn ) was an Estonian chess player and journalist , who four times won the Estonian Chess Championship .
Otto Immisch ( 18 June 1862 , Wartha , Lusatia - 29 October 1936 , Freiburg i m Breisgau ) was a German classical scholar .
Friedrich Adolph Haage ( 24 March 1796 in Erfurt -- 20 September 1866 in Erfurt ) was a German gardener and botanist .
Margaret Clap ( died c. 1726 ) , better known as Mother Clap , ran a coffee house from 1724 to 1726 in Holborn , Middlesex , a short distance from the City of London .
Giuseppe De Cristoforis ( or De Cristofori ) ( 11 October 1803 , Milan -- 27 December 1837 , also Milan ) was an Italian naturalist and collector .
Alfredo Ormando ( 15 December 1958 in San Cataldo -- 23 January 1998 in Rome ) was a gay writer from Palermo who died as a result of setting himself on fire outside Saint Peter 's Basilica in Rome .
Leni Schmidt ( Helene Hermine Schmidt ; 28 December 1906 in Bremen -- 11 November 1985 in Bremen ) was a German athlete who competed mainly in the 100 metres .
The James Dwight Dana House in New Haven , Connecticut was declared a National Historic Landmark in 1965 .
Mary Ann Vincent ( September 18 , 1818 Portsmouth , England -- September 4 , 1887 Boston ) was a British born American actress .
Philip Livingston ( January 15 , 1716 -- June 12 , 1778 ) was an American merchant and statesman from New York City .
Alex Vetchinsky ( 1904- 4 March 1980 , Hove , East Sussex , England ) was a British film art director and production designer , nominated for BAFTA Film Award .
Richard Kohn ( February 27 , 1888 - -1963 ) was an Austrian football player and later coach of FC Bayern Munich , FC Barcelona and Feyenoord Rotterdam .
Sigbert Josef Maria Ganser ( 24 January 1853 , Rhaunen , Rhine Province -- 4 January 1931 , Dresden , Saxony ) was a German psychiatrist born in Rhaunen .
Mirosław Justek ( 23 September 1948 in Słupsk -- 24 January 1998 in Poznań ) was a Polish football player .
Stella Obasanjo died a few weeks before her 60th birthday from complications of cosmetic surgery at a private health clinic in Puerto Banús , Marbella , Spain , on 23 October 2005 .

Anna Maria Schwegelin was born in poverty in the area near Kempten i m Allgäu and served as a maid .

Hendrick de Clerck ( c. 1560 -- 27 August 1630 ) was a Flemish painter active in Brussels during the late sixteenth and early seventeenth centuries .
Felix Krueger ( or Krüger ) ( 10 August 1874 in Posen ; - 25 February 1948 in Basel ) was a German psychologist and professor at the University of Leipzig .
Gaetano Merola ( 4 January 1881 -- 30 August 1953 ) was an Italian conductor , pianist and founder of the San Francisco Opera .
Ludwig Pfyffer ( 1524 -- 17 March 1594 ) was a Swiss military leader , spokesman for Roman Catholic interests in the cantons , chief magistrate of Lucerne , and probably the most important Swiss political figure in the latter half of the 16th century .
Aldo Cevenini ( born 8 November 1889 in Arona ; died 26 October 1973 in Deiva Marina ) was an Italian professional football player and coach .

Pietro Andrea Ziani ( 1616 in Venice -- 1684 in Naples ) was an Italian organist and composer .

Barry Lyndon is a 1975 British - American period drama film written , produced , and directed by Stanley Kubrick , based on the 1844 novel The Luck of Barry Lyndon by William Makepeace Thackeray .
City of Life and Death is a 2009 Chinese drama film written and directed by Lu Chuan , marking his third feature film .

Pleasant Moments ( Czech : Hezké chvilky bez záruky ) is a Czech drama film directed by Věra Chytilová .

Dorcadion pusillum is a species of longhorn beetle of the Lamiinae subfamily .

The Texas spiny softshell turtle ( Apalone spinifera emoryi ) is a subspecies of softshell turtle native to the southwestern United States .

Dinodontosaurus ( meaning `` terrible - toothed lizard '' ) is a genus of dicynodont therapsid .
The type species is Beishanlong grandis , described and named online in 2009 by a team of Chinese and American paleontologists , and formally published in January 2010 by the same Peter Makovicky , Li Daiqing , Gao Keqin , Matthew Lewin , Gregory Erickson and Mark Norrell .

Akaimia is an extinct genus of carpet sharks which existed in Ogrodzieniec near Zawiercie , southern Poland , during the middle or late Jurassic ( Callovian or Oxfordian age ) .
Cristipocregyes rondoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cristipocregyes .
Leptosiphon liniflorus is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name narrowflower flaxflower .

Calopteryx aequabilis , the river jewelwing , is a species of broad - winged damselfly .
Echinodorus horizontalis is a species plants in the of Alismataceae .
Daknopholis is a genus of African and Indian Ocean plants in the grass family .
Atagema alba , common name the Hunchback Doris , is a species of sea slug or dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Discodorididae .
The Strabomantidae are a family of frogs native to South America .
Antennablennius australis , the Moustached blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian Ocean .

Khetranisaurus ( meaning `` Khetran lizard '' , for the Khetran people of Pakistan ) is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod from the Late Cretaceous of Balochistan , western Pakistan ( also spelled `` Khateranisaurus '' in some early reports ) .
Its single species , Dryadula phaetusa , known as the banded orange heliconian , banded orange , or orange tiger , is native from Brazil to central Mexico , and in summer can be found rarely as far north as central Florida .

Adetomyrma goblin is a species of ant that belongs to the Adetomyrma genus .
Rhododendron fulgens ( 猩红杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to Bhutan , northeast India , Nepal , Sikkim , and southern Xizang in China , where it grows at altitudes of 3700 - -4500 meters .
Vitakrisaurus is a genus of noasaurid theropod dinosaurs represented by only one known species .
Babylonia perforata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Babyloniidae ..
Buddleja pichinchensis is endemic to the southern Cordillera Central of Colombia and the northern and central highlands of Ecuador , where it grows with Escallonia in páramo and subparamo regions at altitudes of 3,300 -- 4,200 m. The species was first named and described by Kunth in 1818 .
It is the only species classified under the genus Runcaria .
Phlomis chrysophylla ( golden - leaved Jerusalem sage ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native to south west Asia .
Sycophaga is a mainly Afrotropical gall wasp genus of the family Chalcidoidea that live on the section Sycomorus of the monoecious fig subgenus , Sycomorus , and one of several fig wasp genera to exploit its mutualism with Ceratosolen wasps .
Paphiopedilum victoria - mariae is a species of orchid endemic to western Sumatra ( Bukittinggi ) .
The family Phylliidae ( often misspelled Phyllidae ) contains the extant true leaf insects or walking leaves , which include some of the most remarkably camouflaged leaf mimics in the entire animal kingdom .
Marsupina bufo , common name the chestnut frog shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bursidae , the frog shells .
Spiloprionus sericeomaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Spiloprionus .

Parascorpaena picta , the Northern Scorpionfish , is a species of scorpionfish native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Papyridea soleniformis , or the spiny paper cockle , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Cardiidae .
Stethacanthus is an extinct genus of shark which lived from the Late Devonian to Early Carboniferous epoch , dying out around 320 million years ago .
Paroriaethus multispinis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paroriaethus .

Eurhinodelphis ( `` well - nosed dolphin '' ) is an extinct genus of Miocene cetacean .
Eumenidiopsis is an afrotropical genus of potter wasps with eight known species .
At present , this genus is monotypic , as there is only one commonly accepted species in it , Hormonotus modestus , commonly known as the Uganda house snake or yellow forest snake .

Hoyasemys ( meaning `` turtle of Las Hoyas '' ) is an extinct genus of basal eucryptodiran freshwater turtle from Lower Cretaceous ( upper Barremian stage ) deposits of Cuenca Province , Spain .
Rhabdodermatidae is a family of prehistoric , coelacanthimorph , lobe - finned fishes which lived during the Carboniferous period ( about 359 - 299 million years ago ) .
Dasyatis hastata is a species of stingray in the family Dasyatidae .
Heterotheca subaxillaris , camphorweed , is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family , common name .

Scutiger maculatus ( spotted lazy toad or Piebald alpine toad ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Crocus hyemalis is a species of flowering plant in the genus Crocus of the family Iridaceae , found from south Lebanon to Israel .

Wedelia pimana is a plant species in the genus Wedelia in the family Asteraceae .
Glaucium ( horned poppy ) is a genus of about 25 species of annual , biennial or perennial herbaceous flowering plants in the family Papaveraceae , native to Europe , north Africa , and southwest and central Asia .
Opsarius cocsa is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to India .
Anomiidae is a family of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs related to scallops and oysters , and known as anomiids .
Ablepharus is a genus of skinks that contains the common snake - eyed skinks .

Panulirus pascuensis is a species of spiny lobster found around Easter Island and the Pitcairn Islands in the Pacific Ocean .

Lygosoma bowringii , commonly known as the Christmas Island grass - skink or Bowring 's supple skink , is a species of scincid lizard endemic to Southeast Asia .

Proceratium vinaka is a species of ant from Fiji , and the third species of its genus to be identified there .
The Samarakoon 's shrub frog , ( Pseudophilautus samarakoon ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family , endemic to Sri Lanka .
The Roosevelt elk ( Cervus canadensis roosevelti ) , also known as Olympic elk , is the largest of the four surviving subspecies of elk in North America .

Tabanus autumnalis , the large marsh horsefly , is a medium sized species of biting horse - fly .
Waltheria tomentosa is a species of flowering plant in the family Malvaceae which is endemic to the Marquesas Islands .
Spiranthes romanzoffiana , commonly known as Irish Lady's - tresses or hooded lady 's tresses , is a species of orchid .
Eucratodes agassizii is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Eucratodes .
Aulopareia is a genus of gobies native to the western Pacific Ocean where members of this genus can be found in marine , fresh and brackish waters .
Neoplanorbis tantillus is a species of very small air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
The Common Duffer , Discophora sondaica is a species of nymphalid butterfly found in Southeast Asia .
Cymbopogon martinii is a species of grass in the lemon grass genus native to India and Indochina but widely cultivated in many places for its aromatic oil .
The genus Tyto includes all barn owls ( family Tytonidae ) except for the bay owls ( subfamily Phodilinae , genus Phodilus ) -- that is , the true barn owls , the grass owls and the masked owls collectively making up the subfamily Tytoninae .
Trypanorhyncha is an order of cestode , a type of flatworm .
Gibbonsia elegans , the Spotted kelpfish , is a species of clinid native to subtropical waters of the Pacific Ocean from central California , U.S. to southern Baja California , Mexico .
Terataner is an African genus of arboreal ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Cyrtocara moorii , commonly known as the Hump - head , is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi in east Africa where they prefer areas with sandy substrates .
Saccharomyces cerevisiae is a species of yeast .
Aplodactylus is a genus of perciform fishes , the marblefishes , native to southern Australia , New Zealand , Peru , and Chile .
Trichomorpha gracilis is a species of millipede in the Chelodesmidae family that can be found in San Vito , Costa Rica , where it was initially discovered on either the 17th or the 18th of April 1972 .
Mastigotragus is a genus of whip - lash squid containing a single species .
Dendrobium macrophyllum , commonly known as the Large - leaved Dendrobium or Pastor 's Orchid , is a species of orchid .
Phacelia racemosa is a species of phacelia known by the common name racemose phacelia .
Doesburgia celebiana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Doesburgia .
Dasypus , also known as the long - nosed or naked - tailed armadillo , is a genus of armadillo in the family Dasypodidae .
Abronia ameliae , commonly known as Amelia 's Sand Verbena or Heart 's Delight , is a species of flowering plant in the Four O'clock family , Nyctaginaceae , that is endemic to southern Texas in the United States .
Trifolium obtusiflorum is a species of clover known by the common name clammy clover .
Linaria bipartita is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name clovenlip toadflax .
Inermoparmena besucheti is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Inermoparmena .
Prepotherium is an extinct genus of Prepotheriina ground sloths that lived during the Miocene period .
Blanus aporus is an amphisbaenian species in the family Blanidae .
Cyathea annae is a species of tree fern native to Ambon in the Maluku Islands , where it grows in forest from sea level to about 650 m. The erect trunk is slender and may be as tall as 3 m. Fronds are bipinnate and 1 - 2 m in length .
Platymantis corrugatus ( Philippine wrinkled ground frog or rough - back forest frog ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Nebria chelmosensis is a species of black coloured ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Japan , North and South Korea , as well as in Jiangsu province of China .
Polaskia ( named after American amateur Charles Polaski ) is a genus of tree - like cacti reaching 4 - -5 m high , comprising 2 species .
The Baluchistan bear , also called the Pakistan black bear ( Ursus thibetanus gedrosianus ) is a subspecies of the Asian black bear found in the Baluchistan Mountains of southern Pakistan and Iran .
Aloe ballyi is a species of flowering plant in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae .
Chronoperates ( meaning `` time wanderer '' in Greek ) is an extinct genus of probable mammal whose remains have been found in a late Paleocene deposit in Alberta , Canada .
Salix subfragilis is a species of willow native to Japan , Korea , Russian Far East and northern China .
Antiplanes yukiae is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Pseudomelatomidae .
Amantis aliena is a species of praying mantis native to Amboina , Sumatra , Malaysia , Moluccas , and Myanmar .
Lasiophanes is a small genus of ant with six described species endemic to Patagonia ( Argentina and Chile ) .
Brookesia lambertoni , commonly known as the Fito leaf chameleon , is a species of chameleon endemic to Fito in eastern Madagascar .
Ioichthys kashkini is a species of barreleye known only from the Arabian Sea where it has been recovered from a depth of 700 metres ( 2,300 ft ) .
The Amethyst - colored Dendrobium ( Dendrobium amethystoglossum ) is a species of orchid endemic to the Island of Luzon in the Philippines but cultivated elsewhere as an ornamental .
Clinopodium ashei ( syn . Calamintha ashei ) is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common names Ashe 's savory and Ashe 's calamint .
Macromia taeniolata , the royal river cruiser is a species of dragonfly in the family Macromiidae .
Kajikia is a genus of billfishes found in all subtropical oceans .
Megantereon was a genus of prehistoric machairodontine saber - toothed cat that lived in North America , Eurasia , and Africa .
Prunus armeniaca ( `` Armenian plum '' ) , the most commonly cultivated apricot species , also called ansu apricot , Siberian apricot , Tibetan apricot , is a species of Prunus , classified with the plum in the subgenus Prunus .
Calamaria lumbricoidea , commonly known as Variable Reed Snake , is a species of dwarf snake in the Colubridae family .
Podocarpus dispermus is a species of conifer in the family Podocarpaceae known commonly as the broad - leaved brown pine .
Hymenoxys anthemoides , the South American rubberweed , is a South American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Eurymorpha cyanipes is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Eurymorpha .
Dodecatheon conjugens is a species of flowering plant in the primrose family known by the common name Bonneville shooting star .
Iva cheiranthifolia , the fly marsh elder , is a Caribbean species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Stathmonotus lugubris , the Mexican worm blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny known from southern Mexico , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Calathus rubripes is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Italy and Switzerland .
Pallavicinia is a globally distributed genus in the liverwort family Pallaviciniaceae .
Macrobrachium ohione , commonly known as the Ohio shrimp or Ohio River shrimp , is a species of freshwater shrimp found in rivers throughout the Gulf of Mexico and Atlantic Ocean drainage basins of North America .
Crataegus sanguinea ( common names Redhaw Hawthorn or Siberian hawthorn ) is a species of hawthorn that is native to southern Siberia , Mongolia , and the extreme north of China .
Altudoceras is a genus belonging to the Pseudogastrioceratinae subfamily .
Erigeron supplex is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names supple daisy or supple fleabane .
Calypte is a genus of hummingbirds .
Grypocoris sexguttatus is a species of true bugs belonging to the family Miridae or plant bugs , subfamily Mirinae .
Ceratonia siliqua , commonly known as the carob tree , St John's - bread , or locust bean ( not to be confused with the African locust bean ) is a species of flowering evergreen shrub or tree in the pea family , Fabaceae .
The Senegalese wolf ( Canis anthus anthus ) , also known as the grey jackal , slender jackal or Anthus , is the nominate subspecies of the African golden wolf native to Senegal .
Penaeidae is a family of marine crustacean in the suborder Dendrobranchiata , which are often referred to as penaeid shrimp or penaeid prawn .
Coreopsideae is a tribe of flowering plants belonging to the Asteroideae subfamily .
Kytococcus is a genus of Actinomycete bacteria , including the sequenced species Kytococcus sedentarius .
Thurnia is a group of herbaceous plants described as a genus in 1883 .
Polemon griseiceps , or the Cameroon snake - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Mellissia is a genus in the family Solanaceae with a single species , Mellissia begoniifolia ( Saint Helena Boxwood ) , that is endemic to the island of Saint Helena .
Hibiscus schizopetalus is a species of Hibiscus native to tropical eastern Africa in Kenya , Tanzania and Mozambique .
Photinia raupingensis is a species in the family Rosaceae of flowering plants .
Banksia leptophylla var . melletica is a variety of Banksia leptophylla .
The beetle family Jurodidae was originally described from fossils , but in 1996 , a single species from the Russian Far East , described as Sikhotealinia zhiltzovae , was found and later was recognized to be a living representative of this otherwise extinct family ( a `` living fossil '' ) .
Dictenidia is a genus of true crane flies .
Galium serpenticum is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name Intermountain bedstraw or many - flowered bedstraw .
Acanthochirana is an extinct genus of prawn that existed during the upper Jurassic period .
Yunnanolepis is an extinct genus of primitive Antiarch placoderm .
Mortoniella is a genus of flowering plants in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1939 .
Pantilius tunicatus is a species of bug in Miridae family that could be found in the Baltic states , Faroe Islands , Finland , Italy , United Kingdom , Yugoslavia , the Netherlands , Eastern , Central , and Western Europe ( except for Portugal ) .
Phellinus tremulae is a species of polypore fungus in the family Hymenochaetaceae that grows on Populus tremula and on trembling aspen in Canada .
Oxyuridae is a family of nematode worms of the class Secernentea .
Trachydoras paraguayensis is a species of thorny catfish found in the Paraná River basin of Argentina , Bolivia , Brazil and Paraguay .
Carex assiniboinensis , commonly known as the assiniboia sedge , is a species of sedge ( Carex ) in the section Hymenochlaenae .
Neoscorpaena nielseni is a species of scorpionfish known from the Indian Ocean off the coast of South Africa where it is found at depths of from 100 to 405 metres ( 328 to 1,329 ft ) .
Cybistax is a genus containing a single species , Cybistax antisyphilitica ( Mart . )
Euscelis is a leafhopper genus in the subfamily Deltocephalinae .
Gymnopilus braendlei is a species of agaric fungus that contains the hallucinogens psilocybin and psilocin .
Acer undulatum is a species of maple , endemic to Babadağ near Fethiye in Muğla Province , southwestern Turkey , where it grows at altitudes of between 1,400 and 1,800 meters .
Baileya australis , the Small Baileya Moth , is a species of moth of the Nolidae family .
Allium cristophii , common name Persian Onion or Star of Persia ; is a species of onion native to Turkey , Iran , and Turkmenistan , though grown as an ornamental bulbous plant in many parts of the world .
Mimetes fimbriifolius , also called cowl pagoda or the fringed pagoda , is a species of plant in the Proteaceae family .
Pardiglanis tarabinii , the Somalian giant catfish , is a species of claroteid catfish native to Kenya and Somalia .
Christella is a genus of around 50 species of ferns .
Yunmenglong is an extinct genus of somphospondylan sauropod known from the late Early Cretaceous of Henan Province , central China .
Craniata ( formerly Craniforma ) is a class of Brachiopod originating in the Cambrian period and still extant today .
Lupocyclus is a genus of crabs , containing six species :
Jentink 's duikers stand around 80 cm ( 31 in ) tall at the shoulder and weigh about 70 kg ( 150 lb ) , making them the largest species of the duikers .
Calliostoma roseolum , common name Dall 's rosy top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Acanthostracion is a genus of boxfishes native to the Atlantic Ocean .
Cheirolepidoptus is a genus of extinct mite found in Italy .
Platyzoma microphyllum , the sole species in genus Platyzoma , is a fern native to northern Australia .
Cattleya schilleriana is a species of bifoliate Cattleya orchid .
Rhododendron hyperythrum ( 微笑杜鹃 , wei xiao du juan ) is a Rhododendron species endemic to north - central Taiwan at 900 - -1200 meters altitude .
Acca sellowiana , a species of flowering plant in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae , is native to the highlands of southern Brazil , eastern Paraguay , Uruguay , northern Argentina , and Colombia .
Baeolophus is a genus of birds in the family Paridae .
Warea amplexifolia is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names wideleaf pinelandcress , wide - leaf warea , and clasping warea .
Lycurus is a small genus of New World plants in the grass family , native to North and South America .
Trisetum is a genus of plants in the grass family , widespread in temperate , subarctic , and alpine habitats in much of the world .
Pyrostria revoluta , formerly Scyphochlamys revoluta , is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae that lives on the island of Rodrigues .
Conus ruthae is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Microhyla annamensis ( commonly known as the Annam chorus frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Thwaitesia argentiopunctata known as the sequined spider , mirror spider , or twin - peaked Thwaitesia is a species of spider found in all the states of Australia .
Feylinia is a genus of skinks ( family Scincidae ) .
The family Entomobryidae contains the so - called `` slender springtails '' , a group of springtails characterised as having an enlarged fourth abdominal segment and a well - developed furcula .
Ungusurculus is a genus of viviparous brotulas found in the western Pacific Ocean .
Arachnura is a genus of orb - weaving spiders of Australasia , with one species found in Africa and Madagascar .
Alyxia oliviformis , known as Maile ( pronounced MY - lĕ ) in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering plant in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae , that is native to Hawaii .
Fibrillanosema crangonycis is a species of fungus in the phylum Microsporidia .
Amblyocarpum is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1837 .
Pseudobrevicoceras is an extinct nautilitoid cephalopod genus in the order Oncocerida .
Fissurella nodosa , commonly known as the knobbed keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Madurella is a genus of fungus of the Hyphomycetes class .
Mimecyroschema tuberculipenne is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimecyroschema .
Desseria is a genus of parasitic protozoa belonging the phylum Apicomplexa .
Zizyphomyia is a genus of flies in the family Tachinidae .
Bogertophis is a genus of New World rat snakes endemic to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Pappognatha is a genus of mutillid wasps .
Sobralia fragrans , commonly known as the fragrant sobralia , is a species of orchid found from Mexico to tropical South America .
Glomera is a genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) , with more than 130 species .
Eupolyphaga sinensis , or tǔ biē chóng , 土鳖虫 , is a species of wingless , flightless cockroach in the genus Eupolyphaga , native to Western China and Mongolia .
Pastinaca ( parsnips ) is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , comprising 14 species .
The Pu Hoat muntjac ( Muntiacus puhoatensis ) is a newly discovered species of muntjac only known from Pu Hoat region in Vietnam , which is bordering Laos .
Systenotheca is a monotypic plant genus in the buckwheat family containing the single species Systenotheca vortriedei , which is known by the common name Vortriede 's spineflower .
Oxyops vitiosa is a species of weevil in the Curculionidae family .
Nebria rougemonti is a species of ground beetle from a Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Sichuan province of China .
Calliostoma rosewateri , common name Rosewater 's top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Echinaster sepositus , the Mediterranean red sea star ( sometimes only red sea star , but this name is also used for other species such as Callopatiria granifera ) , is a species of starfish from the East Atlantic , including the Mediterranean Sea .
Centaurea seridis is a species of Centaurea found in Eastern Mediterranean .
Spectrunculus grandis is a species of ray - finned fish in the cusk - eel family known by the common names pudgy cusk - eel and giant cusk - eel .
†Oriostomatidae is an extinct taxonomic family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Neritimorpha .
Drosera macrophylla , the showy sundew , is a perennial tuberous species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to Western Australia .
Parafrasura is a monotypic genus of moth in the family Arctiidae from Africa .
Yssolebias martae is a species of fish only known from the Río Magdalena near Santa Marta , Colombia .
Rastrophyllum is a genus of African plants in the evil tribe within the daisy family .
Xerophyllum tenax is a North American species of plants in the corn lily family .
The genus Cayratia comprises approximately 45 species of plants , some of which have utility value to people .
The sole species it contains , Guamia mariannae , is endemic to the Marianas Islands .
Microryzomys minutus , also known as the montane colilargo or the forest small rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Microryzomys of family Cricetidae .
Heteroteuthis serventyi is a species of bobtail squid native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean , off southeastern Australia .
Parthenium alpinum is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names alpine feverfew and Wyoming feverfew .
Genicanthus personatus is a species of marine angelfishes in the genus , Genicanthus .
The Iringa akalat ( Sheppardia lowei ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Melicope adscendens is a rare species of flowering plant in the citrus family known by the common name auwahi melicope .
Scoparia dulcis is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family .
Fucus spiralis is a species of seaweed , a brown alga ( Heterokontophyta , Phaeophyceae ) , living on the littoral shore of the Atlantic coasts of Europe and North America .
Tropidocarpum is a genus of flowering plants in the mustard family .
Lessingia nemaclada is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name slenderstem lessingia .
Olivella minuta , common name the minute dwarf olive , is a species of small sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olivellidae , the dwarf olives .
Stylonychia is a genus of ciliate , included among the stichotrichs .
Pseudopostega sumbae is a species of moth of the Opostegidae family .
Mimoxylamia gentyi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimoxylamia .
Walckenaeria crocea is a spider species first described by A. F. Millidge in 1983 .
Eleotris vomerodentata is a species of sleeper goby endemic to Madagascar , where it is only known to occur in fresh waters .
Styrax redivivus , with common names that include snowdrop bush , California styrax , bitternut , drug snowbell , and chaparral snowbell , is a species of flowering plant in the family Styracaceae .
Cochylimorpha elegans is a moth species in the Tortricidae family .
Phracyps is a genus of moths of the Xyloryctidae family from the Madagascar .
Labiostrombus epidromis , common name the swan conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Promissum is an extinct genus of primitive chordate that lived in the Ordovician period , about 500 million years ago .
Stilida is a genus of true bugs in the family Tessaratomidae , and endemic to Australia .
Carex simulata is a species of sedge known by the common name analogue sedge .
Rubus depavitus is a North American species of dewberry , known as the Aberdeen dewberry .
Crossoloricaria rhami is a species of armored catfish found in the upper Amazon basin of Ecuador and Peru .
Brassavola venosa is a species of orchid found from Campeche , Oaxaca , Quintana Roo , El Salvador , Guatemala , Honduras and Nicaragua .
Thuspeinanta is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1888 .
Rhagio scolopaceus is a species of flies from the family Rhagionidae .
Asparagus simulans is a species of Asparagus native to Madagascar .
Pterostylis recurva is a species of orchid endemic to west - southwestern and Southwest Australia .
Berberis agricola is a plant species endemic to Xizang ( Tibet ) .
Astragalus montii is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name heliotrope milkvetch .
Gymnallabes nops , popularly known as the blind eel catfish , is a species of airbreathing catfish found in the lower Congo River basin in the countries of the Democratic Republic of the Congo and the Republic of the Congo .
Stachyopsis is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae family , first described in 1923 .
Stenogyne is a genus of flowering plants in the mint family first described in 1830 .
The Mariana crow ( Corvus kubaryi ) ( Chamorro name : aga ) is a species of the crow family from the South Pacific .
Neoechinorhynchida is an order of parasitic worms from the ( phylum Acanthocephala ) .
Tinodontidae is an extinct family of actively mobile mammal , endemic to what would now be North America , Asia , Europe , and Africa during the Jurassic and Cretaceous periods .
Cissampelos pareira ( velvetleaf ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Menispermaceae .
The Rana Marsupial ( Gastrotheca testudinea ) is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
Akysis pulvinatus is a species of stream catfish .
Rosa moschata , the musk rose , is a species of rose long in cultivation .
Penicillium smithii is a species of the genus of Penicillium which produces citreoviridin and canescin Penicillium smithii occurs in soil in Canada and Europe
Amblydoras is a genus of thorny catfishes native to rivers in tropical South America .
Andrewsianthus ferrugineus is a species of liverwort in the family Scapaniaceae .
Delftia is a genus of comamonad bacteria .
The Flea - frog ( Brachycephalus hermogenesi ) is a species of frog in the Brachycephalidae family .
Gymnadenia is a genus in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) containing 22 terrestrial species .
The Brymer 's Dendrobium ( Dendrobium brymerianum ) is a species of orchid .
Oncorhynchus lacustris ( syn . Rhabdofario lacustris ) is an extinct species of prehistoric freshwater trout from the late Miocene to late Pliocene of Western North America .
Polygonum austiniae , common name Mrs. Austin 's knotweed , is a plant species in the buckwheat family .
Apistoloricaria listrorhinos is a species of armored catfish endemic to Colombia where it is found in the Metica River basin .
The former genus Kurodaconus Shikama & Habe , 1968 Shell characters ( living and fossil species ) The shell is pyriform with angulate shoulders and an elevated scalariform spire .
Psorosticha is a moth genus of the superfamily Gelechioidea .
Sphaeromeria cana ( recently proposed name Artemisia albicans ) is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name gray chickensage .
Quercus alnifolia , commonly known as the golden oak , is an evergreen oak species of Cyprus .
Aethalochroa simplicipes is a species of praying mantis found in India that was originally identified as a variety of A. ashmoliana .
The Austrochiloidea or austrochiloids are a group of araneomorph spiders , treated as a superfamily .
Zabrus lycius is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that can be found in Dodecanese islands and in Near East .
Aegiphila caymanensis is a species of mint endemic to Grand Cayman .
Gagea pratensis , called the Yellow Star of Bethlehem , is a European and Mediterranean plant species in the lily family .
Monia zelandica , is a species of marine bivalve mollusc in the family Anomiidae , the jingle shells .
Allium kurssanovii is a species of wild onion native to Central Asia ( Xinjiang , Kazakhstan , and Kyrgyzstan ) .
Dactylosurculus gomoni is a species of viviparous brotula , the only known member of its genus , found in the waters of the Indian Ocean off the coast of western Australia .
Hastula strigilata , common name the strigate auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Hypolepis sparsisora is an Afrotropical fern species with an extensive range in Africa and Madagascar , where it occurs at diverse altitudes .
Pachypodistes angulata is a species of snout moth in the genus Pachypodistes .
Scholtzia oligandra , commonly known as Pink Scholtzia , is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae .
Hexabothriidae is a family of monogenean parasites .
Divaricella dentata , or the dentate lucine , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Lucinidae .
Festuca dolichophylla is a species of grass which is endemic to western South America with an occurrence in Costa Rica .
Hippocampus slovenicus is an extinct species of seahorse found in 2005 in the coprolitic horizon of the Tunjice hills Lagerstätte in Slovenia along with remains of the related species Hippocampus sarmaticus .
Nebria lewisi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Kikuma , Ehime of Japan .
Sporosarcina ureae forms endospores ( like all species of the genus ) .
Imbricaria olivaeformis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miter shells or miter snails .
Helicigona lapicida is a species of medium - sized , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , the typical snails .
Muscari is a genus of perennial bulbous plants native to Eurasia that produce spikes of dense , most commonly blue , urn - shaped flowers resembling bunches of grapes in the spring .
Zodarion lutipes is a spider species found in Cyprus , Israel , Lebanon and Jordan .
Sematophyllaceae is a family of mosses .
Paedogobius kimurai is a species of fish in the goby family , Gobiidae , and the only member of the monotypic genus Paedogobius .
Synodontis woleuensis is a species of upside - down catfish native to Equatorial Guinea and Gabon , where it is known only from the Woleu River , after which it was named , and the Kyé River .
Viburnum lantana ( wayfarer or wayfaring tree ) is a species of Viburnum , native to central , southern and western Europe ( north to Yorkshire in England ) , northwest Africa , and southwestern Asia .
Ecbolium viride is a species of Ecbolium of the family Acanthaceae .
Anomalocaris ( `` abnormal shrimp '' ) is an extinct genus of anomalocaridid , a family of animals thought to be closely related to ancestral arthropods .
Chrysiptera hemicyanea , known commonly as the azure damselfish , azure demoiselle , half - blue demoiselle , and yellow - dipped damsel , is a species of damselfish .
Lobophyllia , commonly called lobed brain coral or lobo coral , is a genus of large polyp stony corals .
Apocheima strigataria , the small phigalia moth , is a species of moth of the family Geometridae .
Polyrhachis convexa is a species of ant in the subfamily Formicinae , found in India , Sri Lanka , and China .
The Neopilionidae are a family of harvestmen with 15 known species .
Odontostomias is a genus of barbeled dragonfishes .
Caecilia subnigricans is a species of amphibian in the Caeciliidae family .
Bonnetia is a genus of flowering plants in the family Bonnetiaceae .
The Kneriidae are a small family of freshwater gonorhynchiform fishes native to Africa .
Hypolophota oodes is a species of snout moth in the genus Hypolophota .
Lycopodium fastigiatum , commonly known as alpine club moss or mountain club moss , is a species of club moss native to New Zealand and Australia .
Gliophorus reginae is a species of agaric fungus in the family Hygrophoraceae .
The Gastrotheca longipes ( also known as the Pastaza Marsupial Frog or Rana Marsupial ) is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
Micropyropsis is a genus of Spanish and Moroccan plants in the grass family .
Cnephia is a genus of 9 species of black flies , They are distributed in scattered locations across the Northern Hemisphere , from Ukraine to Eastern Siberia , and some parts of North America .
Barbicambarus simmonsi is a species of giant crayfish discovered in southern Tennessee in 2010 .
Heuchera rubescens , with common name is pink alumroot , is a species of Heuchera .
Homo antecessor is an extinct human species ( or subspecies ) dating from 800,000 to 1.2 million years ago , that was discovered by Eudald Carbonell , Juan Luis Arsuaga and J. M. Bermúdez de Castro .
When described the genus contained a single Ypresian - age species Microberotha macculloughi .
Norasaphus monroeae is a species of trilobite named after Marilyn Monroe for its hourglass - like shape
Agastache urticifolia is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name nettle - leaf giant hyssop or horse nettle .
Vallentinia gabriellae , the hitch - hiking jellyfish , is a species of small , inconspicuous jellyfish in the family Olindiidae .
Hoplocorypha nana is a species of praying mantis found in Uganda and Zululand .
Partula taeniata , common name the Moorean viviparous tree snail , is a species of gastropod in the Partulidae family .
Tetanops apicalis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Tetanops of the family Ulidiidae .
Ozyptila perplexa is a crab spider species found in Spain , France and Algeria .
Solariella peramabilis , common name the lovely Pacific margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
The Lythraceae are a family of flowering plants , including about 620 species of mostly herbs , with some shrubs and trees , in 31 genera .
Metaspriggina is a genus of chordate initially known from two specimens in the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale and 44 specimens found in 2012 at the Marble Canyon bed in Kootenay National Park .
Homola barbata is a species of crab in the family Homolidae .
Micranthes nidifica is a species of saxifrage known by the common name peak saxifrage .
Anatoma gunteri , common name Gunther 's split shell , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Anatomidae .
The Stephens Island wren was long remembered in local mythos as the only known species to be entirely wiped out by a single living being : the local lighthouse keeper 's cat , named Tibbles .
Megacephala biimpressicollis is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Mandl in 1960 , and can be found only in Bolivia and Brazil .
Bembix is a large cosmopolitan genus of large , often brightly colored predatory sand wasps , consisting of about 380 species .
Ong Sheng - keng and Yu Ching - kin were the first Taiwanese researchers to publish a journal article on Lepidoptera when they described Actias neidhoeferi as a new species .
Zenobia cassinefolia is a North American species of shrubs , in the genus Zenobia , in the heath family .
It contains only one species , Melisoides lobata , which is found in Cameroon , the Democratic Republic of Congo and Equatorial Guinea .
Haplochromis macrocephalus is a species of cichlid endemic to the Tanzanian portion of Lake Victoria where it is found in Mwanza Gulf and Speke Gulf .
Hypsilurus is a genus of arboreal agamid lizards from Melanesia and eastern Australia .
Lyallia kerguelensis , commonly called the Lyallia Cushion ( Coussin de Lyallia in French ) , is a species of flowering cushion plant in the monotypic genus Lyallia in the Montiaceae family .
Oxyothespis noctivaga is a species of praying mantis in the genus Oxyothespis in the order Mantodea .
The Potyviridae are a family of viruses that encompasses more than 30 % of known plant viruses , many of which are of great agricultural significance .
Freesia alba is a species of flowering plant in the iris family .
Megacephala carolina is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Linnaeus in 1766 .
Livistona saribus , commonly known as taraw palm , is a species of palm tree found in Southeast Asia ( Cambodia , Laos , Thailand , Vietnam , Borneo , Java . Peninsular Malaysia and the Philippines ) .
The family Sciomyzidae belongs to the typical flies ( Brachycera ) of the order Diptera .
Bossiaea is a genus in the pea family ( Fabaceae ) consisting of about 70 species which are native to Australia .
Pelargonium rodneyanum , commonly known as magenta storksbill , is a perennial herb species that is endemic to Australia .
Cyathea insulana is a species of tree fern native to New Guinea , where it grows in mossy forest and ravines at an altitude of 750 - -1600 m. The trunk of this species is erect , 8 - -10 m tall , and 14 cm in diameter .
Stylidium divergens is a dicotyledonous plant that belongs to the genus Stylidium ( family Stylidiaceae ) that was described as a new species in 2000 .
Damasonium minus is a species of flowering plant in the water - plantain family known by the common names starfruit and star - fruit ( not to be confused with the cultivated starfruit ) .
Storeini , or flower weevils , is a tribe of true weevils ( Curculionidae ) .
Neritopsis is a genus of sea snails in the family Neritopsidae .
Maytenus ponceana , Ponce mayten , is a species of plant in the Celastraceae family .
Ephippioceratidae is a family of clydonatilacean nautilids with shells as in the Liroceratidae but with sutures that have deep ventral and dorsal saddles .
Neobarynotus microlepis is a species of cyprinid fish found is Southeast Asia .
Aubria subsigillata , commonly known as the brown ball frog or the West African brown frog , is a species of frog belonging to the family Pyxicephalidae .
Drosera cuneifolia is a small rosette - forming species of perennial sundew native to the Cape in South Africa .
Beaufortia kweichowensis is a species of gastromyzontid loach native to rivers in China .
Steneotarsonemus spinki , the panicle rice mite , spinki mite , or rice tarsonemid mite , is a species of mite in the family Tarsonemidae , the white mites .
Carex tricephala is a species in the genus Carex , family Cyperaceae .
Gladiolus italicus is a species of gladiolus known by the common names Italian gladiolus , field gladiolus , and common sword - lily .
Malawimonadidae is a eukaryotic family .
Bougainvillia frondosa is a marine invertebrate , a species of hydroid in the suborder Anthomedusae .
Barbus macrotaenia ( broadband barb ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
Sepia acuminata is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Indian Ocean , from Port Elizabeth , South Africa to Somalia ( 01º30'N--30ºS ) , and Madagascar .
Wasps of the cosmopolitan genus Polistes ( the only genus in the tribe Polistini ) are the most familiar of the polistine wasps , and are the most common type of paper wasp in North America .
Sauries are fish of the family Scomberesocidae .
Trema lamarckiana , the Lamarck 's trema or West Indian nettle tree , is a species of a plant in the Cannabaceae family belonging to a genus of Treme Lour .
Natrix is a genus of colubrid snakes .
Leptobrycon jatuaranae is a species of characin endemic to Brazil , where it occurs in the Amazon River basin .
Picoides is a genus of woodpeckers ( family Picidae ) found primarily in North America .
Streptomyces flavofungini is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from desert sand .
Agyneta proxima is a species of sheet weaver found in Colombia .
Haplochromis omnicaeruleus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria where it is known from the southeastern portion of the lake .
Oberea bivittata is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Aurivillius in 1911 .
Zapsalis is a genus of dromaeosaurine theropod dinosaurs .
Centrolene antioquiense ( common name : Antioquia giant glass frog ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family .
Gyroporus purpurinus is a species of bolete fungus in the family Gyroporaceae .
Pachites is a genus of flowering plants in the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Actinodaphne malaccensis is a species of tree in the laurel family , Lauraceae .
Longitarsus curtus is a species of leaf beetle in the subfamily Galerucinae that can be found everywhere in Europe ( except for Liechtenstein , Norway , Switzerland , Portugal and the island of Sardinia ) .
Ogilbia suarezae is a species of fish of the genus Ogilbia found in the shallows of the Caribbean Sea .
Stenotosaurus is an extinct genus of capitosaurian temnospondyl within the family Mastodonsauridae .
Thrixspermum is a genus of orchids , comprising around 150 species distributed from India to Southeast Asia and New Guinea .
Timbellus phaneus , common name : the Phaneus Murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Allium petraeum is an Asian species of wild onion native to Xinjiang , Kyrgyzstan , and Kazakhstan .
Liangshanella is genus of Cambrian bradoriid known from the Chengjiang biota and Burgess Shale .
Papilio oribazus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in eastern Madagascar .
Crataegus ater , known as the Nashville Hawthorn , is a species of hawthorn that grows as a shrub or tree , native to the Great Lakes region of North America .
It contains the single species Eugraphosia rubrizonea , which is found in Peru .
Oophaga is a genus of poison - dart frogs containing nine species , many of which were formerly in the Dendrobates genus .
Ephedra holoptera is a species of Ephedra that is native to Iran .
Gulella mayottensis was a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Streptaxidae .
Zanha africana , Velvet - fruited zanha is a species of fruit plants from Sapindaceae family which can be found in Angola , Kenya , Mozambique , Zimbabwe , and the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is used as door frame and tool handles .
Arrhoges occidentalis , common name the American pelicanfoot , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Aporrhaidae , the pelican 's foot snails or pelican 's foot shells .
Platanthera orbiculata , the lesser roundleaved orchid , is a species of orchid native to forested areas of North America .
Caloria is a genus of colorful sea slugs , aeolid nudibranchs .
Globigerina is a genus of planktonic Foraminifera that have populated the world 's oceans since the Late Eocene .
Scarus is a genus of parrotfish .
Colanthelia is a genus of South American bamboo in the grass family , native to southern Brazil and northeastern Argentina .
Volucella zonaria , the hornet mimic hoverfly , is a European species of hoverfly .
The Mutillidae are a family of more than 3,000 species of wasps ( despite the names ) whose wingless females resemble large , hairy ants .
Edwardsiella tarda is also found in largemouth bass and freshwater species such as rainbow trout .
It was described by Harrington in 1957 , and the type species is Kanoshia kanoshensis , which was originally described under the genus Pseudomera by Hintze in 1953 .
Psychroteuthis glacialis , the glacial squid , is the only known species in the monotypic genus Psychroteuthis , in the family Psychroteuthidae .
Egernia kingii , King 's skink , is a species of skink native to coastal regions of south - western Australia common on Rottnest Island and Penguin Island and some coastal areas with open forest and open heath .
Penthaleidae , also referred to as earth mites , are a family of mites that are major winter pests of a variety of crops and pastures in southern Australia .
Samoana hamadryas , common name the `` Polynesian tree snail '' , is a species of tropical , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial , pulmonate , gastropod mollusc in the family Partulidae .
Perideridia oregana is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names Oregon yampah and eppaw .
Betula pubescens ' Pendula ' , or Weeping Downy Birch , is a weeping tree and a cultivar of Betula pubescens , the Downy Birch .
The Megaviridae are a proposed family of double - stranded DNA viruses that have not been recognized by the ICTV .
Cyathea propinqua is a species of tree fern native to Fiji and possibly Samoa , where it grows in wet forest .
Voltziales is an extinct order of trees related to modern conifers .
Paracroton pendulus is a species of flowering plant in the family Euphorbiaceae that is endemic to Western Ghats of India and Sri Lanka .
Arabidopsis lyrata is a species of flowering plant in the family Brassicaceae , closely related to the model organism Arabidopsis thaliana .
Stichopogon is a genus of small robber flies of the subfamily Dasypogoninae .
The Spurrell 's free - tailed bat ( Mops spurrelli ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae named after Herbert George Flaxman Spurrell .
Draba serpentina is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name serpentine draba .
Larix decidua , common name European larch , is a species of larch native to the mountains of central Europe , in the Alps and Carpathian Mountains , with disjunct lowland populations in northern Poland and southern Lithuania .
Pristimantis acerus ( common name : Papallacta robber frog ) is a frog species from South America .
Orthochromis machadoi , the Cunene dwarf happy , is a species of cichlid native to Angola and Namibia , where it is known from the Cunene River system .
Malacoctenus margaritae , the Margarita blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of Central America from Costa Rica to Panama .
Lippia alba is a species of flowering plant in the verbena family , Verbenaceae , that is native to southern Texas in the United States , Mexico , the Caribbean , Central America , and South America .
Benthodorbis pawpela is a species of minute freshwater snail with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Glacidorbidae .
Uenanthracus perigonoides is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Uenanthracus .
Tagetes micrantha is a North American species wild marigolds within the daisy family ( Asteraceae ) , common name licorice marigold .
Maotianoascus octonarius is an extinct species of stem - group ctenophore , known from the Chinese Maotianshan shales of Yunnan .
Hypolysia usambarica is a species of small tropical air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Subulinidae .
Aphaenogaster sommerfeldti is an extinct species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae known from a group of Middle Eocene fossils found in Europe .
Athyrium filix - femina ( lady fern or common lady - fern ) is a large , feathery species of fern native throughout most of the temperate Northern Hemisphere , where it is often abundant ( one of the more common ferns ) in damp , shady woodland environments and is often grown for decoration .
Bulis bivittata is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Bulis .
Gagea peduncularis is a Mediterranean plant species in the lily family .
Farriolla is a genus of fungi in the Ascomycota phylum .
Mimulus moschatus is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name muskflower .
Schnusimyia parvula is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Schnusimyia of the family Ulidiidae .
The Tettigarctidae , also known as the hairy cicadas , are a small relict ( mostly extinct ) family of primitive cicadas , containing a single genus Tettigarcta , with two extant species , one in southern Australia ( Tettigarcta crinita ) , and the other in Tasmania ( Tettigarcta tomentosa ) .
Lobiger viridis is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Oxynoidae .
The Mount Cameroon forest shrew ( Sylvisorex morio ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae endemic to Cameroon .
Penicillium purpurescens is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil in Canada .
Schultzites axelrodi is a species of characin endemic to Colombia , where it is found in the upper Meta River basin .
Miomantis ehrenbergi is a species of praying mantis in the genus Miomantis in the order Mantodea , in Africa .
Pelvicachromis taeniatus is a species of cichlid from Cameroon and Nigeria that is occasionally kept as an aquarium fish .
Leach orchids ( genus Stelis ) is a large group of orchids , with perhaps 500 species .
Lapparentosaurus is a genus of macronarian sauropod dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic .
Gigantspinosaurus ( meaning `` giant - spined lizard '' ) is a genus of herbivorous ornithischian dinosaur from the Late Jurassic .
Cirsium perplexans is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Rocky Mountain thistle and Adobe Hills thistle .
Thecideida is an order of cryptic articulate brachiopods characterized by their small size and habit of cementing their ventral valves to hard substrates such as shells , rocks and carbonate hardgrounds .
Poposauridae is a family of large ( around 2.5 to 5 meters long ) carnivorous archosaurs which lived alongside dinosaurs during the Late Triassic .
Lysimachia pendens is a rare species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae known by the common name broad - leaf yellow loosestrife .
Sinocyclocheilus huanglongdongensis is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to China .
Advena charon is a species of air - breathing land snail or semi - slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Helicarionidae .

Dendrochilum magnum is a species of orchid , commonly known as the Large Dendrochilum , endemic to Philippines .
Virgatosphinctes is an extinct genus of ammonites , which lived in the Tithonian stage of the Jurassic period , from 150.8 to 140.2 Ma .

The type species is Texacephale langstoni ; its fossils were discovered in the Aguja Formation and described in 2010 by Longrich , Sankey and Tanke .

The Chelydridae are a family of turtles which has seven extinct and two extant genera .
Fissidens polypodioides is a species of moss first classified by Johannes Hedwig .
Renalia is a genus of extinct vascular plants from the Early Devonian ( around 420 to 390 million years ago ) .
Paschalococos disperta ( Rapa Nui palm or Easter Island palm ) , formerly Jubaea disperta , was the native cocoid palm species of Easter Island .
Taurocottus bergii is a species of sculpin native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Vanstraelenia chirophthalma , the African solenette , is a species of sole native to the Atlantic coast of Africa where it is found from Guinea - Bissau south to Angola .
Euspira nitida ( common name : Common necklace shell ) is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Naticidae , the moon snails .

Barbus ethiopicus is a species of ray - finned fish .
Calvatia oblongispora is a species of puffball from the genus Calvatia .
Pancratium maritimum , or sea daffodil , is a species of bulbous plant native to both sides of the Mediterranean region and Black Sea from Portugal , Morocco and the Canary Islands east to Turkey , Syria , Israel and the Caucasus .
Bihariosaurus ( meaning `` Bihor lizard '' ) was a genus of camptosaurid dinosaur from Late Cretaceous Romania .
Liolaemus atacamensis ( Atacama tree iguana ) is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Pasquiaornis is a prehistoric flightless bird genus from the Late Cretaceous .
Tympanopalpus dorsalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tympanopalpus .
Eugnosta erigeronana , the Fleabane Cochylid Moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Tachopteryx thoreyi , commonly known as the gray petaltail and Thorey 's grayback , is a species of dragonfly .
The Sapygidae are a family of solitary aculeate wasps .

Chrysostoma paradoxum , common name the orange - mouthed top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .

Malapterurus teugelsi is a species of electric catfish endemic to Guinea where it occurs in the Kogon River .
Proctonotidae is a family of sea slugs , nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs , in the clade Euthyneura .
The Bioko forest shrew or Isabella 's shrew ( Sylvisorex isabellae ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae found in Cameroon and Equatorial Guinea .
Kermes vermilio is one of the species of Kermes used to make the crimson dye also called kermes .
Nosferatu pantostictus , the Chairel cichlid , is a species of cichlid native to the Panuco River drainage of Mexico 's Atlantic coast where it is mostly found in moderately fast flowing rivers , slightly brackish , murky lakes and lagoons along the coast .
Eriogonum gossypinum is an uncommon species of wild buckwheat known by the common name cottony buckwheat .
Arunta is a genus of cicada in the thophini tribe of the Cicadinae subfamily and is allied to the genus Thopha .
Commersonia is a genus of trees and shrubs in the family Malvaceae .
Calycularia is the only genus of liverwort in the family Calyculariaceae .

Pseudolaureola atlantica , or the Spiky Yellow Woodlouse is a species of woodlouse endemic to St. Helena 's High Peak .

Leachia is a genus containing six species of glass squids .

Gonolabina is a genus of earwigs in the subfamily Anisolabidinae .
Digitalis laevigata , common name Grecian Foxglove or Giraffe Foxglove , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Digitalis , in the family Plantaginaceae .
Harperocallis flava , known by the common name Harper 's beauty , is a species endemic to Florida in the United States , where it is known mainly from the Apalachicola National Forest in the Panhandle .

Cantuaria dendyi is a species of trapdoor spider in the family Idiopidae .
Erosaria lamarckii , common name the Lamarck 's cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .

Chamaedorea elegans , the neanthe bella palm or parlour palm , is species of small palm tree native to the rainforests in Southern Mexico and Guatemala .
Sibbaldia procumbens is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name creeping sibbaldia .
Acanthochaenus luetkenii , the pricklefish , is a species of pricklefish found in the oceans at depths of from 1,655 to 5,397 metres ( 5,430 to 17,707 ft ) .
Furcodontichthys novaesi is the only species of the monotypic genus Furcodontichthys , a genus of armored catfish .
Allium subvillosum , Spring Garlic , is a European and North African species of wild onion native to southern Spain , the Balearic Islands , southern Portugal , Sicily and northern Africa ( Libya , Tunisia , Algeria , Morocco , the Azores , and the Canary Islands ) .
Propleopus is an extinct genus of marsupials .
Dioscorea bulbifera , the air potato , is a species of true yam in the yam family , Dioscoreaceae .
Penicillus capitatus is a species of green algae .
Benthoctopus is a genus of octopuses comprising around 25 species .
The Cliopsidae , common name sea angels , are a taxonomic family of small , free - swimming sea slugs , pelagic marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the order Opisthobranchia .

Oryctopleura arcuatalis is a moth of the family Pyralidae , and the only species in the genus Oryctopleura .
Ilex palawanica is a species of plant in the Aquifoliaceae family .
Albertoceras is an Early Ordovician ellesmoeroceratid genus with a small , slender , orthoconic to slightly endogastric shell ; some even tiny .
The Northern Sumatran rhinoceros ( Dicerorhinus sumatrensis lasiotis ) , also known as Chittagong rhinoceros or northern hairy rhinoceros was the most widespread subspecies of Sumatran rhinoceros , also the only known subspecies native to mainland Asia whilst the latter live in Indonesian islands .
Tetragnatha is a genus of spiders containing hundreds of species .
With a length of 1.6 metres ( 5 ft 4 in ) , Kvabebihyrax was much larger than modern hyraxes , comparable in size to larger species of the Paleogene genus Titanohyrax .
Nolina cismontana , the chaparral beargrass , chaparral nolina , California beargrass , Peninsular beargrass , or peninsular nolina , is a rare species of flowering plant of the Peninsular and Transverse Ranges in California .
Galathea squamifera , the black squat lobster , or Montagu 's plated lobster , is a species of squat lobster that lives in the north - east Atlantic Ocean and Mediterranean Sea .
Vespula flaviceps is a species of social wasp in the genus Vespula .
Bangasternus orientalis is a species of true weevil known as the yellow starthistle bud weevil .
Neocrepidodera peirolerii is a species of flea beetle from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in Austria , Bosnia and Herzegovina , France , Germany , Italy , Liechtenstein , Macedonia , Slovenia , and Switzerland .
Ochetellus epinotalis is a species of ant in the genus Ochetellus .
Prunum amygdalum , common name : the almond marginella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
The group was originally defined as a superfamily by L. D. Boonstra in 1962 to include the families Brithopodidae and Anteosauridae .
Urocoras munieri is a funnel weaver spider species found in Italy , Slovenia and Croatia .
Strain VK of Bacillus safensis is a salt - tolerant microbe , and can grow beyond the 0 - 10 % salt range for the general microbial species .
Mangifera rubropetala was a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family .
Hoffmann 's pika ( Ochotona hoffmanni ) is a species of mammal in the pika family , Ochotonidae , that is endemic to Mongolia .
Languriomorpha bicolor is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Languriomorpha .
Hylaeamys megacephalus , also known as Azara 's broad - headed oryzomys or the large - headed rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Hylaeamys of family Cricetidae , of which it is the type species .
Decachorda pomona is a species of moth of the family Saturniidae .
Synodontis vaillanti is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Central African Republic , where it is known only from the upper Ubangui River in the central Congo River basin .
Achatella is a genus of trilobite in the order Phacopida , which existed in what is now Ontario , Canada .
The Scottish crossbill was confirmed as a unique species in August 2006 , on the basis of having a distinctive bird song .
Triodanis biflora ( syn . Specularia biflora ) is a species of flowering plant native to the Americas and known commonly as small Venus ' looking - glass .
Ericameria compacta , Charleston Mountain goldenbush , is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Pterygodermatites ondatrae is a species of parasitic nematode in the genus Pterygodermatites .
Colpomenia sinuosa , the oyster thief or sinuous ballweed , is a brown alga species in the genus Colpomenia .

Nannacara aureocephalus is a species of cichlid endemic to French Guiana in South America where it occurs in the Approuague River basin .

Cheilosia albipila is a European and Asian species of hoverfly .
Espostoa is a genus of columnar cacti , comprising 16 species known from the Andes of southern Ecuador and Peru .
Procambarus liberorum is a species of crayfish endemic to Arkansas and Oklahoma .
Chorizanthe xanti is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name Riverside spineflower .
Ischnura posita , the fragile forktail , is a species of damselfly in the genus Ischnura .
Pseudocyphellaria is a genus of large , leafy lichens that are sometimes referred to as `` specklebelly '' lichens .
Ghilianella phasma is a species of assassin bug in the subfamily Emesinae .
The type species , Rocasaurus muniozi , was formally described by Salgado and Azpilicueta in 2000 .
Rhamnus globosa , the lokao , is a species of plant in the Rhamnaceae family .
Malleidae , or the hammer oysters , is a family of saltwater clams .
Quercus tarahumara ( also called Tarahumara oak ) is a species of trees in the beech family .
Lycopodium dendroideum , tree groundpine , is a North American species of clubmoss .
Pseudophichthys splendens , or the Purple - mouthed conger is a species of eel in the family Congridae .
Cephalomyidae is an extinct family of caviomorph rodents from South America .
Staphylococcus lutrae is a species of Gram - positive bacteria and a member of the genus Staphylococcus .
The Jamaican pewee ( Contopus pallidus ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Nemotelus nigrinus , the all - black snout , is a European species of soldier fly .
Asperula arvensis , known as blue woodruff , is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Ribes magellanicum is a South American species of shrubs in the currant family , found in Patagonia ( southern Chile and Argentina ) .
Sciades parkeri , the Gillbacker sea catfish , is a species of sea catfish found in coastal rivers in Brazil , French Guiana , Guyana , Suriname and Venezuela .
Copadichromis is a genus of haplochromine cichlids endemic to Lake Malawi in Eastern Africa .
Erica cabernetea is a plant species endemic to a small region in the Western Cape Province of South Africa .
Mimosophronica rufula is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimosophronica .
Lindbergella is a genus of plants in the grass family , found only on the Island of Cyprus in the Mediterranean .
Alticus anjouanae is a species of combtooth blenny ( family Blenniidae ) in the genus Alticus .
Protocaptorhinus is an extinct genus of Early Permian ( Cisuralian epoch captorinid ) known from Texas of the United States .
Ormocarpopsis is a genus of legume in the Fabaceae family , and was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Dalbergia clade of the Dalbergieae .
Scytalichthys miurus , the Short - tailed viper - eel , is a species of eel in the family Ophichthidae .
Priscilla hypsiomoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Priscilla .
Punctaconchus is a genus of microconchid tubeworms .
Megamastax is a genus of lobe - finned fish which lived during the late Silurian period , about 423 million years ago .
Campylonotoidea is a superfamily of shrimp , containing the two families Campylonotidae and Bathypalaemonellidae .
Hebe speciosa is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names New Zealand hebe , showy hebe , and showy - speedwell .
Dactylomys is the genus of South American bamboo rats or coro - coros .
Haliotis varia , common name the variable abalone or the common ear shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Handleyomys intectus , also known as the white - footed Handley 's mouse or Colombian rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Handleyomys of family Cricetidae .
Amphiura filiformis is a species of brittle star belonging to the family Amphiuridae .
Mesopsocus graecus is a species of Psocoptera from Mesopsocidae family that can be found in Cyprus , Greece , and North Aegean islands .
Musa jackeyi ( Johnstone River banana ) is a species of wild banana ( genus Musa ) .
Hymenophyllum megistocarpum is a species of fern in the family Hymenophyllaceae .
Erythronium helenae is a species of flowering plant in the lily family which is known by the common names Pacific fawn lily and St. Helena fawn lily .
The Lilian 's lovebird ( Agapornis lilianae ) , also known as Nyasa lovebird , is a small African parrot species of the lovebird genus .
Pseudonaja is a genus of venomous elapid snakes native to Australia .
Plagiobothrys fulvus is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names field popcornflower or fulvous popcornflower .
Ameles heldreichi is a species of praying mantis that lives in France , Italy , Spain , Croatia , Greece , Israel , Libya , Palestine , Turkey , and Cyprus .
The Sunda pangolin ( Manis javanica ) , also known as the Malayan or Javan pangolin , is a species of pangolin found in Southeast Asia , including Thailand , Indonesia ( Java , Sumatra , Borneo , and the Lesser Sunda Islands ) , Vietnam , Laos , Cambodia , Malaysia , and Singapore .
Pseudolithoxus is a genus of suckermouth armored catfishes native to South America where it is only found in Venezuela .
Lotosaurus is an extinct genus of sail - backed poposauroid known from Hunan Province of central China .
Krzyzanowskisaurus is the name given to a genus of archosaur from the Late Triassic .
Luzula piperi , commonly known as Piper 's woodrush is a perennial species of plant in the genus Luzula of the ( rush ) family Juncaceae .
Calystegia macrostegia , with the common names island false bindweed ' and island morning glory , is a species of morning glory in the Convolvulaceae family .
Draco maculatus , commonly known as the spotted flying dragon , is a species of agamid flying lizard endemic to Southeast Asia .
Toona calantas is a species of tree in the mahogany family .
Illex argentinus , commonly known as the Argentine shortfin squid , is a species of squid in the family Ommastrephidae .
Oophytum is a genus of succulent plants native to South Africa .
Derodontidae is a family of beetles , in its own superfamily , Derodontoidea , sometimes known as the tooth - necked fungus beetles .

Eucalyptus redunca , the black marlock , black - barked marlock , wandoo or myrtan , is a tree species in the genus Eucalyptus .

Hippoglossoides is a genus of righteye flounders native to the North Pacific and North Atlantic oceans .
Neocogniauxia hexaptera is a species of orchid in the subfamily Epidendroideae .
Anhinga species are found all over the world in warm shallow waters .
Phacellocera plumicornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Phacellocera .
Afrodynerus is an afrotropical genus of potter wasps .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Globonectria cochensis .
Cerithiopsis fusiformis is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from the Gulf of Mexico and the Caribbean Sea .
Anomiopus caputipilus is a species of true dung beetle that is endemic to Goiás and Mato Grosso in Brazil .
Schizocyathidae is a family of stony corals .
Cyanea shipmanii is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Shipman 's cyanea .
Citrullus is a genus of seven species of desert vines , among which Citrullus lanatus ( the watermelon ) is an important crop .
Copromorphidae , the `` tropical fruitworm moths '' is a family of insects in the lepidopteran order .
The Dermateaceae is a family of cup fungi .
Lathyrus vestitus is a species of wild pea known by the common name Pacific pea .
Macrarene californica , common name the Californian liotia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Liotiidae .
Lophiomus setigerus , the Blackmouth angler , is a species of goosefish found in the Indian and western Pacific Oceans where it occurs at depths of from 30 to 800 metres ( 98 to 2,625 ft ) .
Lasiancistrus caucanus is a species of armored catfish native to Panama and Colombia .
Hammatoceratoidea , formerly Hammatocerataceae is a superfamily of middle Jurassic ammonites ( order Ammonitida ) , erected by Schindewolf ( 1964 ) that combines the families Graphoceratidae , Hammatoceratidae , and Soninniidae .
Vicia hirsuta ( Hairy Tare , hairy vetch , tiny vetch ) is a species of flowering plant from the large genus Vicia .
Thunbergia laurifolia , the laurel clockvine or blue trumpet vine , is native to India ( Starr et al . , 2003 ) and the Indomalaya ecozone , the species occurs from Indochina to Malaysia ( Schonenberger , 1999 ) .
Chaetostoma lexa is a species of armored catfish only known from streams and rivers that feed into the Huallaga River near Tingo María , Leoncio Prado Province , Peru .
Hemiscyllium michaeli , ( leopard epaulette shark ) , is a species of bamboo shark in the genus Hemiscyllium .
Gnaphosa mcheidzeae is a ground spider species found in Georgia .
Brancasaurus is an extinct genus of plesiosaur from the Early Cretaceous of what is now Germany .
Aparallactus guentheri , or the black centipede - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .

Synaptidae is a family of sea cucumber that have no tube feet , tentacle ampullae , retractor muscles , respiratory trees , or cuvierian organs .
Nelson 's spiny pocket mouse ( Heteromys nelsoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Heteromyidae .
Androsace septentrionalis ( pygmyflower rockjasmine , pygmy - flower rock - jasmine , northern rockjasmine , Northern fairy candelabra , Chinese : bei dian di mei ) is a species of annual herbaceous plant in the Primrose family ( Primulaceae ) , native to North America , Asia , and Europe .
Liobranchia stria , the Minute clingfish , is a tiny species of clingfish native to reef environments around the island of Guam , the Marshall Islands and the Northern Marianas Islands .
Rothia dentocariosa ( previously known as Stomatococcus mucilaginosus ) is a species of Gram - positive , round- to rod - shaped bacteria that is part of the normal community of microbes residing in the mouth and respiratory tract .

Heteroclinus wilsoni , Wilson 's weedfish , is a species of clinid found along the coast of southern Australia and Tasmania where it can be found in weedy reefs from the intertidal zone down to a depth of about 20 metres ( 66 ft ) .
Sepia typica is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Indian Ocean and southeastern Atlantic Ocean .
The superorder Peracarida is a large group of malacostracan crustaceans , having members in marine , freshwater , and terrestrial habitats .

Cerithideopsilla incisa is a species of medium - sized sea snail or mud snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Potamididae , the horn snails .
