Thiothrix is a genus of filamentous sulfur - oxidizing bacteria , related to the genera Beggiatoa and Thioploca .
Halicephalobus mephisto is a species of nematode , among a number of other roundworms , discovered by geoscientists Gaetan Borgonie and Tullis Onstott in 2011 .
Erigeron lonchophyllus is an Asian and North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name shortray fleabane .
Qianichthyosaurus is an extinct genus of Ichthyosaur from the late Triassic ( Carnian ) period .
Erethistoides cavatura is a species of South Asian river catfish endemic to Nepal where it is found in the Rapi River system of Narayani River basin .
Chamaerops is a genus of flowering plants in the family Arecaceae ( palm family ) , comprising a single species Chamaerops humilis ( European fan palm , Mediterranean dwarf palm or dwarf fan palm ) .
Galium porrigens is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common names graceful bedstraw and climbing bedstraw .
Arixenia camura is a species of earwigs , one of three species in the genus Arixenia .
Coriandrum is a genus of herbs in the Apiaceae family containing the cultivated species Coriandrum sativum ( coriander ) and the wild species Coriandrum tordylium .
Eriastrum is a genus of flowering plants in the phlox family which are known commonly as woollystars .
Parentelopes albomaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parentelopes .
Acroeimeria is a genus of protozoan parasites that contains those parasites which initially develop immediately beneath the brush - border of the intestinal epithelium , but the meronts and gamonts of which are early on extruded to form a layer on the surface of the gut mucosa .
Bulnesia carrapo is a species of plant in the Zygophyllaceae family .
Gongylophis muelleri , known commonly as the Saharan sand boa , is a species of snake in the Boidae family .

Labeobarbus intermedius intermedius is the only subspecies of Labeobarbus intermedius .

Pachyiulus varius is a species of millipede from Julidae family that can be found in Bulgaria , France , Greece , Italy , Romania , all states of former Yugoslavia and various European islands .
Paspalidium caespitosum , commonly known as Brigalow grass , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family native to inland eastern Australia , where it is found in the Brigalow Belt .

Oxynoemacheilus is a genus of stone loaches that are found in Europe and Western Asia .

Synaptotylus is an extinct genus of prehistoric sarcopterygian or lobe - finned fish from the Pennsylvanian .
Helenium amarum is a species of annual herb in the daisy family known by the common names yellowdicks , yellow sneezeweed , fiveleaf sneezeweed , and bitter sneezeweed .
Solenochilidae is a small family of Carboniferous and Early Permian nautilids , similar and related to the Aipoceratidae that comprises genera with whorls in contact and which develop laterally projecting umbilical spines by maturity .

Bactrocythara is a genus of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Mangeliidae .

Pseudopleuronectes is a genus of righteye flounders mostly native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean with one species ( P. americanus ) found in the northwestern Atlantic Ocean .

Ilybius montanus is a species of beetle native to Europe and North Africa .

Buddleja chapalana is a rare species endemic to the rocky cliffs bordering the northern and western shores of Lake Chapala , Jalisco , Mexico .
Macrurosaurus ( meaning `` large - tailed lizard '' ) is the name given to a genus of dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous .

Orthotheca is a genus of sessile bottom - dwelling hyolith .
Buchenavia is a genus of plant in family Combretaceae .
Epicauta rufidorsum ( Goeze , 1777 ) is a species of beetle of the family Meloidae .
Lonicera utahensis is a species of flowering plant in the honeysuckle family known by the common names Utah honeysuckle , red twinberry , and fly honeysuckle .
Motobdella montezuma is a species of leech which is only found in Montezuma Well , central Arizona , United States .
Plagiosauridae is a family of Temnospondyli that lived in the Triassic period .
Tornatellides subperforata is a species of minute , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk , in the family Achatinellidae .
Choriaster granulatus , commonly known as the granulated sea star , cushion seastar , and doughboy star , is a species of starfish .
The Fringed - lipped Dendrobium ( Dendrobium fimbriatum ) is a species of orchid .
Ipomoea violacea is a perennial species of Ipomoea that occurs throughout the world by the exception of European continent .
Cantharis fusca is a species of soldier beetle .
Berberis chiapensis is a shrub in the Berberidaceae family described as a species in 1940 .
Priscatoides tatila is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Priscatoides .
Solaster paxillatus , the orange sun star , is a species of starfish found at varying depths in the northern Pacific Ocean .
Chicomurex laciniatus , common name the laciniated murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
The Dory snapper , Lutjanus fulviflamma , also known as Blackspot snapper , is a species of snapper native to the Indian Ocean and into the Pacific Ocean as far east as Samoa .
Myrtillocactus geometrizans ( bilberry cactus , whortleberry cactus or blue candle ) is a species of cactus in the genus Myrtillocactus , native to central and northern Mexico .
Toxomerus geminatus , is a species of flower fly found from eastern Canada south to Texas .
Denticetopsis macilenta is a species of whale catfish endemic to Guyana where it is only known from a limited area in the Essequibo River basin .
Silene gallica is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by several common names , including common catchfly , small - flowered catchfly , and windmill pink .
Aeonium hierrense is a species in the genus Aeonium and has a stem but does not grow very tall .
The West Peruvian screech owl ( Megascops roboratus ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Banksia attenuata , commonly known as the candlestick banksia , slender banksia or biara as known by the Nyoongar Aboriginal people , is a species of plant in the proteaceae family .
Toxopeia demodes is a species of sedge moths , and the only species in the genus Toxopeia .
Spirobolidae is a family of millipedes in the order Spirobolida .
Calais parreysii is a species of click beetle belonging to the family Elateridae subfamily Agrypninae .
Epitonium tenellum , common name the small wentletrap , is a species of small ectoparasitic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Epitoniidae , the wentletraps .
Aplysia depilans , the `` depilatory sea hare '' , is a species of sea hare or sea slug , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Aplysiidae .
Charaxes kirki is a member of the Charaxes etheocles species group .
The South China sika deer ( Cervus nippon kopschi ) is one of many subspecies of sika deer .
Neolamprologus olivaceous is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known from Ruhanga Bay in the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Cenchritis muricatus is a species of sea snail in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
Acoetidae is a family of polychaete worms in the subclass Aciculata .
Phymosia umbellata is a species of flowering plant in the family Malvaceae .
Phytophthora pseudosyringae is a semi - papillate homothallic soil - borne plant pathogen causing root and collar rot of deciduous tree species in Europe .
Stonogobiops yasha , the Orange - striped shrimpgoby , is a species of goby native to the Western Pacific Ocean where it occurs at depths of from 15 to 40 metres ( 49 to 131 ft ) .
Myosotis laxa is a species of forget - me - not known by several common names , including tufted forget - me - not , bay forget - me - not , and small - flowered forget - me - not .
The Peramelidae family of marsupials contains all of the extant bandicoots .
Galium matthewsii is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common names bushy bedstraw and Matthews ' bedstraw .
Platycheirus discimanus is a small species of hoverfly .
Stylophorum ( Celandine - poppy ) is a genus of three species of herbaceous perennial plants native to woodland in eastern North America and China .
Ventenata is a genus of plants in the grass family , native to Europe , North Africa , and central + southwest Asia .
Achyranthes atollensis ( also called atoll achyranthes or Hawaiʻi chaff flower ) was a species of plant in the Amaranthaceae family .
It is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Leucocortinarius bulbiger , found in Europe .
Inioteuthis capensis is a species of bobtail squid native to the southeastern Atlantic Ocean , specifically from Lüderitz Bay to Mossel Bay off South Africa .
Drilliola is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Borsoniidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Callilepis is a genus of gnaphosid spiders with about 20 described species .
Rana amurensis ( Khabarovsk frog , Siberian wood frog , Heilongjiang brown frog or Amur brown frog ) is a species of true frog found in northern Asia .
Ceriporia xylostromatoides is a species of fungus in the family Phanerochaetaceae .
Promethichthys prometheus , the Roudi escolar , is a species of snake mackerel native to the warm temperate and tropical waters of all the oceans where it occurs at depths of from 80 to 800 metres ( 260 to 2,620 ft ) ( mostly between 300 to 400 metres ( 980 to 1,310 ft ) ) .
Apterocerina argentea is a species of ulidiidae or picture - winged fly in the genus Apterocerina of the family Ulidiidae .
Chironex fleckeri , commonly known as sea wasp , is a species of box jellyfish found in coastal waters from northern Australia and New Guinea north to the Philippines and Vietnam .
Leyesaurus is an extinct genus of massospondylid sauropodomorph dinosaur known from the San Juan Province , northwestern Argentina .
Chiloschista , abbreviated Chsch in the horticultural trade , is a genus of orchid , comprising 20 currently recognized species native to China , the Indian Subcontinent , Southeast Asia , New Guinea , Australia , Fiji and Micronesia .
Greigia kessleri is a species in the genus Greigia .
Cyamus boopis is a species of whale louse in the family Cyamidae .
Ciliopagurus tenebrarum is a species of hermit crab native to Cape Comorin .
Perkinsidae is a family of protists in the phylum Perkinsozoa , a sister group to the dinoflagellates .
Bacteroides is a genus of gram - negative , obligate anaerobic bacteria .
Anthemis arvensis , also known as corn chamomile , mayweed , scentless chamomile , or field chamomile is a species of the genus Anthemis and in the Asteraceae family .
Monoclonius ( meaning `` single sprout '' ) is a dubious genus of herbivorous ceratopsian dinosaurs found in the Late Cretaceous layers of the Judith River Formation in Montana , northern US , and the uppermost rock layers of the Dinosaur Park Formation in Alberta , Canada dated to between 75 and 74.6 million years ago .
Cedrelinga cateniformis ( the Wyra Caspi or huaira Caspi ) is a flowering plant species in the genus Cedrelinga .
Glossoloma herthae is a plant species in the family Gesneriaceae .
Solidago satanica , the devil 's goldenrod , is a rare North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Serapias lingua , commonly known as tongue - orchid or the tongue Serapias , is a species of orchid native to the Mediterranean .
Vaccinium reticulatum , known as ʻŌhelo ʻai in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering plant in the heather family , Ericaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
The genus Umbravirus includes plant viruses assigned to the family Tombusviridae .
Rhus glabra , the smooth sumac , is a species of sumac in the family Anacardiaceae , native to North America , from southern Quebec west to southern British Columbia in Canada , and south to northern Florida and Arizona in the United States and Tamaulipas in northeastern Mexico .
Myosotis decumbens is a plant species of the genus Myosotis .
Oreophrynella ( bush toads ) is a genus of true toads native to the tepuis of southern Venezuela and adjacent Guyana .
Opeas hannense , common name the dwarf awlsnail , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Subulinidae .
Entoloma murrayi , commonly known as the yellow unicorn Entoloma or the unicorn pinkgill , is a species of fungus in the Entolomataceae family .
Synothele is a genus of spiders found in South Australia and Western Australia .
Quercus inopina , the sandhill oak , is an uncommon North American species of shrubs in the beech family .
Ophiclinus antarcticus , the Adelaide snakeblenny , is a species of clinid found in the coastal waters of southern Australia .
Azuragrion vansomereni is a species of damselfly in family Coenagrionidae .
Forresteria is an extinct genus of cephalopod belonging to the subclass Ammonoidea that flourished during the late Turonian and early Coniacian of the Late Cretaceous .
Pilosocereus royenii is a species of cactus that is native to the Caribbean and Mexico 's Yucatán Peninsula .
Acragas fallax is a species of jumping spider in the genus Acragas .
Bybe parmenoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Bybe .
Lystrosauridae is a family of dicynodont therapsids from the Permian and Triassic time periods .
Oliva multiplicata , common name the many - plaited olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
Perkinsus marinus is a species of protist belonging to the phylum Perkinsozoa .
Scutiger jiulongensis , also known as Juilong Cat - eyed Toad , is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Leptoglossus zonatus is a species of leaf - footed bug , a type of true bug .
Impatiens hawkeri ( New Guinea impatiens ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Balsaminaceae .
Synoeca septentrionalis is one of five species of wasps in the Synoeca genus .
Latridae is a family ( about 5 species ) of perciform fishes known as the Trumpeters .
Rhodocollybia butyracea , common name Buttery Collybia , is a species of fungus in the Marasmiaceae family of mushrooms .
Rasborichthys helfrichii is a species of cyprinid fish found on the islands of Sumatra and Borneo in Southeast Asia .
Aconogonon alaskanum is an Asian and North American species of flowering plants in the buckwheat family known by the common name Alaska wild - rhubarb .
Danacetichthys galathenus is a species of flabby whalefish found in the ocean depths at around 1,330 metres ( 4,360 ft ) .
Conus sculletti , common name Scullett 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Homosteus is a genus of flattened arthrodire placoderm from the Middle Devonian .
Astroloba corrugata is a compact Astroloba species , with slender , sprawling stems ( up to 20 cm long ) , densely covered in spirally arranged pointed leaves .
Pseudhepomidion assamense is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudhepomidion .
Elpistostegidae is an extinct family of tetrapod - like fish that lived in the Late Devonian period ( Late Givetian to Early Frasnian ) .
Lamellidea subcylindrica is a species of air - breathing tropical land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Achatinellidae .
Pterothecidae is an extinct family of Paleozoic molluscs of uncertain position , either Gastropoda or Monoplacophora , with isostrophically coiled shells .
Karl Terkal ( October 7 , 1919 , Vienna - August 12 , 1996 , Vienna ) was an Austrian operatic tenor , particularly associated with lyric roles of the German repertory , both opera and operetta .
David Ffrangcon - Davies , M.A. ( Oxon ) ( 11 December 1855 -- 13 April 1918 ) was a Welsh operatic baritone .
Gerhard Stolze ( 1 October 1926 , Dessau -- 11 March 1979 , Garmisch - Partenkirchen ) was a German tenor .
Marietta Sacchi was an Italian operatic soprano who had an active career during the 1820s and 1830s .
Ivo Žídek ( 4 June 1926 -- 19 May 2003 ) was a celebrated Czech lyric tenor , known for his vivid portrayals of character roles in the operas of Smetana , Dvořák and Janáček .
Annelies Burmeister ( 1928 - -1988 ) was a German contralto and actress .
Mila Vilotijević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Мила Вилотијевић ; born ? ) is a Serbian soprano .
Güneş Gürle ( born July 7 , 1975 in Izmir , Turkey ) is a Turkish opera singer , bass - baritone .
Giuseppina Finzi - Magrini ( Turin , 1878-Desio , 1944 ) was an Italian soprano .
Derek Lee Ragin ( born June 17 , 1958 ) is an American countertenor .
Ileana Cotrubaș ( Romanian pronunciation : ( iˈle̯ana kotruˈbaʃ ) ; born June 9 , 1939 ) is a Romanian opera soprano whose career spanned from the 1960s to the 1980s .
Emmy Destinn ( Ema Destinnová ( ( ˈɛma ˈdɛstɪnovaː ) ) ; 26 February 1878 -- 28 January 1930 ) was a Czech operatic soprano with a strong and soaring lyric - dramatic voice .
John Spray ( c.1768 -- 21 January 1827 ) was an acclaimed tenor singer , known for performing works by John Andrew Stevenson , who wrote a number of pieces for him including the popular Faithless Emma .
He Hui ( Chinese : 和慧 ; born 1972 in Xi'an ) , sometimes in the West known as Hui He , is a Chinese operatic soprano .
Theodor Lay was a nineteenth - century German operatic baritone who was particularly admired for his interpretations of the roles of Richard Wagner and Albert Lortzing .
Toby Spence ( born 22 May 1969 , London ) is a British tenor active internationally on the concert platform , in the opera house and in recordings across a wide range of classical music .
Maria Duchêne - Billiard ( 1884 - ? ) was a French contralto of the Metropolitan Opera from 1912 to 1916 .
Leona Mitchell ( born October 13 , 1949 , Enid , Oklahoma ) , is an African - American and Chickasaw operatic soprano and an Oklahoma Music Hall of Fame inductee .
Mabel Garrison Siemonn ( April 24 , 1886 - August 20 , 1963 ) , was an American coloratura soprano who sang at the Metropolitan Opera from 1914 to 1921 .
Karel Strakatý ( 2 July 1804 -- 26 April 1868 ) was a Czech operatic bass who had a lengthy career at the Estates Theatre in Prague from 1827 until his retirement in 1858 .
Philipp Stolle ( 1614 -- 4 October 1675 ) was a German composer , tenor and theorbo player of the Baroque era .
Laura Claycomb ( born August 23 , 1968 ) is an American lyric coloratura soprano opera singer .
Isabella Young ( also Isabella Scott ) ( 17 ? , London -- 12 August 1791 , London ) was an English mezzo - soprano and organist who had a successful career as a concert performer and opera singer during the latter half of the eighteenth century .
Dinara Aliyeva ( Azerbaijani : Dinarə Əliyeva , Russian : Динара Алиева ) ( born 17 December 1980 , Baku , Azerbaijan ) is an Azerbaijani operatic soprano .
Dorothy Warenskjold ( May 11 , 1921 in San Leandro , California -- December 27 , 2010 in Lenexa , Kansas ) was an American lyric soprano who had an active career in operas and concerts from the mid-1940s through the early 1960s .
Max Ciolek ( born 4 November 1959 ) is a German tenor and conductor .
Deon van der Walt ( 28 July 1958 -- 29 November 2005 ) , was a South African tenor .
Kate Aldrich ( b. October 31 , 1973 , Damariscotta , Maine ) is an American mezzo soprano .
Lutz - Michael Harder ( born 1951 , Langenfeld / Długoszyn near Küstrin ) is a German lyric tenor known mostly for his interpretation of Mozart opera roles and as a baroque concert soloist .
Antoinette Miggiani ( born 5 September 1937 ) is a Maltese operatic soprano and singing teacher .
Gilbert Duprez ( 6 December 1806 -- 23 September 1896 ) was a French tenor , singing teacher and minor composer who famously pioneered the delivery of the operatic high C from the chest .
Monica Groop ( born 14 April 1958 , Helsinki ) is a Finnish operatic mezzo - soprano .
Tito Gobbi ( 24 October 1913 -- 5 March 1984 ) was an Italian operatic baritone with an international reputation .
Charles Courtice Pounds ( 30 May 1862 -- 21 December 1927 ) , better known by the stage name Courtice Pounds , was an English singer and actor known for his performances in the tenor roles of the Savoy Operas with the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company and his later roles in Shakespeare plays and Edwardian musical comedies .
Bruce Boyce ( 1910 in London , Ontario -- 11 May 1996 ) was a prominent Canadian - born American baritone singer of opera , oratorio and lieder , who made his postwar career in Britain and became a professor at the Royal Academy of Music .
Ferruccio Tagliavini ( pronounced ( ferˈruttʃo taʎʎaˈviːni ) ; 14 August 1913 -- 28 January 1995 ) was an Italian operatic tenor mainly active in the 1940s and 1950s .
Oleg Bryjak ( Ukrainian : Олег Брижак , 27 October 1960 -- 24 March 2015 ) was a Kazakhstani - German bass - baritone opera singer .
Isabel Bayrakdarian ( born 1974 in Zahlé , Lebanon ) is an Armenian - Canadian operatic soprano .
Gérard Souzay ( 8 December 1918 -- 17 August 2004 ) was a French baritone , regarded as one of the very finest interpreters of mélodie ( French art song ) in the generation after Charles Panzéra and Pierre Bernac .
Anne Chabanceau de La Barre ( 1628 - -1688 ) was a French soprano of the baroque era .
Oszkár Kálmán ( 19 June 1887 - 17 September 1971 ) was a Hungarian bass , remembered as the first Bluebeard .
Robert Tear , ( pronounced to rhyme with `` hear '' ) CBE ( 8 March 1939 -- 29 March 2011 ) was a Welsh tenor singer , teacher and conductor .
Edda Moser ( born 27 October 1938 ) is a German coloratura soprano .
Etelka Gerster ( 25 June 1855 , Košice -- 20 August 1920 , Pontecchio ) was a Hungarian soprano .
Jack Harrold ( June 10 , 1920 -- July 22 , 1994 ) was an American operatic tenor and voice teacher .
